OPTION.en: One of a set of choices that can be made.
OPTION.zh: 可以做出的一组选择之一。

SEA.en: A large body of salt water.

BUILT.en: To form (something) by combining materials or parts.
BUILT.zh: 通过组合材料或零件形成（某物）。

BLOOD.en: A member of the Los Angeles gang The __s.

IMPROVE.en: To make (something) better; to increase the value or productivity (of something).
IMPROVE.zh: 使（某事）变得更好；增加（某物）的价值或生产力。

LARGER.en: Of considerable or relatively great size or extent.
LARGER.zh: 具有相当大或相对较大的规模或范围。

ANTI.en: A person opposed to a concept or principle.
ANTI.zh: 反对某个概念或原则的人。

NETWORKS.en: A fabric or structure of fibrous elements attached to each other at regular intervals.
NETWORKS.zh: 纤维元素以规则的间隔相互连接的织物或结构。

EARTH.en: The third planet of the Solar System; the world upon which humans live.
EARTH.zh: 太阳系第三颗行星；人类赖以生存的世界。

PARENTS.en: One of the two persons from whom one is immediately biologically descended; a mother or father.
PARENTS.zh: 两个人中的一个，其中一个在生物学上是直接后裔；母亲或父亲。

TRANSFER.en: The act of conveying or removing something from one place, person or thing to another.
TRANSFER.zh: 将某物从一个地方、人或物转移或移至另一个地方的行为。

STRONG.en: Capable of producing great physical force.

WEDDING.en: To perform the marriage ceremony for; to join in matrimony.
WEDDING.zh: 为以下人士举行婚礼；加入婚姻。

SHIP.en: A water-borne vessel generally larger than a boat.
SHIP.zh: 通常比船大的水上船只。

PAID.en: To give money or other compensation to in exchange for goods or services.
PAID.zh: 给予金钱或其他补偿以换取商品或服务。

HAIR.en: A pigmented filament of keratin which grows from a follicle on the skin of humans and other mammals.
HAIR.zh: 一种有色角蛋白丝，从人类和其他哺乳动物皮肤上的毛囊中生长出来。

KIT.en: A circular wooden vessel, made of hooped staves.
KIT.zh: 一种圆形木器，由箍筋制成。

CITIES.en: A large settlement, bigger than a town; sometimes with a specific legal definition, depending on the place.
CITIES.zh: 一个比城镇还大的大型定居点；有时根据地点有具体的法律定义。

EXPRESS.en: A mode of transportation, often a train, that travels quickly or directly.
EXPRESS.zh: 一种快速或直达的交通方式，通常是火车。

AWARD.en: A judgment, sentence, or final decision. Specifically: The decision of arbitrators in a case submitted.
AWARD.zh: 判决、判决或最终决定。具体来说：仲裁员对所提交案件的决定。

DISTANCE.en: The amount of space between two points, usually geographical points, usually (but not necessarily) measured along a straight line.
DISTANCE.zh: 两点（通常是地理点）之间的空间量，通常（但不一定）沿直线测量。

TREE.en: Fast growing function based on Kruskal's __ theorem.
TREE.zh: 基于克鲁斯卡尔树定理的快速增长函数。

ENSURE.en: To make a pledge to (someone); to promise, guarantee (someone of something); to assure.
ENSURE.zh: 向（某人）做出承诺；承诺、保证（某人某事）；来保证。

WALL.en: A rampart of earth, stones etc. built up for defensive purposes.
WALL.zh: 为防御目的而用土、石等筑成的城墙。

INVOLVED.en: To roll or fold up; to wind round; to entwine.
INVOLVED.zh: 卷起或折叠起来；绕圈；缠绕。

EXTRA.en: Something additional, such as an item above and beyond the ordinary school curriculum, or added to the usual charge on a bill.
EXTRA.zh: 额外的东西，例如超出普通学校课程的项目，或添加到账单上的通常费用中。

PARTNERS.en: Someone who is associated with another in a common activity or interest.
PARTNERS.zh: 与他人有共同活动或兴趣的人。

BUDGET.en: The amount of money or resources earmarked for a particular institution, activity or time-frame.
BUDGET.zh: 指定用于特定机构、活动或时间范围的资金或资源数量。

RATED.en: To assign or be assigned a particular rank or level.
RATED.zh: 分配或被分配特定的军衔或级别。

GUIDES.en: Someone who __, especially someone hired to show people around a place or an institution and offer information and explanation.
GUIDES.zh: 提供指导的人，尤其是受雇带人们参观某个地方或机构并提供信息和解释的人。

QUITE.en: (heading) To the greatest extent or degree; completely, entirely.
QUITE.zh: （标题）最大范围或程度；完全地，完全地。

SELECTED.en: To choose one or more elements of a set, especially a set of options.
SELECTED.zh: 选择一组中的一个或多个元素，尤其是一组选项。

PATIENTS.en: A person or animal who receives treatment from a doctor or other medically educated person.
PATIENTS.zh: 接受医生或其他受过医学教育的人员治疗的人或动物。

WINE.en: An alcoholic beverage made by fermenting the juice of grapes.
WINE.zh: 通过发酵葡萄汁制成的酒精饮料。

HORSE.en: Any of several animals related to Equus ferus caballus.
HORSE.zh: 与马属（Equus ferus caballus）有关的几种动物中的任何一种。

VOTE.en: A formalized choice on matters of administration or other democratic activities
VOTE.zh: 对行政事务或其他民主活动的正式选择

FORWARD.en: One of the eight players (comprising two props, one hooker, two locks, two flankers and one number eight, collectively known as the pack) whose primary task is to gain and maintain possession of the ball (compare back).
FORWARD.zh: 八名球员（包括两名支柱球员、一名勾手、两名锁卫、两名侧翼球员和一名八号球员，统称为“包”）中的一名球员，其主要任务是获得并保持控球权（比较）。

FLOWERS.en: A colorful, conspicuous structure associated with angiosperms, frequently scented and attracting various insects, and which may or may not be used for sexual reproduction.
FLOWERS.zh: 一种与被子植物相关的色彩缤纷、引人注目的结构，经常散发香味并吸引各种昆虫，可能会也可能不会用于有性繁殖。

STARS.en: Any small luminous dot appearing in the cloudless portion of the night sky, especially with a fixed location relative to other such dots.
STARS.zh: 出现在夜空无云部分的任何小发光点，尤其是相对于其他此类点具有固定位置的发光点。

LISTS.en: A strip of fabric, especially from the edge of a piece of cloth.
LISTS.zh: 一块布，特指一块布边缘的布条。

RETAIL.en: The sale of goods directly to the consumer, encompassing the storefronts, mail-order, websites, etc., and the corporate mechanisms, branding, advertising, etc. that support them.
RETAIL.zh: 直接向消费​​者销售商品，包括店面、邮购、网站等，以及支持它们的企业机制、品牌、广告等。

ANIMALS.en: In scientific usage, a multicellular organism that is usually mobile, whose cells are not encased in a rigid cell wall (distinguishing it from plants and fungi) and which derives energy solely from the consumption of other organisms (distinguishing it from plants).
ANIMALS.zh: 在科学用途中，多细胞生物体通常是可移动的，其细胞没有被坚硬的细胞壁包裹（与植物和真菌不同），并且仅从其他生物体的消耗中获取能量（与植物不同）。

USEFUL.en: Having a practical or beneficial use.
USEFUL.zh: 具有实际或有益的用途。

DIRECTLY.en: In a direct manner; in a straight line or course.
DIRECTLY.zh: 以直接的方式；沿直线或路线。

WAYS.en: (heading) To do with a place or places.
WAYS.zh: （标题）与一个或多个地方有关。

MAC.en: A waterproof long coat made of rubberized cloth.
MAC.zh: 由橡胶布制成的防水长外套。

TAKES.en: The or an act of taking.

TRYING.en: To attempt; to endeavour. Followed by infinitive.
TRYING.zh: 尝试；努力。后面接不定式。

TOLD.en: (archaic outside of idioms) To count, reckon, or enumerate.
TOLD.zh: （习语之外的古语）计数、推算或列举。

TRAFFIC.en: Pedestrians or vehicles on roads, or the flux or passage thereof.
TRAFFIC.zh: 道路上的行人或车辆，或其流动或通行。

JOINED.en: To connect or combine into one; to put together.
JOINED.zh: 连接或组合成一个；放在一起。

INPUT.en: The act or process of putting in; infusion.
INPUT.zh: 投入的行为或过程；输液。

STRATEGY.en: The science and art of military command as applied to the overall planning and conduct of warfare.
STRATEGY.zh: 军事指挥的科学和艺术应用于战争的总体规划和实施。

FEET.en: A biological structure found in many animals that is used for locomotion and that is frequently a separate organ at the terminal part of the leg.
FEET.zh: 在许多动物中发现的一种生物结构，用于运动，通常是腿末端的一个独立器官。

AGENT.en: One who exerts power, or has the power to act
AGENT.zh: 行使权力或有权力采取行动的人

VALID.zh: 有充分根据或合理、相关。

BIN.en: A box, frame, crib, or enclosed place, used as a storage container.
BIN.zh: 用作储存容器的盒子、框架、婴儿床或封闭的地方。

TEACHING.en: Something taught by a religious or philosophical authority.
TEACHING.zh: 由宗教或哲学权威教导的东西。

DOOR.en: A portal of entry into a building, room, or vehicle, consisting of a rigid plane movable on a hinge. __s are frequently made of wood or metal. May have a handle to help open and close, a latch to hold the __ closed and a lock that ensures the __ cannot be opened without the key.
DOOR.zh: 进入建筑物、房间或车辆的入口，由可通过铰链移动的刚性平面组成。门通常由木材或金属制成。可能有一个帮助打开和关闭的把手、一个用于保持门关闭的闩锁以及一个确保没有钥匙就无法打开门的锁。

GRAND.en: (plural "__") A thousand of some unit of currency, such as dollars or pounds. (Compare G.)
GRAND.zh: （复数“__”）一千种某种货币单位，例如美元或英镑。 （比较G。）

TRIAL.en: An opportunity to test something out; a test.
TRIAL.zh: 测试某些东西的机会；一个测试。

UNITS.en: A particular, minute unit of mass, defined differently for different substances, but so that varying substances of the same general type have the property that one international unit of the one has the same effect on the human body as one international unit of the other.
UNITS.zh: 一种特殊的微小质量单位，对不同物质的定义不同，但同一类型的不同物质具有这样的特性：一种国际单位与另一种国际单位对人体具有相同的影响。

COOL.en: A moderate or refreshing state of cold; moderate temperature of the air between hot and cold; __ness.
COOL.zh: 中度或清爽的寒冷状态；空气温度介于冷热之间；凉爽。

WROTE.en: To form letters, words or symbols on a surface in order to communicate.
WROTE.zh: 在表面上形成字母、单词或符号以进行交流。

SHIPS.en: A water-borne vessel generally larger than a boat.
SHIPS.zh: 通常比船大的水上船只。

LEADING.en: To cover, fill, or affect with lead

METAL.en: (heading) Chemical elements or alloys, and the mines where their ores come from.
METAL.zh: （标题）化学元素或合金，及其矿石来源的矿山。

FITNESS.en: The condition of being fit, suitable or appropriate.
FITNESS.zh: 适合、适合或适当的条件。

OUTPUT.en: Production; quantity produced, created, or completed.
OUTPUT.zh: 生产;生产、创建或完成的数量。

FUNDS.en: A sum or source of money.

GREATER.en: Relatively large in scale, size, extent, number (i.e. having many parts or members) or duration (i.e. relatively long); very big.
GREATER.zh: 规模、大小、范围、数量（即具有许多部分或成员）或持续时间（即相对较长）相对较大；很大。

LIKELY.zh: 某事或某人被认为是可能的。

DEVELOP.en: To change with a specific direction, progress.
DEVELOP.zh: 改变有一个特定的方向，进步。

JAVA.en: A blend of coffee imported from the island of __.
JAVA.zh: 从爪哇岛进口的混合咖啡。

GUEST.en: A recipient of hospitality, specifically someone staying by invitation at the house of another.
GUEST.zh: 受款待者，特指受邀请住在他人家中的人。

SEEMS.en: To appear; to look outwardly; to be perceived as.

TRUST.en: Confidence in or reliance on some person or quality.
TRUST.zh: 对某人或品质的信心或依赖。

VAN.en: A covered vehicle used for carrying goods or people, usually roughly cuboid in shape, longer and higher than a car but smaller than a truck/lorry.
VAN.zh: 用于运载货物或人员的有盖车辆，通常形状大致为长方体，比汽车更长、更高，但比卡车/卡车小。

REPUBLIC.en: A state where sovereignty rests with the people or their representatives, rather than with a monarch or emperor; a country with no monarchy.
REPUBLIC.zh: 主权属于人民或其代表而不是君主或皇帝的国家；一个没有君主制的国家。

FEES.en: (feudal law) A right to the use of a superior's land, as a stipend for services to be performed; also, the land so held; a fief.
FEES.zh: （封建法）使用上级土地的权利，作为提供服务的津贴；此外，所持有的土地；封地。

VACATION.en: Freedom from some business or activity.
VACATION.zh: 摆脱某些业务或活动的自由。

SKIN.en: The outer protective layer of the body of any animal, including of a human.
SKIN.zh: 任何动物（包括人类）身体的外保护层。

GRAPHICS.en: The making of architectural or design drawings.
GRAPHICS.zh: 建筑或设计图纸的制作。

EXPECTED.en: To predict or believe that something will happen
EXPECTED.zh: 预测或相信某事将会发生

RING.en: (physical) A solid object in the shape of a circle.

DATING.en: To note the time or place of writing or executing; to express in an instrument the time of its execution.
DATING.zh: 注明书写或执行的时间或地点；在文书中表达其执行的时间。

POP.en: A loud, sharp sound as of a cork coming out of a bottle.
POP.zh: 一种响亮、尖锐的声音，就像软木塞从瓶子里拔出来一样。

MAILING.en: (ditransitive) To send (a letter, parcel, etc.) through the mail.
MAILING.zh: （双及物）通过邮件发送（信件、包裹等）。

LONGER.en: Having much distance from one terminating point on an object or an area to another terminating point (usually applies to horizontal dimensions; see Usage Notes below).
LONGER.zh: 从对象或区域上的一个终止点到另一终止点的距离很远（通常适用于水平尺寸；请参阅下面的使用说明）。

INT.en: A number that is not a fraction; an element of the infinite and numerable set {..., -3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, 3, ...}.

PANEL.en: A (usually) rectangular section of a surface, or of a covering or of a wall, fence etc.
PANEL.zh: 表面、覆盖物或墙壁、栅栏等的（通常）矩形截面。

FLOOR.en: The interior bottom or surface of a house or building; the supporting surface of a room.
FLOOR.zh: 房屋或建筑物的内部底部或表面；房间的支撑面。

BUYING.en: To obtain (something) in exchange for money or goods
BUYING.zh: 用金钱或物品换取（某物）

MATCH.en: A competitive sporting event such as a boxing meet, a baseball game, or a cricket __.
MATCH.zh: 竞技性体育赛事，例如拳击比赛、棒球比赛或板球比赛。

PROPOSED.en: To suggest a plan, course of action, etc.

OUTDOOR.en: (in some African communities) To publicly display a child after it has been named
OUTDOOR.zh: （在一些非洲社区）在命名后公开展示孩子

DEEP.en: (with "the") The __ part of a lake, sea, etc.

ALLOWS.en: To grant, give, admit, accord, afford, or yield; to let one have.
ALLOWS.zh: 授予、给予、承认、同意、负担或让步；让一个人拥有。

REST.en: (of a person or animal) Relief from work or activity by sleeping; sleep.
REST.zh: （人或动物）通过睡眠来缓解工作或活动；睡觉。

PLANT.en: An organism that is not an animal, especially an organism capable of photosynthesis. Typically a small or herbaceous organism of this kind, rather than a tree.
PLANT.zh: 非动物的生物体，尤其是能够进行光合作用的生物体。通常是这种小型或草本生物，而不是树。

REPORTED.en: To relate details of (an event or incident); to recount, describe (something).
REPORTED.zh: 关联（事件或事件）的细节；叙述、描述（某事）。

HIT.en: A blow; a punch; a striking against; the collision of one body against another; the stroke that touches anything.
HIT.zh: 一击；一拳；打击；一个物体与另一个物体的碰撞；触及任何东西的笔触。

POOL.en: A small and rather deep collection of (usually) fresh water, as one supplied by a spring, or occurring in the course of a stream; a reservoir for water.
POOL.zh: 一小部分相当深的（通常是）淡水的集合，如由泉水供应或在溪流中产生的水；水库。

PARTNER.en: Someone who is associated with another in a common activity or interest.
PARTNER.zh: 与他人有共同活动或兴趣的人。

AUTHORS.en: The originator or creator of a work, especially of a literary composition.
AUTHORS.zh: 作品（尤其是文学作品）的创作者或创作者。

BOARDS.en: A relatively long, wide and thin piece of any material, usually wood or similar, often for use in construction or furniture-making.
BOARDS.zh: 任何材料的相对长、宽、薄的一块，通常是木材或类似材料，通常用于建筑或家具制造。

FACULTY.en: The academic staff at schools, colleges, universities or not-for-profit research institutes, as opposed to the students or support staff.
FACULTY.zh: 学校、学院、大学或非营利研究机构的学术人员，而不是学生或支持人员。

PARTIES.en: A person or group of people constituting a particular side in a contract or legal action.
PARTIES.zh: 构成合同或法律诉讼中特定一方的个人或团体。

FISH.en: A cold-blooded vertebrate animal that lives in water, moving with the help of fins and breathing with gills.
FISH.zh: 一种生活在水中的冷血脊椎动物，借助鳍移动并用鳃呼吸。

MISSION.en: A set of tasks that fulfills a purpose or duty; an assignment set by an employer, or by oneself.
MISSION.zh: 完成某一目的或职责的一组任务；由雇主或自己指定的任务。

EYE.en: An organ through which animals see (perceive surroundings via light).
EYE.zh: 动物观察的器官（通过光感知周围环境）。

SENSE.en: Any of the manners by which living beings perceive the physical world: for humans sight, smell, hearing, touch, taste.
SENSE.zh: 生物感知物质世界的任何方式：人类的视觉、嗅觉、听觉、触觉、味觉。

MODIFIED.zh: 用于改装赛车的任何车辆。

PACK.en: A bundle made up and prepared to be carried; especially, a bundle to be carried on the back, but also a load for an animal, a bale.
PACK.zh: 准备好携带的包裹；特别是，可以背在背上的包裹，也可以是动物的负载，即捆包。

RELEASED.en: To let go (of); to cease to hold or contain.
RELEASED.zh: 放开（的）；停止持有或遏制。

GOODS.en: The forces or behaviours that are the enemy of evil. Usually consists of helping others and general benevolence.
GOODS.zh: 与邪恶为敌的力量或行为。通常包括帮助他人和普遍的仁慈。

BORN.en: To carry or convey, literally or figuratively.
BORN.zh: 从字面上或比喻上携带或传达。

UNLESS.en: Except on a specified condition; if not.
UNLESS.zh: 除非有指定条件；如果不。

RACE.en: A contest between people, animals, vehicles, etc. where the goal is to be the first to reach some objective. Example: Several horses run in a horse __, and the first one to reach the finishing post wins
RACE.zh: 人、动物、车辆等之间的竞赛，目标是成为第一个达到某个目标的人。例：多匹马参加赛马比赛，最先到达终点的获胜

APPROVED.en: To sanction officially; to ratify; to confirm; to set as satisfactory.
APPROVED.zh: 正式批准；批准；确认；设置为满意。

TARGET.en: A butt or mark to shoot at, as for practice, or to test the accuracy of a firearm, or the force of a projectile.
TARGET.zh: 用来射击的枪托或标记，用于练习，或测试枪支的准确性或射弹的力量。

EXCEPT.en: To exclude; to specify as being an __ion.

MOVING.en: To change place or posture; to go, in any manner, from one place or position to another.
MOVING.zh: 改变地点或姿势；以任何方式从一个地方或位置到另一个地方或位置。

PLACES.en: (physical) An area; somewhere within an area.
PLACES.zh: （物理）一个区域；某个区域内的某处。

PRETTY.en: A __ person; a term of address to a __ person.
PRETTY.zh: 一个漂亮的人；对漂亮人的称呼。

SOUTHERN.en: Someone from one of the states which seceded in 1861 and briefly formed the Confederate States of America, or, more broadly, from some neighboring states as well (but excluding geographically-southerly states like Arizona); compare the South.
SOUTHERN.zh: 来自 1861 年脱离联邦并短暂成立美利坚联盟国之一的某人，或者更广泛地说，也来自一些邻近的州（但不包括亚利桑那州等地处南部的州）；对比南方。

BATTERY.en: A device used to power electric devices, consisting of a set of electrically connected electrochemical or, archaically, electrostatic cells. A single such cell when used by itself.
BATTERY.zh: 用于为电子设备供电的设备，由一组电连接的电化学电池或传统的静电电池组成。单独使用时单个这样的电池。

YOUTH.en: The quality or state of being young.

DEBT.en: An action, state of mind, or object one has an obligation to perform for another, adopt toward another, or give to another.
DEBT.zh: 一个人有义务为另一个人执行、采纳另一个人或给予另一个人的行为、精神状态或物体。

KEYWORDS.en: Any word used as the key to a code.
KEYWORDS.zh: 用作代码密钥的任何单词。

CORE.en: The central part of fruit, containing the kernels or seeds.
CORE.zh: 水果的中心部分，含有果仁或种子。

BREAK.en: An instance of __ing something into two or more pieces.
BREAK.zh: 将某物分成两块或更多块的实例。

PURPOSES.en: An objective to be reached; a target; an aim; a goal.
PURPOSES.zh: 要达到的目标；一个目标；一个目标；一个目标。

DANCE.en: A sequence of rhythmic steps or movements usually performed to music, for pleasure or as a form of social interaction.
DANCE.zh: 通常随着音乐表演的一系列有节奏的步骤或动作，以供娱乐或作为社交互动的一种形式。

WOOD.en: The substance making up the central part of the trunk and branches of a tree. Used as a material for construction, to manufacture various items, etc. or as fuel.
WOOD.zh: 构成树干和树枝中心部分的物质。用作建筑材料、制造各种物品等或用作燃料。

DEFINED.en: To determine with precision; to mark out with distinctness; to ascertain or exhibit clearly.
DEFINED.zh: To determine with precision;清楚地标出；明确地确定或展示。

PAPERS.en: A sheet material used for writing on or printing on (or as a non-waterproof container), usually made by draining cellulose fibres from a suspension in water.
PAPERS.zh: 用于书写或印刷的片材（或作为不防水容器），通常通过从水中的悬浮液中沥干纤维素纤维而制成。

PLAYING.en: To act in a manner such that one has fun; to engage in activities expressly for the purpose of recreation or entertainment.
PLAYING.zh: 以一种让人感到有趣的方式行事；从事明确以休闲或娱乐为目的的活动。

AWARDS.en: A judgment, sentence, or final decision. Specifically: The decision of arbitrators in a case submitted.
AWARDS.zh: 判决、判决或最终决定。具体来说：仲裁员对所提交案件的决定。

FEE.en: (feudal law) A right to the use of a superior's land, as a stipend for services to be performed; also, the land so held; a fief.
FEE.zh: （封建法）使用上级土地的权利，作为提供服务的津贴；此外，所持有的土地；封地。

STUDIO.en: An artist’s or photographer’s workshop or the room in which an artist works.
STUDIO.zh: 艺术家或摄影师的工作室或艺术家工作的房间。

VIRTUAL.en: A __ member function of a class.

ANSWERS.en: A response or reply; something said or done in reaction to a statement or question.
ANSWERS.zh: 回应或答复；针对陈述或问题而说或做的事情。

RENT.en: A payment made by a tenant at intervals in order to occupy a property.
RENT.zh: 租户为了占用房产而定期支付的费用。

REMOTE.en: An element of broadcast programming originating away from the station's or show's control room.
REMOTE.zh: 源自电台或节目控制室的广播节目的一个元素。

DARK.en: Having an absolute or (more often) relative lack of light.
DARK.zh: 绝对或（更常见的是）相对缺乏光线。

EXTERNAL.en: (chiefly in the plural) The exterior; outward features or appearances.
EXTERNAL.zh: （主要是复数）外​​部；外在特征或外观。

APPLE.en: A common, round fruit produced by the tree Malus domestica, cultivated in temperate climates.
APPLE.zh: 一种常见的圆形水果，由生长在温带气候的苹果树产生。

MIN.en: A unit of time equal to sixty seconds (one-sixtieth of an hour).
MIN.zh: 等于六十秒（一小时的六十分之一）的时间单位。

OFFERED.en: To propose or express one's willingness (to do something).
OFFERED.zh: 提议或表达某人的意愿（做某事）。

THEORY.en: A description of an event or system that is considered to be accurate.
THEORY.zh: 对事件或系统的描述被认为是准确的。

ENJOY.en: To receive pleasure or satisfaction from something
ENJOY.zh: 从某事中获得快乐或满足

VISUAL.en: Any element of something that depends on sight.
VISUAL.zh: 依赖于视觉的事物的任何元素。

HOST.en: One which receives or entertains a guest, socially, commercially, or officially.
HOST.zh: 用于社交、商业或正式接待或招待客人的一种活动。

TEACHERS.en: A person who teaches, especially one employed in a school.
TEACHERS.zh: 教书的人，尤指受雇于学校的人。

MARTIN.en: Any of various passerine birds of the family Hirundinidae, which also includes swallows, that catch insects whilst flying.
MARTIN.zh: 燕雀科的任何一种雀形目鸟类，其中还包括燕子，在飞行时捕捉昆虫。

BLOCK.en: A substantial, often approximately cuboid, piece of any substance.
BLOCK.zh: 任何物质的实体，通常近似长方体。

SUBJECTS.en: (grammar) In a clause: the word or word group (usually a noun phrase) that is dealt with. In active clauses with verbs denoting an action, the subject and the actor are usually the same.
SUBJECTS.zh: （语法）在子句中：所处理的单词或词组（通常是名词短语）。在动词表示动作的主动从句中，主语和行动者通常是相同的。

AGENTS.en: One who exerts power, or has the power to act
AGENTS.zh: 行使权力或有权力采取行动的人

FAIR.en: Something which is __ (in various senses of the adjective).
FAIR.zh: 公平的东西（在形容词的各种意义上）。

CIVIL.en: Having to do with people and government office as opposed to the military or religion.
CIVIL.zh: 与人民和政府办公室有关，而不是与军队或宗教有关。

STEEL.en: An artificial metal produced from iron, harder and more elastic than elemental iron; used figuratively as a symbol of hardness.
STEEL.zh: 由铁制成的人造金属，比元素铁更硬、更有弹性；比喻性地用作硬度的象征。

SONGS.en: A musical composition with lyrics for voice or voices, performed by singing.
SONGS.zh: 一种带有歌词的音乐作品，通过歌唱来表演。

FIXED.en: To pierce; now generally replaced by transfix.

WRONG.en: Something that is immoral or not good.

HANDS.en: The part of the forelimb below the forearm or wrist in a human, and the corresponding part in many other animals.
HANDS.zh: 人类前臂或手腕下方的前肢部分，以及许多其他动物的相应部分。

FINALLY.en: At the end or conclusion; ultimately.

UPDATES.en: An advisement providing more up-to-date information than currently known.
UPDATES.zh: 提供比目前已知的更多最新信息的建议。

DESKTOP.en: The top surface of a desk.

CLASSES.en: A group, collection, category or set sharing characteristics or attributes.
CLASSES.zh: 共享特征或属性的群体、集合、类别或集合。

CAPACITY.en: The ability to hold, receive or absorb
CAPACITY.zh: 持有、接收或吸收的能力

REQUIRES.en: To ask (someone) for something; to request.

JERSEY.en: A garment knitted from wool, worn over the upper body.
JERSEY.zh: 穿在上身的羊毛针织服装。

FAT.en: A specialized animal tissue with a high oil content, used for long-term storage of energy.
FAT.zh: 一种含油量高的特殊动物组织，用于长期储存能量。

FULLY.en: In a full manner; without lack or defect.

ELECTRIC.zh: （通常带有定冠词）电力；电力供应。

SAW.en: A tool with a toothed blade used for cutting hard substances, in particular wood or metal
SAW.zh: 带有齿形刀片的工具，用于切割硬质物质，特别是木材或金属

QUOTES.en: A quotation; a statement attributed to a person.
QUOTES.zh: 报价单；归因于某人的陈述。

OFFICER.en: One who has a position of authority in a hierarchical organization, especially in military, police or government organizations.
OFFICER.zh: 在等级组织中，特别是在军队、警察或政府组织中拥有权威职位的人。

DRIVER.en: One who drives something, in any sense of the verb to drive.
DRIVER.zh: 一个驾驶某物的人，无论是在动词驾驶的任何意义上。

DEAD.en: (with "the", a demonstrative, or a possessive) Those who have died.
DEAD.zh: （与“the”、指示词或所有格）那些已经去世的人。

RESPECT.en: An attitude of consideration or high regard
RESPECT.zh: 考虑或高度尊重的态度

TRIP.en: A journey; an excursion or jaunt
TRIP.zh: 一次旅行；短途旅行或短途旅行

PST.en: Implies that the speaker is sending secret or whispered information to another person.
PST.zh: 暗示说话者正在向另一个人发送秘密或耳语信息。

POOR.en: (with "the") Those who have little or no possessions or money, taken as a group.
POOR.zh: （与“the”）那些拥有很少或没有财产或金钱的人，作为一个群体。

EYES.en: An organ through which animals see (perceive surroundings via light).
EYES.zh: 动物观察的器官（通过光感知周围环境）。

WORKERS.en: A person who performs labor for a living, especially manual labor.
WORKERS.zh: 以劳动为生的人，尤其是体力劳动。

FARM.en: A place where agricultural and similar activities take place, especially the growing of crops or the raising of livestock.
FARM.zh: 进行农业和类似活动的地方，尤其是种植农作物或饲养牲畜的地方。

PEACE.en: A state of tranquility, quiet, and harmony; absence of violence. For instance, a state free from civil disturbance.
PEACE.zh: 一种安宁、安静、和谐的状态；没有暴力。例如，一个没有内乱的国家。

CAMPUS.en: The grounds or property of a school, college, university, business, church, or hospital, often understood to include buildings and other structures.
CAMPUS.zh: 学校、学院、大学、企业、教堂或医院的场地或财产，通常被理解为包括建筑物和其他结构。

TOM.en: A flat gong (without knob) that is struck with a felt-covered hammer.
TOM.zh: 用毡锤敲击的扁锣（无旋钮）。

SHOWING.en: To display, to have somebody see (something).

CREATIVE.en: A person directly involved in a __ marketing process.
CREATIVE.zh: 直接参与创意营销过程的人。

COAST.en: The edge of the land where it meets an ocean, sea, gulf, bay, or large lake.
COAST.zh: 与海洋、大海、海湾、海湾或大湖交汇的陆地边缘。

DEVICES.en: Any piece of equipment made for a particular purpose, especially a mechanical or electrical one.
DEVICES.zh: 为特定目的而制造的任何设备，尤其是机械或电气设备。

LORD.en: The master of the servants of a household; the master of a feudal manor
LORD.zh: 家庭仆人的主人；封建庄园主

GRANT.en: The act of __ing; a bestowing or conferring; concession; allowance; permission.
GRANT.zh: 授予行为；授予或授予；让步;津贴;允许。

AGREE.en: To harmonize in opinion, statement, or action; to be in unison or concord; to be or become united or consistent; to concur.
AGREE.zh: 协调意见、声明或行动；一致或一致；变得团结或一致；同意。

HEAR.en: (stative) To perceive sounds through the ear.

WATCHES.zh: 便携式或可穿戴计时器。

CAREERS.en: One's calling in life; a person's occupation; one's profession.
CAREERS.zh: 一个人在生命中的召唤；一个人的职业；一个人的职业。

FAMILIES.en: A group of people who are closely related to one another (by blood, marriage or adoption); kin; for example, a set of parents and their children; an immediate family.
FAMILIES.zh: 彼此有密切关系（血缘、婚姻或收养）的一群人；亲属;例如，一组父母和他们的孩子；直系亲属。

MUSEUM.en: A building or institution dedicated to the acquisition, conservation, study, exhibition, and educational interpretation of objects having scientific, historical, cultural or artistic value.
MUSEUM.zh: 致力于收购、保护、研究、展览和教育阐释具有科学、历史、文化或艺术价值的物品的建筑物或机构。

FAN.en: A hand-held device consisting of concertinaed material, or slats of material, gathered together at one end, that may be opened out into the shape of a sector of a circle and waved back and forth in order to move air towards oneself and cool oneself.
FAN.zh: 一种手持式装置，由六角形材料或材料板条组成，一端聚集在一起，可以打开成扇形，并前后挥动，以便将空气吹向自己并为自己降温。

BLOGS.en: A website that allows users to reflect, share opinions, and discuss various topics in the form of an online journal, sometimes letting readers comment on their posts. Most __ are written in a slightly informal tone (personal journals, news, businesses, etc.)
BLOGS.zh: 一个允许用户以在线日记的形式反思、分享观点和讨论各种主题的网站，有时还让读者对他们的帖子发表评论。大多数博客都是以稍微非正式的语气撰写的（个人日记、新闻、商业等）

WIFE.en: A married woman, especially in relation to her spouse.
WIFE.zh: 已婚妇女，尤其是与她的配偶有关的妇女。

ACCEPTED.en: To receive, especially with a consent, with favour, or with approval.
ACCEPTED.zh: 接受，尤指在同意、青睐或批准的情况下接受。

TEN.en: A set or group with __ elements.
TEN.zh: 包含十个元素的集合或组。

HITS.en: A blow; a punch; a striking against; the collision of one body against another; the stroke that touches anything.
HITS.zh: 一击；一拳；打击；一个物体与另一个物体的碰撞；触及任何东西的笔触。

ZONE.en: Each of the five regions of the earth's surface into which it was divided by climatic differences, namely the torrid __ (between the tropics), two temperate __s (between the tropics and the polar circles), and two frigid __s (within the polar circles).
ZONE.zh: 地球表面按气候差异划分为五个区域，即热带地区（热带地区之间）、两个温带地区（热带地区和极圈之间）和两个寒冷地区（极圈以内）。

CAT.en: An animal of the family Felidae:

DIE.en: To stop living; to become dead; to undergo death.
DIE.zh: 停止生活；变得死了；去经历死亡。

JACK.en: A coarse mediaeval coat of defence, especially one made of leather.
JACK.zh: 一种粗糙的中世纪防御外套，尤指皮革制成的外套。

FLOW.en: A movement in people or things with a particular way in large numbers or amounts
FLOW.zh: 人或物以特定方式大量或大量地运动

AGENCIES.en: The capacity, condition, or state of acting or of exerting power.
AGENCIES.zh: 行动或施加权力的能力、条件或状态。

PARENT.en: One of the two persons from whom one is immediately biologically descended; a mother or father.
PARENT.zh: 两个人中的一个，其中一个在生物学上是直接后裔；母亲或父亲。

SPANISH.en: To subject to __ing, a printing process in which an ink is deposited on the bottoms and sides of depressions formed in a plastic material
SPANISH.zh: 西班牙印刷是一种印刷工艺，其中油墨沉积在塑料材料形成的凹陷的底部和侧面上

SCALE.en: A ladder; a series of steps; a means of ascending.
SCALE.zh: 一个梯子；一系列步骤；一种提升的手段。

ECONOMY.en: Effective management of a community or system, or especially its resources.
ECONOMY.zh: 有效管理社区或系统，特别是其资源。

HIGHEST.en: Very elevated; extending or being far above a base; tall; lofty.
HIGHEST.zh: 非常高；延伸或远高于底座；高的;崇高的。

MONTHLY.en: A publication that is published once a month.
MONTHLY.zh: 每月出版一次的出版物。

FRAME.en: The structural elements of a building or other constructed object.
FRAME.zh: 建筑物或其他建筑物体的结构元件。

MUSICAL.en: A stage performance, show or film that involves singing, dancing and __ numbers performed by the cast as well as acting.
MUSICAL.zh: 涉及演员表演的歌唱、舞蹈和音乐表演的舞台表演、表演或电影。

PATH.en: A trail for the use of, or worn by, pedestrians.
PATH.zh: 供行人使用或行走的小径。

CHIEF.en: A leader or head of a group of people, organisation, etc.
CHIEF.zh: 一群人、组织等的领导者或负责人

GIVES.en: (ditransitive) To move, shift, provide something abstract or concrete to someone or something or somewhere.
GIVES.zh: （双及物）移动、转移、向某人、某物或某处提供抽象或具体的东西。

PACKAGES.en: Something which is packed, a parcel, a box, an envelope.
PACKAGES.zh: 包装好的东西，包裹，盒子，信封。

LAWS.en: The body of binding rules and regulations, customs and standards established in a community by its legislative and judicial authorities.
LAWS.zh: 由立法和司法当局在社区中制定的具有约束力的规则和条例、习俗和标准的体系。

PET.en: An animal kept as a companion.

HEARD.en: (stative) To perceive sounds through the ear.

ROYAL.en: A __ person; a member of a __ family.

SWITCH.en: A bundle of thin sticks, typically made of wood, sometimes bond in such a way that binding can be moved so that it varies the tightness of the binding.
SWITCH.zh: 一捆通常由木头制成的细木棍，有时以这样的方式粘合，即可以移动装订，从而改变装订的松紧度。

LARGEST.en: Of considerable or relatively great size or extent.
LARGEST.zh: 具有相当大或相对较大的规模或范围。

GUY.en: An effigy of a man burned on a bonfire on the anniversary of the Gunpowder Plot (5th November).
GUY.zh: 在火药阴谋周年纪念日（11 月 5 日），一尊男子肖像被篝火焚烧。

TITLES.en: A prefix (honorific) or suffix (post-nominal) added to a person's name to signify either veneration, official position or a professional or academic qualification. See also
TITLES.zh: 添加到人名上的前缀（尊称）或后缀（后称），表示尊敬、官方职位或专业或学术资格。参见

RELEVANT.en: Directly related, connected, or pertinent to a topic.
RELEVANT.zh: 与主题直接相关、连接或相关。

CUP.en: A concave vessel for drinking from, usually made of opaque material (as opposed to a glass) and with a handle.
CUP.zh: 用于饮用的凹形容器，通常由不透明材料（而不是玻璃）制成并带有手柄。

WEEKLY.en: A publication that is published once a week.
WEEKLY.zh: 每周出版一次的出版物。

SUITE.en: A retinue or company of attendants, as of a distinguished personage
SUITE.zh: 显赫人物的随从或随行人员

VEGAS.en: (Latin America) An open tract of ground; a plain, especially one which is moist and fertile, such as those used for growing tobacco.
VEGAS.zh: （拉丁美洲）开阔的土地；平原，特指潮湿肥沃的平原，例如用于种植烟草的平原。

SQUARE.en: A polygon with four sides of equal length and four right angles; an equilateral rectangle; a regular quadrilateral.
SQUARE.zh: 四条边等长、四个直角的多边形；等边长方形；正四边形。

ADVANCE.en: A forward move; improvement or progression.

SKIP.zh: 跳跃、跳跃或跳绳的动作。

DIET.en: The food and beverage a person or animal consumes.
DIET.zh: 人或动物消耗的食物和饮料。

ARMY.en: A large, highly organized military force, concerned mainly with ground (rather than air or naval) operations.
ARMY.zh: 一支规模庞大、组织严密的军事力量，主要从事地面（而不是空中或海上）行动。

AUCTION.en: A public event where goods or property are sold to the highest bidder.
AUCTION.zh: 将货物或财产出售给出价最高者的公共活动。

GEAR.en: Equipment or paraphernalia, especially that used for an athletic endeavor.
GEAR.zh: 设备或用具，尤其是用于运动的设备或用具。

LEE.en: A protected cove or harbor, out of the wind.
LEE.zh: 避风、受保护的海湾或港口。

ALLOWED.en: To grant, give, admit, accord, afford, or yield; to let one have.
ALLOWED.zh: 授予、给予、承认、同意、负担或让步；让一个人拥有。

NATION.en: A historically constituted, stable community of people, formed on the basis of a common language, territory, economic life, ethnicity and/or psychological make-up manifested in a common culture.
NATION.zh: 在历史上形成的、稳定的人民共同体，在共同语言、领土、经济生活、种族和/或共同文化所体现的心理素质的基础上形成。

SELLING.en: (ditransitive) To transfer goods or provide services in exchange for money.
SELLING.zh: （双及物）转移货物或提供服务以换取金钱。

LOTS.en: A large quantity or number; a great deal.

PIECE.en: A part of a larger whole, usually in such a form that it is able to be separated from other parts.
PIECE.zh: 较大整体的一部分，通常以能够与其他部分分离的形式存在。

SHEET.en: A thin bed cloth used as a covering for a mattress or as a layer over the sleeper.
SHEET.zh: 一种薄床布，用作床垫的覆盖物或覆盖睡眠者的一层。

FIRM.en: A business partnership; the name under which it trades.
FIRM.zh: 商业伙伴关系； the name under which it trades.

SEVEN.en: The digit/figure 7 or an occurrence thereof.
SEVEN.zh: 数字/数字 7 或其出现。

OLDER.en: Of an object, concept, relationship, etc., having existed for a relatively long period of time.
OLDER.zh: 存在了相当长一段时间的对象、概念、关系等。

ELEMENTS.en: One of the simplest or essential parts or principles of which anything consists, or upon which the constitution or fundamental powers of anything are based.
ELEMENTS.zh: 任何事物组成的最简单或基本的部分或原则之一，或者任何事物的宪法或基本权力所基于的。

JUMP.en: The act of __ing; a leap; a spring; a bound.
JUMP.zh: 跳跃的动作；一次飞跃；一个弹簧；一个界限。

CELLS.en: A single-room dwelling for a hermit.

MODULE.en: A self-contained component of a system, often interchangeable, which has a well-defined interface to the other components.
MODULE.zh: 系统的独立组件，通常可以互换，具有与其他组件明确定义的接口。

RESORT.en: A place where people go for recreation, especially one with facilities such as lodgings, entertainment, and a relaxing environment.
RESORT.zh: 人们休闲娱乐的地方，尤指有住宿、娱乐、环境轻松等设施的地方。

PRICING.en: To determine the monetary value of (an item); to put a price on.
PRICING.zh: 确定（物品）的货币价值；定价。

LOOKS.zh: 一个人的外表或吸引力。

VISITORS.en: Someone who visits someone else; someone staying as a guest.
VISITORS.zh: 拜访别人的人；有人作为客人入住。

MONITOR.en: Someone who watches over something; a person in charge of something or someone.
MONITOR.zh: 监视某事的人；负责某事或某人的人。

WHOSE.en: (interrogative) That or those of whom or belonging to whom.
WHOSE.zh: （疑问）那个或那些人的或属于谁的。

COVERAGE.en: An amount by which something or someone is covered.
COVERAGE.zh: 承保某物或某人的金额。

COUPLE.en: Two partners in a romantic or sexual relationship.
COUPLE.zh: 处于浪漫或性关系中的两个伙伴。

GIVING.en: (ditransitive) To move, shift, provide something abstract or concrete to someone or something or somewhere.
GIVING.zh: （双及物）移动、转移、向某人、某物或某处提供抽象或具体的东西。

VISION.en: The sense or ability of sight.

BALL.en: A solid or hollow sphere, or roughly spherical mass.
BALL.zh: 实心或空心球体，或大致球形的物体。

CLIENTS.en: A customer, a buyer or receiver of goods or services.
CLIENTS.zh: 顾客、商品或服务的购买者或接收者。

ACTIONS.en: Something done so as to accomplish a purpose.
ACTIONS.zh: 为了达到某种目的而做的事情。

DISCUSS.en: To converse or debate concerning a particular topic.
DISCUSS.zh: 就特定主题进行交谈或辩论。

NAKED.zh: 赤身露体，没有衣服遮盖。

GOAL.en: A result that one is attempting to achieve.
GOAL.zh: 一个人试图达到的结果。

SOLD.en: (ditransitive) To transfer goods or provide services in exchange for money.
SOLD.zh: （双及物）转移货物或提供服务以换取金钱。

WIND.en: Real or perceived movement of atmospheric air usually caused by convection or differences in air pressure.
WIND.zh: 通常由对流或气压差异引起的实际或感知的大气运动。

SCIENCES.en: A particular discipline or branch of learning, especially one dealing with measurable or systematic principles rather than intuition or natural ability.
SCIENCES.zh: 一种特定的学科或学习分支，尤其是涉及可测量或系统原则而不是直觉或自然能力的学科或分支。

MARKETS.en: A gathering of people for the purchase and sale of merchandise at a set time, often periodic.
MARKETS.zh: 人们在规定的时间（通常是周期性的）聚集在一起购买和销售商品。

LOWEST.en: Situated close to, or even below, the ground or another normal reference plane; not high or lofty.
LOWEST.zh: 位于地面或其他法线参考平面附近甚至下方；不高也不崇高。

HIGHLY.en: In a high or esteemed manner.
HIGHLY.zh: 以一种崇高或受人尊敬的方式。

APPEAR.en: To come or be in sight; to be in view; to become visible.
APPEAR.zh: 来到或出现在眼前；在视野中；变得可见。

LEATHER.en: A tough material produced from the skin of animals, by tanning or similar process, used e.g. for clothing.
LEATHER.zh: 由动物皮肤通过鞣制或类似工艺制成的坚韧材料，例如用于皮革制品。用于服装。

PALM.en: Any of various evergreen trees from the family __ae or Arecaceae, which are mainly found in the tropics.
PALM.zh: 棕榈科或槟榔科的各种常绿乔木，主要分布在热带地区。

PATIENT.en: A person or animal who receives treatment from a doctor or other medically educated person.
PATIENT.zh: 接受医生或其他受过医学教育的人员治疗的人或动物。

STONE.en: A hard earthen substance that can form large rocks.
STONE.zh: 一种坚硬的土质物质，可以形成大岩石。

BOB.en: A __bing motion; a quick up and down movement.
BOB.zh: 上下摆动的动作；快速的上下运动。

COMMERCE.en: The exchange or buying and selling of commodities; especially the exchange of merchandise, on a large scale, between different places or communities; extended trade or traffic.
COMMERCE.zh: 商品交换或买卖；尤其是不同地方或社区之间大规模的商品交换；扩大贸易或交通。

PERSONS.en: An individual; usually a human being.

ACCOUNTS.en: A registry of pecuniary transactions; a written or printed statement of business dealings or debts and credits, and also of other things subjected to a reckoning or review.
ACCOUNTS.zh: 金钱交易登记处；商业交易或债务和信贷以及其他需要计算或审查的事项的书面或印刷的报表。

MET.en: To make contact (with) while in proximity.

PAIN.en: An ache or bodily suffering, or an instance of this; an unpleasant sensation, resulting from a derangement of functions, disease, or injury by violence; hurt.
PAIN.zh: 疼痛或身体痛苦，或此类情况；由于功能紊乱、疾病或暴力伤害而导致的不愉快感觉；伤害。

FACTORS.en: A doer, maker; a person who does things for another person or organization.
FACTORS.zh: 实干家、创造者；为另一个人或组织做事的人。

COFFEE.en: A beverage made by infusing the beans of the __ plant in hot water.
COFFEE.zh: 将咖啡豆浸泡在热水中制成的饮料。

SETTINGS.en: The time, place and circumstance in which something (such as a story or picture) is set; context; scenario.
SETTINGS.zh: 某事物（例如故事或图片）发生的时间、地点和环境；语境;设想。

BUYER.en: A person who makes one or more purchases.
BUYER.zh: 进行一次或多次购买的人。

ORAL.en: A spoken test or examination, particularly in a language class.
ORAL.zh: 口语测试或考试，特别是在语言课上。

FORD.en: A location where a stream is shallow and the bottom has good footing, making it possible to cross from one side to the other with no bridge, by walking, riding, or driving through the water; a crossing.
FORD.zh: 溪流较浅且底部基础良好的位置，无需桥梁，可以通过步行、骑马或驾车从一侧穿过水流到另一侧；一个十字路口。

POSTER.en: A picture of a celebrity, an event etc., intended to be attached to a wall.
POSTER.zh: 名人、活动等的照片，适合贴在墙上。

EDGE.en: The boundary line of a surface.

ROOT.en: The part of a plant, generally underground, that anchors and supports the plant body, absorbs and stores water and nutrients, and in some plants is able to perform vegetative reproduction.
ROOT.zh: 植物的一部分，通常位于地下，固定和支撑植物体，吸收和储存水和养分，并且在某些植物中能够进行营养繁殖。

HOLIDAYS.en: A day on which a festival, religious event, or national celebration is traditionally observed.
HOLIDAYS.zh: 传统上庆祝节日、宗教活动或全国庆祝活动的日子。

REPLIES.en: A written or spoken response; part of a conversation.
REPLIES.zh: 书面或口头答复；谈话的一部分。

LABEL.en: A small ticket or sign giving information about something to which it is attached or intended to be attached.
LABEL.zh: 一种小票或标志，提供有关其所附着或打算附着的物品的信息。

CANON.en: A generally accepted principle; a rule.
CANON.zh: 普遍接受的原则；一条规则。

LEAGUE.en: A group or association of cooperating members.
LEAGUE.zh: 合作成员组成的团体或协会。

WASTE.en: Excess of material, useless by-products or damaged, unsaleable products; garbage; rubbish.
WASTE.zh: 材料过剩、无用副产品或损坏、无法销售的产品；垃圾;垃圾。

BUS.en: A motor vehicle for transporting large numbers of people along roads.
BUS.zh: 沿道路运送大量人员的机动车辆。

PROVIDER.en: One who, or that which, provides a service, commodity, or the means for subsistence.
PROVIDER.zh: 提供服务、商品或生存资料的人或事物。

COLD.en: (of a thing) Having a low temperature.

SECTIONS.en: A cutting; a part cut out from the rest of something.
SECTIONS.zh: 一次切割；从某物的其余部分中切出的一部分。

CHAIR.en: An item of furniture used to sit on or in, comprising a seat, legs, back, and sometimes arm rests, for use by one person. Compare stool, couch, sofa, settee, loveseat and bench.
CHAIR.zh: 一种用于坐在上面或里面的家具，包括座椅、腿、靠背，有时还有扶手，供一个人使用。比较凳子、沙发、沙发、长沙发、双人沙发和长凳。

EFFORT.en: The work involved in performing an activity; exertion.
EFFORT.zh: 执行某项活动所涉及的工作；用力。

FIELDS.en: A land area free of woodland, cities, and towns; open country.
FIELDS.zh: 没有林地、城市和城镇的土地区域；野外。

BAG.en: A flexible container made of cloth, paper, plastic, etc.
BAG.zh: 由布、纸、塑料等制成的柔性容器。

MOTOR.en: A machine or device that converts other energy forms into mechanical energy, or imparts motion.
MOTOR.zh: 将其他能量形式转换为机械能或传递运动的机器或装置。

SHIRT.en: An article of clothing that is worn on the upper part of the body, and often has sleeves, either long or short, that cover the arms.
SHIRT.zh: 穿在上半身的衣服，通常有长袖或短袖，覆盖手臂。

FOOT.en: A biological structure found in many animals that is used for locomotion and that is frequently a separate organ at the terminal part of the leg.
FOOT.zh: 在许多动物中发现的一种生物结构，用于运动，通常是腿末端的一个独立器官。

CRIME.en: A specific act committed in violation of the law.
CRIME.zh: 违反法律规定的具体行为。

COUNT.en: The act of __ing or tallying a quantity.
COUNT.zh: 计算或统计数量的行为。

BREAST.en: Either of the two organs on the front of a female human's chest, which contain the mammary glands; also the analogous organs in males.
BREAST.zh: 女性胸部前面的两个器官之一，其中含有乳腺；还有男性的类似器官。

DOLLARS.en: Official designation for currency in some parts of the world, including Canada, the United States, Australia, New Zealand, Hong Kong, and elsewhere. Its symbol is $.
DOLLARS.zh: 世界某些地区的货币官方指定，包括加拿大、美国、澳大利亚、新西兰、香港和其他地方。它的符号是$。

WEBSITES.en: A collection of interlinked web pages on the World Wide Web that are typically accessible from the same base URL and reside on the same server.
WEBSITES.zh: 万维网上相互链接的网页的集合，通常可通过同一基本 URL 进行访问并驻留在同一服务器上。

RELIGION.en: Belief in a spiritual or metaphysical reality (often including at least one deity), accompanied by practices or rituals pertaining to the belief.
RELIGION.zh: 对精神或形而上现实的信仰（通常包括至少一个神），并伴有与该信仰相关的实践或仪式。

CLAIM.en: A demand of ownership made for something.

DRIVING.en: To provide an impetus for motion or other physical change, to move an object by means of the provision of force thereto.
DRIVING.zh: 为运动或其他物理变化提供动力，通过向物体提供力来移动物体。

SURGERY.en: A procedure involving major incisions to remove, repair, or replace a part of a body.
SURGERY.zh: 涉及大切口以切除、修复或更换身体一部分的手术。

PATCH.en: A piece of cloth, or other suitable material, sewed or otherwise fixed upon a garment to repair or strengthen it, especially upon an old garment to cover a hole.
PATCH.zh: 一块布或其他合适的材料，缝制或以其他方式固定在衣服上以修复或加固它，特别是在旧衣服上以覆盖破洞。

WILD.en: The undomesticated state of a __ animal
WILD.zh: 野生动物的未驯化状态

CHEMICAL.en: Any specific __ element or __ compound or alloy.
CHEMICAL.zh: 任何特定的化学元素或化合物或合金。

TASK.en: A piece of work done as part of one’s duties.
TASK.zh: 作为职责的一部分完成的一项工作。

REDUCE.en: To bring down the size, quantity, quality, value or intensity of something; to diminish, to lower.
REDUCE.zh: 降低某物的大小、数量、质量、价值或强度；减少，降低。

HIMSELF.en: (reflexive pronoun) Him; the male object of a verb or preposition that also appears as the subject
HIMSELF.zh: （反身代词）他；也作为主语出现的动词或介词的男性宾语

NOR.en: And not (introducing a negative statement, without necessarily following one).
NOR.zh: 而不是（引入否定陈述，不一定遵循否定陈述）。

ENABLE.en: To make somebody able (to do, or to be, something); to give sufficient ability or power to do or to be; to give strength or ability to.
ENABLE.zh: 使某人能够（做某事或成为某事）；给予足够的能力或权力去做或成为；给予力量或能力。

BUG.en: An insect of the order Hemiptera (the “true __s”).
BUG.zh: 半翅目昆虫（“真正的昆虫”）。

DIAMOND.en: A glimmering glass-like mineral that is an allotrope of carbon in which each atom is surrounded by four others in the form of a tetrahedron.
DIAMOND.zh: 一种闪闪发光的玻璃状矿物，是碳的同素异形体，其中每个原子都被四个其他原子包围，形成四面体。

SOFT.en: A __ or foolish person; an idiot.
SOFT.zh: 软弱或愚蠢的人；一个白痴。

SERVERS.en: A program that provides services to other programs or devices, either in the same computer or over a computer network.
SERVERS.zh: 为同一计算机中或通过计算机网络的其他程序或设备提供服务的程序。

MEETINGS.en: (gerund) The act of persons or things that meet.
MEETINGS.zh: （动名词）相遇的人或事物的行为。

SECONDS.en: Something that is number two in a series.

KEYWORD.en: Any word used as the key to a code.
KEYWORD.zh: 用作代码密钥的任何单词。

FUEL.en: Substance consumed to provide energy through combustion, or through chemical or nuclear reaction.
FUEL.zh: 通过燃烧、化学或核反应提供能量而消耗的物质。

USERNAME.en: A person's identification on an individual computer system.
USERNAME.zh: 个人计算机系统上的个人身份。

WALK.en: To move on the feet by alternately setting each foot (or pair or group of feet, in the case of animals with four or more feet) forward, with at least one foot on the ground at all times. Compare run.
WALK.zh: 通过交替地将每只脚（或一对或一组脚，如果是有四只或更多脚的动物）向前移动，至少一只脚始终踩在地面上。比较跑。

PRODUCED.en: To yield, make or manufacture; to generate.
PRODUCED.zh: 产出、制造或制造；来生成。

SAINT.en: A person whom a church or another religious group has officially recognised as especially holy or godly; one eminent for piety and virtue.
SAINT.zh: 被教会或其他宗教团体正式认可为特别神圣或虔诚的人；一位以虔诚和美德而闻名的人。

ROSE.en: A shrub of the genus Rosa, with red, pink, white or yellow flowers.
ROSE.zh: 蔷薇属灌木，开红色、粉红色、白色或黄色的花。

CREATING.en: To bring into existence; (sometimes in particular:)

JOINT.en: The point where two components of a structure join, but are still able to rotate.
JOINT.zh: 结构的两个组件连接但仍能够旋转的点。

FRESH.en: A rush of water, along a river or onto the land; a flood.
FRESH.zh: 沿着河流或冲向陆地的水流；一场洪水。

ATTORNEY.en: A lawyer; one who advises or represents others in legal matters as a profession.
ATTORNEY.zh: 律师；作为一种职业在法律事务上为他人提供建议或代表他人的人。

FACTOR.en: A doer, maker; a person who does things for another person or organization.
FACTOR.zh: 实干家、创造者；为另一个人或组织做事的人。

GROWING.en: To become larger, to increase in magnitude.

PICK.en: A tool used for digging; a __axe.
PICK.zh: 用于挖掘的工具；一把镐。

HEARING.en: (stative) To perceive sounds through the ear.

EASTERN.en: Of, facing, situated in, or related to the east.
EASTERN.zh: 属于、面向、位于或与东方有关的。

AUCTIONS.en: A public event where goods or property are sold to the highest bidder.
AUCTIONS.zh: 将货物或财产出售给出价最高者的公共活动。

THERAPY.en: Attempted remediation of a health problem following a diagnosis, usually synonymous with treatment.
THERAPY.zh: 诊断后尝试修复健康问题，通常与治疗同义。

DATES.en: The fruit of the date palm, Phoenix dactylifera, somewhat in the shape of an olive, containing a soft, sweet pulp and enclosing a hard kernel.
DATES.zh: 枣椰树（Phoenix dactylifera）的果实，有点像橄榄的形状，含有柔软、甜的果肉，并包裹着坚硬的果仁。

UPPER.en: A stimulant, such as amphetamine, that increases energy and decreases appetite.
UPPER.zh: 兴奋剂，例如安非他明，可以增加能量并降低食欲。

PRIME.en: The first hour of daylight; the first canonical hour.
PRIME.zh: 天亮的第一个小时；第一个规范小时。

LIMIT.en: A restriction; a bound beyond which one may not go.
LIMIT.zh: 限制；一个人不能超越的界限。

BEGAN.en: To start, to initiate or take the first step into something.
BEGAN.zh: 开始、开始或迈出某事的第一步。

LOUIS.en: Any gold or silver coin issued by the French kings from __ XIII to __ XVI and bearing their image on the obverse side, particularly the gold __ d'ors, originally a French form of the Spanish doubloon but varying in value between 10 and 24 livres.
LOUIS.zh: 从路易十三到路易十六的法国国王发行的任何金币或银币，正面印有他们的肖像，特别是金币 __ d'ors，最初是西班牙达布隆的法国形式，但价值在 10 到 24 里弗之间。

STEPS.en: An advance or movement made from one foot to the other; a pace.
STEPS.zh: 从一只脚到另一只脚的前进或移动；一个步伐。

ERRORS.en: The state, quality, or condition of being wrong.
ERRORS.zh: 错误的状态、性质或情况。

SHOPS.en: An establishment that sells goods or services to the public; originally only a physical location, but now a virtual establishment as well.
SHOPS.zh: 向公众销售商品或服务的机构；最初只是一个物理位置，但现在也是一个虚拟场所。

DEL.en: The symbol ∇ used to denote the gradient operator.
DEL.zh: 符号∇用于表示梯度算子。

EFFORTS.en: The work involved in performing an activity; exertion.
EFFORTS.zh: 执行某项活动所涉及的工作；用力。

INFORMED.en: To instruct, train (usually in matters of knowledge).
INFORMED.zh: 指导、培训（通常是知识方面的）。

THOUGHTS.en: Form created in the mind, rather than the forms perceived through the five senses; an instance of thinking.
THOUGHTS.zh: 头脑中创造的形式，而不是通过五种感官感知的形式；一个思考的例子。

CREEK.en: A small inlet or bay, often saltwater, narrower and extending farther into the land than a cove; a recess in the shore of the sea, or of a river; the inner part of a port that is used as a dock for small boats.
CREEK.zh: 小海湾或海湾，通常是咸水，比海湾更窄并且延伸到陆地更远；海岸或河边的凹处；用作小船码头的港口内部。

WORKED.en: To do a specific task by employing physical or mental powers.
WORKED.zh: 利用体力或脑力完成特定任务。

QUANTITY.en: A fundamental, generic term used when referring to the measurement (count, amount) of a scalar, vector, number of items or to some other way of denominating the value of a collection or group of items.
QUANTITY.zh: 当指标量、向量、项目数量的测量（计数、金额）或指称集合或项目组的值的其他方式时使用的基本通用术语。

SORTED.en: To separate items into different categories according to certain criteria that determine their sorts.
SORTED.zh: 根据确定其类别的特定标准将项目分为不同的类别。

MYSELF.en: (reflexive pronoun) Me, as direct or indirect object the speaker as the object of a verb or preposition, when the speaker is also the subject.
MYSELF.zh: （反身代词）我，作为直接或间接宾语，说话者作为动词或介词的宾语，当说话者也是主语时。

TOURS.en: A journey through a particular building, estate, country, etc.
TOURS.zh: 穿越特定建筑物、庄园、国家等的旅程。

LOAD.en: A burden; a weight to be carried.
LOAD.zh: 一个负担；要携带的重量。

LABOR.en: Effort expended on a particular task; toil, work.
LABOR.zh: 为某项特定任务付出的努力；辛劳，工作。

NURSING.en: To breastfeed: to feed (a baby) at the breast; to suckle.
NURSING.zh: 母乳喂养：用乳房喂养（婴儿）；哺乳。

DEFENSE.en: The action of defending or protecting from attack, danger, or injury.
DEFENSE.zh: 防御或保护免受攻击、危险或伤害的行为。

MACHINES.en: A device that directs and controls energy, often in the form of movement or electricity, to produce a certain effect.
MACHINES.zh: 引导和控制能量（通常以运动或电力的形式）以产生某种效果的装置。

HEAVY.en: A villain or bad guy; the one responsible for evil or aggressive acts.
HEAVY.zh: 恶棍或坏人；对邪恶或侵略行为负责的人。

COVERED.en: To place something over or upon, as to conceal or protect.
COVERED.zh: 将某物放置在上面或上面，以隐藏或保护。

RECOVERY.en: The act or process of regaining or repossession of something lost.
RECOVERY.zh: 重新获得或收回失去的东西的行为或过程。

JOE.en: A male; a guy; a fellow.
JOE.zh: 男性；一个男人；一个家伙。

GUYS.en: An effigy of a man burned on a bonfire on the anniversary of the Gunpowder Plot (5th November).
GUYS.zh: 在火药阴谋周年纪念日（11 月 5 日），一尊男子肖像被篝火焚烧。

EXPERT.en: A person with extensive knowledge or ability in a given subject.
EXPERT.zh: 在某一特定学科领域具有广泛知识或能力的人。

DROP.en: A small quantity of liquid, just large enough to hold its own round shape via surface tension, especially one that falls from a source of liquid.
DROP.zh: 少量液体，大小刚好足以通过表面张力保持其自身的圆形形状，尤其是从液体源中落下的液体。

SOLID.en: A substance in the fundamental state of matter that retains its size and shape without need of a container (as opposed to a liquid or gas).
SOLID.zh: 处于基本物质状态的物质，无需容器即可保持其尺寸和形状（与液体或气体相反）。

VEHICLES.en: A conveyance; a device for carrying or transporting substances, objects or individuals.
VEHICLES.zh: 运输工具；用于运载或运输物质、物体或个人的装置。

PREVENT.en: To stop (an outcome); to keep from (doing something).

THEME.en: A subject of a talk or an artistic piece; a topic.
THEME.zh: 谈话或艺术作品的主题；一个话题。

GUITAR.en: A stringed musical instrument, of European origin, usually with a fretted fingerboard and six strings, played with the fingers or a plectrum (__ pick).
GUITAR.zh: 一种起源于欧洲的弦乐器，通常带有按动的指板和六根弦，用手指或拨片（吉他拨片）演奏。

FINDING.en: To encounter or discover by accident; to happen upon.
FINDING.zh: 偶然遇见或发现；发生在。

EXAMPLES.en: Something that is representative of all such things in a group.
EXAMPLES.zh: 代表群体中所有此类事物的事物。

CLAIMS.en: A demand of ownership made for something.

SEEM.en: To appear; to look outwardly; to be perceived as.

AFFAIRS.en: (often in the plural) Something which is done or is to be done; business of any kind, commercial, professional, or public.
AFFAIRS.zh: （通常为复数）已完成或将要完成的事情；任何类型的业务，无论是商业的、专业的还是公共的。

INTENDED.en: (usually followed by the particle "to") To hope; to wish (something, or something to be accomplished); be intent upon
INTENDED.zh: （通常后接助词“to”）希望；希望；希望（某事或要完成的事）；专心致志

GOALS.en: A result that one is attempting to achieve.
GOALS.zh: 一个人试图达到的结果。

HIRE.en: Payment for the temporary use of something.

SUGGEST.en: To imply but stop short of saying explicitly.

CHARGES.en: The amount of money levied for a service.
CHARGES.zh: 为某项服务征收的金额。

SERVE.en: An act of putting the ball or shuttlecock in play in various games.
SERVE.zh: 在各种游戏中将球或毽子投入比赛的动作。

MAGIC.en: The application of rituals or actions, especially those based on occult knowledge, to subdue or manipulate natural or supernatural beings and forces in order to have some benefit from them
MAGIC.zh: 应用仪式或行动，特别是基于神秘知识的仪式或行动，来征服或操纵自然或超自然的存在和力量，以便从中获得一些利益

TALKING.en: The action of the verb talk.

GAVE.en: (ditransitive) To move, shift, provide something abstract or concrete to someone or something or somewhere.
GAVE.zh: （双及物）移动、转移、向某人、某物或某处提供抽象或具体的东西。

AVOID.en: To try not to meet or communicate with (a person); to shun
AVOID.zh: 尽量不与（人）见面或交流；避开

RANK.en: Strong of its kind or in character; unmitigated; virulent; thorough; utter (used of negative things).
RANK.zh: 同类或性格上的坚强；毫无缓解；有毒的；彻底; utter（用于负面事物）。

BIRTH.en: The process of childbearing; the beginning of life.
BIRTH.zh: 生育的过程；生命的开始。

VIRUS.en: A submicroscopic, non-cellular structure consisting of a core of DNA or RNA surrounded by a protein coat, that requires a living host cell to replicate, and often causes disease in the host organism.
VIRUS.zh: 一种亚显微的非细胞结构，由被蛋白​​质外壳包围的 DNA 或 RNA 核心组成，需要活的宿主细胞才能复制，并且通常会导致宿主生物体患病。

ABUSE.en: Improper treatment or usage; application to a wrong or bad purpose; an unjust, corrupt or wrongful practice or custom.
ABUSE.zh: 处理或使用不当；用于错误或不良目的；不公正、腐败或错误的做法或习俗。

REQUESTS.en: Act of requesting (with the adposition at in the presence of possessives, and on in their absence).
REQUESTS.zh: 请求的行为（有所有格时用介词 at，没有所有格时用 on）。

SEPARATE.en: (usually in the plural) Anything that is sold by itself, especially an article of clothing.
SEPARATE.zh: （通常为复数）任何单独出售的东西，尤其是一件衣服。

TABLES.en: Furniture with a top surface to accommodate a variety of uses.
TABLES.zh: 具有顶面以适应多种用途的家具。

DEFINE.en: A kind of macro in source code that replaces one text string with another wherever it occurs.
DEFINE.zh: 源代码中的一种宏，无论文本字符串出现在哪里，都会将其替换为另一个文本字符串。

RACING.en: To take part in a race (in the sense of a contest).
RACING.zh: 参加比赛（竞赛意义上的）。

FACTS.en: Something actual as opposed to invented.
FACTS.zh: 与发明相反的实际事物。

COLUMN.en: A solid upright structure designed usually to support a larger structure above it, such as a roof or horizontal beam, but sometimes for decoration.
COLUMN.zh: 坚固的直立结构，通常设计用于支撑其上方的较大结构，例如屋顶或水平梁，但有时用于装饰。

PLANTS.en: An organism that is not an animal, especially an organism capable of photosynthesis. Typically a small or herbaceous organism of this kind, rather than a tree.
PLANTS.zh: 非动物的生物体，尤其是能够进行光合作用的生物体。通常是这种小型或草本生物，而不是树。

FAITH.en: A trust or confidence in the intentions or abilities of a person, object, or ideal from prior empirical evidence.
FAITH.zh: 根据先前的经验证据对人、物体或理想的意图或能力的信任或信心。

CHAIN.en: A series of interconnected rings or links usually made of metal.
CHAIN.zh: 一系列相互连接的环或链接，通常由金属制成。

IDENTIFY.en: To establish the identity of someone or something.
IDENTIFY.zh: 确定某人或某物的身份。

AVENUE.en: A broad street, especially one bordered by trees.
AVENUE.zh: 一条宽阔的街道，尤其是一条两旁树木环绕的街道。

DIED.en: To stop living; to become dead; to undergo death.
DIED.zh: 停止生活；变得死了；去经历死亡。

MOVED.en: To change place or posture; to go, in any manner, from one place or position to another.
MOVED.zh: 改变地点或姿势；以任何方式从一个地方或位置到另一个地方或位置。

REACH.en: The act of stretching or extending; extension.
REACH.zh: 伸展或伸展的动作；扩大。

MOMENT.en: A brief, unspecified amount of time.
MOMENT.zh: 一段短暂的、未指定的时间。

SEQUENCE.en: A set of things next to each other in a set order; a series
SEQUENCE.zh: 按一定顺序彼此相邻的一组事物；一系列

INCH.en: A unit of length equal to one twelfth of a foot, or exactly 2.54 centimetres.
INCH.zh: 长度单位，等于十二分之一英尺，即 2.54 厘米。

ATTACK.en: An attempt to cause damage, injury to, or death of opponent or enemy.
ATTACK.zh: 试图对对手或敌人造成损害、伤害或死亡。

SORRY.en: The act of saying __; an apology.

CENTERS.en: The point in the interior of a circle that is equidistant from all points on the circumference.
CENTERS.zh: 圆内部与圆周上所有点距离相等的点。

OPENING.en: To make something accessible or allow for passage by moving from a shut position.
OPENING.zh: 通过从关闭位置移动来使某物可接近或允许通过。

DAMAGE.en: Injury or harm; the condition or measure of something not being intact.
DAMAGE.zh: 受伤或伤害；某事物不完整的状况或措施。

RECIPES.en: A formula for preparing or using a medicine; a prescription; also, a medicine prepared from such instructions.
RECIPES.zh: 制备或使用药物的配方；处方；此外，还提供了根据此类说明制备的药物。

GAMMA.en: The third letter of the Greek alphabet (Γ, γ), preceded by beta (Β, β) and followed by delta, (Δ, δ).
GAMMA.zh: 希腊字母表的第三个字母（Г、γ），前面是 beta（Β、β），后面是 delta（Δ、δ）。

SNOW.en: The frozen, crystalline state of water that falls as precipitation.
SNOW.zh: 以降水形式落下的冰冻结晶状态的水。

PLACED.en: To put (an object or person) in a specific location.
PLACED.zh: 将（物体或人）放置在特定位置。

TRUTH.en: True facts, genuine depiction or statements of reality.
TRUTH.zh: 真实的事实、真实的描述或现实的陈述。

FAILURE.en: State or condition of not meeting a desirable or intended objective, opposite of success.
FAILURE.zh: 未达到理想或预期目标的状态或状况，与成功相反。

FOLLOWS.en: (sometimes attributive) In billiards and similar games, a stroke causing a ball to follow another ball after hitting it.
FOLLOWS.zh: （有时是定语）在台球和类似游戏中，击球使一个球在击中另一个球后跟随另一个球。

WEEKEND.en: The break in the working week, usually two days including the traditional holy or sabbath day. Thus in western countries, Saturday and Sunday.
WEEKEND.zh: 工作周的休息时间，通常是两天，包括传统的圣日或安息日。因此在西方国家，周六和周日。

DOLLAR.en: Official designation for currency in some parts of the world, including Canada, the United States, Australia, New Zealand, Hong Kong, and elsewhere. Its symbol is $.
DOLLAR.zh: 世界某些地区的货币官方指定，包括加拿大、美国、澳大利亚、新西兰、香港和其他地方。它的符号是$。

CAMP.en: An outdoor place acting as temporary accommodation in tents or other temporary structures.
CAMP.zh: 在帐篷或其他临时建筑中充当临时住所的户外场所。

FILMS.en: A thin layer of some substance; a pellicle; a membranous covering, causing opacity.
FILMS.zh: 某种物质的薄层；薄膜；膜状覆盖物，导致不透明。

FILL.en: To occupy fully, to take up all of.

PRINTING.en: To produce one or more copies of a text or image on a surface, especially by machine; often used with out or off: print out, print off.
PRINTING.zh: 在表面上制作一份或多份文本或图像副本，尤其是通过机器；常与out或off连用：打印输出、打印关闭。

BASEBALL.en: A sport common in North America, the Caribbean, and Japan, in which the object is to strike a ball so that one of a nine-person team can run counter-clockwise among four bases, resulting in the scoring of a run. The team with the most runs after termination of play, usually nine innings, wins.
BASEBALL.zh: 一项流行于北美、加勒比地区和日本的运动，其目标是击球，使九人队中的一个人能够在四个垒之间逆时针奔跑，从而获得一分。比赛结束后（通常是九局）得分最多的球队获胜。

OWNED.en: To have rightful possession of (property, goods or capital); to have legal title to.
OWNED.zh: 合法占有（财产、货物或资本）；拥有合法所有权。

DRAFT.en: A current of air, usually coming into a room or vehicle.
DRAFT.zh: 通常进入房间或​​车辆的气流。

PLAYED.en: To act in a manner such that one has fun; to engage in activities expressly for the purpose of recreation or entertainment.
PLAYED.zh: 以一种让人感到有趣的方式行事；从事明确以休闲或娱乐为目的的活动。

CONTACTS.en: The act of touching physically; being in close association.
CONTACTS.zh: 身体接触的行为；密切联系。

CLUBS.en: An association of members joining together for some common purpose, especially sports or recreation.
CLUBS.zh: 为某种共同目的（特别是体育或娱乐）而聚集在一起的成员协会。

EQUAL.en: A person or thing of __ status to others.
EQUAL.zh: 与他人具有同等地位的人或物。

MATCHING.en: To agree; to be equal; to correspond.
MATCHING.zh: 同意； to be equal;对应。

SHIRTS.en: An article of clothing that is worn on the upper part of the body, and often has sleeves, either long or short, that cover the arms.
SHIRTS.zh: 穿在上半身的衣服，通常有长袖或短袖，覆盖手臂。

PROFIT.en: Total income or cash flow minus expenditures. The money or other benefit a non-governmental organization or individual receives in exchange for products and services sold at an advertised price.
PROFIT.zh: 总收入或现金流量减去支出。非政府组织或个人以广告价格出售产品和服务而获得的金钱或其他利益。

LEADERS.en: Any person that leads or directs

POSTERS.en: A picture of a celebrity, an event etc., intended to be attached to a wall.
POSTERS.zh: 名人、活动等的照片，适合贴在墙上。

PARKING.en: To bring (something such as a vehicle) to a halt or store in a specified place.
PARKING.zh: 使（诸如车辆之类的东西）停下来或存放在指定的地方。

COMPARED.en: To assess the similarities and differences between two or more things ["to compare X with Y"]. Having made the comparison of X with Y, one might have found it similar to Y or different from Y.
COMPARED.zh: 评估两个或多个事物之间的相似点和差异[“将 X 与 Y 进行比较”]。将X与Y进行比较后，人们可能会发现它与Y相似或与Y不同。

CODES.en: A short symbol, often with little relation to the item it represents.
CODES.zh: 一个简短的符号，通常与其代表的项目关系不大。

KINDS.en: A type, race or category; a group of entities that have common characteristics such that they may be grouped together.
KINDS.zh: 类型、种族或类别；一组具有共同特征的实体，因此可以将它们组合在一起。

TEAMS.en: A set of draught animals, such as two horses in front of a carriage.
TEAMS.zh: 一组役畜，例如马车前的两匹马。

FORT.en: A __ified defensive structure stationed with troops.

SENATE.en: In some bicameral legislative systems, the upper house or chamber.
SENATE.zh: 在一些两院制立法体系中，上议院或下议院。

FORCES.en: Strength or energy of body or mind; active power; vigour; might; capacity of exercising an influence or producing an effect.
FORCES.zh: 身体或精神的力量或能量；有功功率；活力;可能;施加影响或产生效果的能力。

BROTHER.en: Son of the same parents as another person.
BROTHER.zh: 与另一个人同父母的儿子。

GENE.en: A theoretical unit of heredity of living organisms; a __ may take several values and in principle predetermines a precise trait of an organism's form (phenotype), such as hair color.
GENE.zh: 生物体遗传的理论单位；一个基因可能有几个值，并且原则上预先确定了生物体形态（表型）的精确特征，例如头发颜色。

TURNED.en: (heading) to make a non-linear physical movement.

PORTABLE.en: A __ building used for temporary purposes, particularly:
PORTABLE.zh: 用于临时用途的便携式建筑物，特别是：

TRIED.en: Tested, hence, proven to be firm or reliable.
TRIED.zh: 因此，经过测试，证明是牢固或可靠的。

DISC.en: A thin, flat, circular plate or similar object.
DISC.zh: 薄的、扁平的、圆形的板或类似物体。

RETURNED.en: To come or go back (to a place or person).
RETURNED.zh: 来或回去（到一个地方或一个人）。

BOAT.en: A craft used for transportation of goods, fishing, racing, recreational cruising, or military use on or in the water, propelled by oars or outboard motor or inboard motor or by wind.
BOAT.zh: 用于水上或水中货物运输、钓鱼、竞赛、休闲巡航或军事用途的船只，由桨或舷外发动机或舷内发动机或风驱动。

THEATRE.en: A place or building, consisting of a stage and seating, in which an audience gathers to watch plays, musical performances, public ceremonies, and so on.
THEATRE.zh: 由舞台和座位组成的地方或建筑物，观众聚集在其中观看戏剧、音乐表演、公共仪式等。

LASER.en: A device that produces a monochromatic, coherent beam of light.
LASER.zh: 产生单色相干光束的装置。

EARLIER.en: At a time in advance of the usual or expected event.
EARLIER.zh: 在通常或预期事件之前的某个时间。

SPONSOR.en: A person or organisation with some sort of responsibility for another person or organisation, especially where the responsibility has a religious, legal, or financial aspect.
SPONSOR.zh: 对另一个人或组织负有某种责任的个人或组织，尤其是当责任涉及宗教、法律或财务方面时。

ICON.en: An image, symbol, picture, or other representation usually as an object of religious devotion.
ICON.zh: 通常作为宗教信仰对象的图像、符号、图片或其他表示形式。

WARRANTY.en: A guarantee that a certain outcome or obligation will be fulfilled; security.
WARRANTY.zh: 保证一定的结果或义务将得到履行；安全。

OBJECTS.en: A thing that has physical existence.

ENDS.en: The terminal point of something in space or time.
ENDS.zh: 空间或时间中某物的终点。

DELETE.en: A key that may be pressed to __ something (such as text or files) from a computer.
DELETE.zh: 按下该键可从计算机中删除某些内容（例如文本或文件）。

ASSEMBLY.en: A set of pieces that work together in unison as a mechanism or device.
ASSEMBLY.zh: 作为机制或设备协同工作的一组部件。

TAXES.en: Money paid to the government other than for transaction-specific goods and services.
TAXES.zh: 除特定交易的商品和服务外，还向政府支付的款项。

MOUSE.en: Any small rodent of the genus Mus.
MOUSE.zh: 鼠属的任何小型啮齿动物。

ISSUED.en: To flow out, to proceed from, to come out or from.

BRAIN.en: The control center of the central nervous system of an animal located in the skull which is responsible for perception, cognition, attention, memory, emotion, and action.
BRAIN.zh: 动物中枢神经系统的控制中心位于头骨，负责感知、认知、注意力、记忆、情感和行动。

SEXUAL.en: A species which reproduces by __ rather than a__ reproduction, or a member of such a species.
SEXUAL.zh: 通过有性繁殖而不是无性繁殖的物种，或该物种的成员。

DREAM.en: Imaginary events seen in the mind while sleeping.
DREAM.zh: 睡觉时脑海中看到的想象事件。

OBTAINED.en: To get hold of; to gain possession of, to procure; to acquire, in any way.
OBTAINED.zh: 抓住;获得占有，取得；以任何方式获得。

FALSE.en: One of two options on a true-or-__ test.
FALSE.zh: 真或假测试的两个选项之一。

FELT.en: A cloth or stuff made of matted fibres of wool, or wool and fur, fulled or wrought into a compact substance by rolling and pressure, with lees or size, without spinning or weaving.
FELT.zh: 由羊毛或羊毛和毛皮的缠结纤维制成的布或材料，通过滚动和压力，用酒糟或浆料填充或加工成致密物质，无需纺纱或编织。

SUPPLIED.en: To provide (something), to make (something) available for use.
SUPPLIED.zh: 提供（某物），使（某物）可供使用。

FALLS.en: The act of moving to a lower position under the effect of gravity.
FALLS.zh: 在重力作用下移动到较低位置的行为。

SOUL.en: The spirit or essence of a person usually thought to consist of one's thoughts and personality. Often believed to live on after the person's death.
SOUL.zh: 一个人的精神或本质通常被认为由一个人的思想和个性组成。通常认为人死后仍会继续存在。

OPINIONS.en: A subjective belief, judgment or perspective that a person has formed about a topic, issue, person or thing.
OPINIONS.zh: 一个人对某个主题、问题、人或事物形成的主观信念、判断或观点。

STATED.en: To declare to be a fact.

STATS.en: A mathematical science concerned with data collection, presentation, analysis, and interpretation.
STATS.zh: 一门涉及数据收集、呈现、分析和解释的数学科学。

APPEARS.en: To come or be in sight; to be in view; to become visible.
APPEARS.zh: 来到或出现在眼前；在视野中；变得可见。

CARRY.en: A manner of transporting or lifting something; the grip or position in which something is carried.
CARRY.zh: 运输或提升某物的方式；携带某物的抓握或位置。

FLAG.en: A piece of cloth, often decorated with an emblem, used as a visual signal or symbol.
FLAG.zh: 一块布，通常装饰有徽章，用作视觉信号或符号。

DECIDED.en: To resolve (a contest, problem, dispute, etc.); to choose, determine, or settle
DECIDED.zh: 解决（竞赛、问题、争议等）；选择、决定或解决

DESIGNS.en: A specification of an object or process, referring to requirements to be satisfied and thus conditions to be met for them to solve a problem.
DESIGNS.zh: 对象或过程的规范，指的是要满足的要求以及解决问题所需满足的条件。

TOURISM.en: The act of travelling or sightseeing, particularly away from one's home.
TOURISM.zh: 旅行或观光的行为，尤其是离开家的行为。

PRIORITY.zh: 一个项目的相对重要性。

ADULTS.en: A fully grown human or animal.

CLIPS.en: Something which __ or grasps; a device for attaching one object to another.
CLIPS.zh: 夹住或抓住的东西；用于将一个物体连接到另一个物体上的装置。

SAVINGS.en: A reduction in cost or expenditure.

ATOM.en: The smallest possible amount of matter which still retains its identity as a chemical element, now known to consist of a nucleus surrounded by electrons.
ATOM.zh: 仍然保留其化学元素特性的尽可能少的物质，现在已知由被电子包围的原子核组成。

BINDING.en: To tie; to confine by any ligature.
BINDING.zh: 打结；通过任何结扎来限制。

BRIEF.en: A writ summoning one to answer to any action.
BRIEF.zh: 传唤人对任何行动作出回应的令状。

IRON.en: A common, inexpensive metal, silvery grey when untarnished, that rusts, is attracted by magnets, and is used in making steel.
IRON.zh: 一种常见的廉价金属，未变色时呈银灰色，会生锈，被磁铁吸引，用于炼钢。

STRAIGHT.en: Something that is not crooked or bent such as a part of a road or track.
STRAIGHT.zh: 不弯曲或不弯曲的物体，例如道路或轨道的一部分。

SERVED.en: (personal) To provide a service (or, by extension, a product, especially food or drink).
SERVED.zh: （个人）提供服务（或者延伸到产品，尤其是食物或饮料）。

PREPARED.en: To make ready for a specific future purpose; to set up; to assemble or equip.
PREPARED.zh: 为未来的特定目的做好准备；设立；组装或装备。

DINING.en: To eat; to eat dinner or supper.

DISK.en: A thin, flat, circular plate or similar object.
DISK.zh: 薄的、扁平的、圆形的板或类似物体。

QUEEN.zh: 一位女君主。例如：维多利亚女王。

CREDITS.en: Reliance on the truth of something said or done; faith; trust.
CREDITS.zh: 相信所说或所做的事情的真实性；信仰;相信。

SWEET.en: The basic taste sensation induced by sugar.

DESK.en: A table, frame, or case, in past centuries usually with a sloping top but now usually with a flat top, for the use of writers and readers. It often has a drawer or repository underneath.
DESK.zh: 桌子、框架或盒子，在过去的几个世纪中通常具有倾斜的顶部，但现在通常具有平顶，供作家和读者使用。它下面通常有一个抽屉或存储库。

TRUCK.en: A small wheel or roller, specifically the wheel of a gun carriage.
TRUCK.zh: 小轮子或滚轮，特指炮架的轮子。

BEHAVIOR.en: Human conduct relative to social norms.
BEHAVIOR.zh: 与社会规范相关的人类行为。

RAY.en: A beam of light or radiation.

VOTES.en: A formalized choice on matters of administration or other democratic activities
VOTES.zh: 对行政事务或其他民主活动的正式选择

DUTY.en: That which one is morally or legally obligated to do.
DUTY.zh: 一个人在道德上或法律上有义务去做的事情。

BEAR.en: A large omnivorous mammal, related to the dog and raccoon, having shaggy hair, a very small tail, and flat feet; a member of family Ursidae.
BEAR.zh: 一种大型杂食性哺乳动物，与狗和浣熊有关，具有蓬松的毛发、非常小的尾巴和扁平足；熊科的成员。

OCEAN.en: One of the large bodies of water separating the continents.
OCEAN.zh: 分隔大陆的大型水域之一。

EXPERTS.en: A person with extensive knowledge or ability in a given subject.
EXPERTS.zh: 在某一特定学科领域具有广泛知识或能力的人。

SIGNS.en: (sometimes also used uncountably) A visible indication.
SIGNS.zh: （有时也用于不可数）可见的指示。

LACK.en: A defect or failing; moral or spiritual degeneracy.
LACK.zh: 缺陷或失败；道德或精神的堕落。

DEPTH.en: The vertical distance below a surface; the degree to which something is deep
DEPTH.zh: 表面以下的垂直距离；某事物的深度

VINTAGE.en: The yield of grapes or wine from a vineyard or district during one season.
VINTAGE.zh: 一个葡萄园或地区在一个季节内葡萄或葡萄酒的产量。

DRY.en: The process by which something is dried.

SPA.en: A health resort near a mineral spring or hot spring.
SPA.zh: 靠近矿泉或温泉的疗养胜地。

CHECKOUT.en: The process of checking out of a hotel, or the latest time to vacate a room in one.
CHECKOUT.zh: 退房的过程，或者最晚腾出房间的时间。

HANDLING.en: A touching, controlling, managing, using, take care of, etc., with the hand or hands, or as with the hands.
HANDLING.zh: 用手或用手或用手触摸、控制、管理、使用、照顾等。

KNEW.en: To perceive the truth or factuality of; to be certain of or that.
KNEW.zh: 感知以下事实的真相或事实；确定或那个。

FEEDS.zh: 给（尤其是草食性）动物的食物。

FASTER.en: Firmly or securely fixed in place; stable.
FASTER.zh: 牢固或可靠地固定到位；稳定的。

BOUGHT.en: To obtain (something) in exchange for money or goods
BOUGHT.zh: 用金钱或物品换取（某物）

CON.en: To study or examine carefully, especially in order to gain knowledge of; to learn, or learn by heart.
CON.zh: 仔细研究或检查，尤其是为了获得知识；去学习，或者用心去学习。

UPS.en: The direction opposed to the pull of gravity.
UPS.zh: 与重力方向相反的方向。

NATIONS.en: A historically constituted, stable community of people, formed on the basis of a common language, territory, economic life, ethnicity and/or psychological make-up manifested in a common culture.
NATIONS.zh: 在历史上形成的、稳定的人民共同体，在共同语言、领土、经济生活、种族和/或共同文化所体现的心理素质的基础上形成。

ROUTE.en: A course or way which is traveled or passed.
ROUTE.zh: 旅行或通过的路线或方式。

FOLLOWED.en: To go after; to pursue; to move behind in the same path or direction.
FOLLOWED.zh: 去追寻；追求；沿相同的路径或方向向后移动。

BROKEN.en: To separate into two or more pieces, to fracture or crack, by a process that cannot easily be reversed for reassembly.
BROKEN.zh: 通过无法轻易逆转重新组装的过程，将其分成两块或多块，使其断裂或破裂。

FRANK.en: Free postage, a right exercised by governments (usually with definite article).
FRANK.zh: 免费邮资，政府行使的权利（通常带有定冠词）。

ZOOM.en: To communicate with someone using the __ videoconferencing software.
ZOOM.zh: 使用 __ 视频会议软件与某人进行交流。

ANIME.en: An artistic style originating in, and associated with, Japanese animation, and that has also been adopted by a comparatively low number of animated works from other countries.
ANIME.zh: 一种起源于日本动画并与之相关的艺术风格，也被少数其他国家的动画作品所采用。

SPEAK.zh: 一个低级酒吧，一个地下酒吧。

PROTOCOL.en: The minutes, or official record, of a negotiation or transaction; especially a document drawn up officially which forms the legal basis for subsequent agreements based on it.
PROTOCOL.zh: 谈判或交易的会议记录或正式记录；特别是正式起草的文件，构成后续协议的法律基础。

QUERY.en: A question, an inquiry (US), an enquiry (UK).
QUERY.zh: 一个问题，一个询问（美国），一个询问（英国）。

CLIP.en: Something which __s or grasps; a device for attaching one object to another.
CLIP.zh: 夹住或抓住的东西；用于将一个物体连接到另一个物体上的装置。

EQUITY.en: Fairness, impartiality, or justice as determined in light of "natural law" or "natural right".
EQUITY.zh: 根据“自然法”或“自然权利”确定的公平、公正或正义。

SPEECH.en: The faculty of uttering articulate sounds or words; the ability to speak or to use vocalizations to communicate.
SPEECH.zh: 发出清晰的声音或单词的能力；说话或使用发声进行交流的能力。

WIRE.en: Metal formed into a thin, even thread, now usually by being drawn through a hole in a steel die.
WIRE.zh: 金属形成细而均匀的线，现在通常通过钢模上的孔拉拔。

RURAL.en: A person from the countryside; a rustic.
RURAL.zh: 一个来自农村的人；质朴的。

SHARED.en: To give part of what one has to somebody else to use or consume.
SHARED.zh: 将自己所拥有的一部分给予他人使用或消费。

SOUNDS.en: A sensation perceived by the ear caused by the vibration of air or some other medium.
SOUNDS.zh: 由空气或其他介质的振动引起的耳朵感知的感觉。

TAPE.en: Flexible material in a roll with a sticky surface on one or both sides; adhesive __.
TAPE.zh: 卷状柔性材料，一侧或两侧具有粘性表面；胶带。

JUDGE.en: A public official whose duty it is to administer the law, especially by presiding over trials and rendering judgments; a justice.
JUDGE.zh: 职责是执行法律，特别是主持审判和作出判决的公职人员；一位正义者。

SPAM.zh: （很少可数）未经请求的批量电子消息。

BYTES.en: A short sequence of bits (binary digits) that can be operated on as a unit by a computer; the smallest usable machine word.
BYTES.zh: 可由计算机作为一个单元进行操作的短位序列（二进制数字）；最小的可用机器字。

CENT.en: (money) A subunit of currency equal to one-hundredth of the main unit of currency in many countries. Symbol: ¢.
CENT.zh: （货币）一种货币子单位，在许多国家等于主要货币单位的百分之一。符号：￠。

FIGHT.en: To contend in physical conflict, either singly or in war, battle etc.
FIGHT.zh: 在身体冲突中进行斗争，无论是单独还是在战争、战斗等中。

HEIGHT.en: The distance from the base of something to the top.
HEIGHT.zh: 从某物的底部到顶部的距离。

NULL.en: A non-existent or empty value or set of values.
NULL.zh: 不存在或为空的值或值集。

ZERO.en: The numeric symbol that represents the cardinal number __.
ZERO.zh: 代表基数零的数字符号。

FILED.en: To commit (official papers) to some office.
FILED.zh: 将（官方文件）提交给某个办公室。

OFFICES.en: A ceremonial duty or service, particularly:
OFFICES.zh: 仪式性职责或服务，特别是：

REMAIN.en: (chiefly in the plural) That which is left; relic; __der.

MANAGED.en: To direct or be in charge of.

ROLL.en: The act or result of __ing, or state of being __ed.
ROLL.zh: 滚动的行为或结果，或被滚动的状态。

BANKS.en: An institution where one can place and borrow money and take care of financial affairs.
BANKS.zh: 可以存入、借入资金并处理财务事务的机构。

BATH.en: A tub or pool which is used for __ing: __tub.
BATH.zh: 用于沐浴的浴缸或水池：浴缸。

LEADS.en: A heavy, pliable, inelastic metal element, having a bright, bluish color, but easily tarnished; both malleable and ductile, though with little tenacity. It is easily fusible, forms alloys with other metals, and is an ingredient of solder and type metal. Atomic number 82, symbol Pb (from Latin plumbum).
LEADS.zh: 一种重、柔韧、无弹性的金属元素，具有明亮的蓝色，但很容易失去光泽；具有延展性和延展性，但缺乏韧性。它很容易熔化，与其他金属形成合金，并且是焊料和金属的成分。原子序数82，符号Pb（来自拉丁文plumbum）。

THEATER.en: A place or building, consisting of a stage and seating, in which an audience gathers to watch plays, musical performances, public ceremonies, and so on.
THEATER.zh: 由舞台和座位组成的地方或建筑物，观众聚集在其中观看戏剧、音乐表演、公共仪式等。

SPRINGS.en: To weaken, as a joint, ligament, or muscle, by sudden and excessive exertion, as by wrenching; to overstrain, or stretch injuriously, but without luxation
SPRINGS.zh: 由于突然过度用力，如扭动，使关节、韧带或肌肉变弱；过度紧张或损伤性伸展，但不脱位

VAR.en: A unit of electrical power, in an AC circuit, equal to the power dissipated when 1 volt produces a current of 1 ampere.
VAR.zh: 交流电路中的电功率单位，等于 1 伏特产生 1 安培电流时消耗的功率。

FONT.en: A receptacle in a church for holy water, especially one used in baptism.
FONT.zh: 教堂中盛装圣水的容器，尤其是用于洗礼的容器。

ASSETS.en: Something or someone of any value; any portion of one's property or effects so considered.
ASSETS.zh: 有任何价值的东西或人；如此考虑的一个人的财产或财物的任何部分。

INJURY.en: Damage to the body of a human or animal.
INJURY.zh: 对人类或动物的身体造成损害。

MINISTRY.en: Government department, at the administrative level normally headed by a minister (or equivalent rank, e.g. secretary of state), who holds it as portfolio, especially in a constitutional monarchy, but also as a polity
MINISTRY.zh: 政府部门，在行政级别，通常由部长（或同等级别，例如国务卿）领导，他作为部长负责，特别是在君主立宪制国家，但也作为一个政体

DRIVERS.en: One who drives something, in any sense of the verb to drive.
DRIVERS.zh: 一个驾驶某物的人，无论是在动词驾驶的任何意义上。

LAWYER.en: A professional person qualified (as by a law degree or bar exam) and authorized to practice law, i.e. represent parties in lawsuits or trials and give legal advice.
LAWYER.zh: 具有资格（如通过法律学位或律师考试）并有权执业的专业人士，即在诉讼或审判中代表当事人并提供法律建议。

FIGURES.en: A drawing or diagram conveying information.
FIGURES.zh: 传达信息的绘图或图表。

SHARING.en: To give part of what one has to somebody else to use or consume.
SHARING.zh: 将自己所拥有的一部分给予他人使用或消费。

PORTAL.en: An entrance, entry point, or means of entry.
PORTAL.zh: 入口、入口点或进入方式。

WAITING.en: To delay movement or action until the arrival or occurrence of; to await. (Now generally superseded by “wait for”.)
WAITING.zh: 延迟移动或行动，直至以下情况发生或发生；等待。 （现在通常被“等待”取代。）

BIRTHDAY.en: The anniversary of the day on which someone is born.
BIRTHDAY.zh: 某人出生的周年纪念日。

BETA.en: The second letter of the Greek alphabet (Β,  β), preceded by alpha (Α,  α) and followed by gamma, (Γ,  γ). In modern Greek it represents the voiced labiodental fricative sound of v found in the English words have and vase.
BETA.zh: 希腊字母表中的第二个字母 (Β, β)，前面是 alpha (α, α)，后面是 gamma (Γ, γ)。在现代希腊语中，它代表英语单词have和vase中v的浊唇齿擦音。

BANKING.en: To deal with a bank or financial institution, or for an institution to provide financial services to a client.
BANKING.zh: 与银行或金融机构打交道，或为客户提供金融服务的机构。

TOWARD.en: Yielding, pliant; docile; ready or apt to learn; not froward.
TOWARD.zh: 屈服、柔顺；温顺;准备好或易于学习；不向前。

ASSIST.en: A helpful action or an act of giving.
ASSIST.zh: 有益的行动或给予的行为。

LINGERIE.en: Women's underwear or nightclothes, now especially when lacy or designed to be seductive.
LINGERIE.zh: 女士内衣或睡衣，尤其是带有蕾丝或设计性感的内衣或睡衣。

JAZZ.en: A musical art form rooted in West African cultural and musical expression and in the African American blues tradition, with diverse influences over time, commonly characterized by blue notes, syncopation, swing, call and response, polyrhythms and improvisation.
JAZZ.zh: 一种植根于西非文化和音乐表现形式以及非裔美国蓝调传统的音乐艺术形式，随着时间的推移产生了多种影响，通常以蓝调、切分音、摇摆、呼唤和响应、多节奏和即兴创作为特征。

SERVING.en: (personal) To provide a service (or, by extension, a product, especially food or drink).
SERVING.zh: （个人）提供服务（或者延伸到产品，尤其是食物或饮料）。

BAGS.en: A flexible container made of cloth, paper, plastic, etc.
BAGS.zh: 由布、纸、塑料等制成的柔性容器。

PROFILES.en: The outermost shape, view, or edge of an object.
PROFILES.zh: 物体最外层的形状、视图或边缘。

HOUSES.en: A structure built or serving as an abode of human beings.
HOUSES.zh: 建造或用作人类住所的建筑物。

POSTAL.en: Relating to the collection, sorting and delivery of mail.
POSTAL.zh: 涉及邮件的收集、分类和递送。

BREAKING.en: To separate into two or more pieces, to fracture or crack, by a process that cannot easily be reversed for reassembly.
BREAKING.zh: 通过无法轻易逆转重新组装的过程，将其分成两块或多块，使其断裂或破裂。

COMBINED.en: An event in alpine skiing which combines runs on a downhill skiing course and a slalom course, for individual skiers.
COMBINED.zh: 一项针对个人滑雪者的高山滑雪赛事，结合了速降滑雪场和回转赛场的滑行。

MINOR.en: A person who is below the age of majority, consent, criminal responsibility or other adult responsibilities and accountabilities.
MINOR.zh: 未达到法定成年年龄、同意年龄、刑事责任或其他成人责任和义务的人。

FINISH.en: An end; the end of anything.
FINISH.zh: 一个结束；任何事情的结束。

NOTED.en: To notice with care; to observe; to remark; to heed.
NOTED.zh: 小心留意；观察；评论；留意。

REDUCED.en: To bring down the size, quantity, quality, value or intensity of something; to diminish, to lower.
REDUCED.zh: 降低某物的大小、数量、质量、价值或强度；减少，降低。

PHYSICS.en: A medicine or drug, especially a cathartic or purgative.
PHYSICS.zh: 药品或药物，尤其是泻药或泻药。

SAMPLES.en: A part or snippet of something taken or presented for inspection, or shown as evidence of the quality of the whole; a specimen.
SAMPLES.zh: 为检查而采取或呈现的某物的一部分或片段，或作为整体质量的证据；一个标本。

BARS.en: A solid, more or less rigid object of metal or wood with a uniform cross-section smaller than its length.
BARS.zh: 固体，或多或少刚性的金属或木材物体，具有小于其长度的均匀横截面。

REVIEWED.en: To survey; to look broadly over.

ROW.en: A line of objects, often regularly spaced, such as seats in a theatre, vegetable plants in a garden etc.
ROW.zh: 一排物体，通常间隔规则，例如剧院的座位、花园里的蔬菜植物等。

REMOVED.en: To move something from one place to another, especially to take away.
REMOVED.zh: 将某物从一处移至另一处，尤指拿走。

HELPS.en: Action given to provide assistance; aid.
HELPS.zh: 为提供援助而采取的行动；援助。
