SINGLES.en: A 45 RPM vinyl record with one song on side A and one on side B.
SINGLES.zh: 一张 45 RPM 黑胶唱片，A 面一首歌曲，B 面一首歌曲。

CYCLE.en: An interval of space or time in which one set of events or phenomena is completed.
CYCLE.zh: 完成一组事件或现象的空间或时间间隔。

AMOUNTS.en: The total, aggregate or sum of material (not applicable to discrete numbers or units or items in standard English).
AMOUNTS.zh: 材料的总计、合计或总和（不适用于标准英语中的离散数字或单位或项目）。

ACCURACY.en: The state of being accurate; being free from mistakes, this exemption arising from carefulness; exactness; correctness
ACCURACY.zh: 准确的状态；没有错误，这种豁免是由于谨慎而产生的；精确;正确性

DUAL.en: Of an item that is one of a pair, the other item in the pair.
DUAL.zh: 对于一对中的一个项目，该对中的另一个项目。

RISE.en: To move, or appear to move, physically upwards relative to the ground.
RISE.zh: 相对于地面物理向上移动或看似移动。

SLEEP.en: To rest in a state of reduced consciousness.
SLEEP.zh: 在意识减弱的状态下休息。

BIRD.en: A member of the class of animals Aves in the phylum Chordata, characterized by being warm-blooded, having feathers and wings usually capable of flight, and laying eggs.
BIRD.zh: 脊索动物门鸟纲的成员，其特征是温血动物，具有通常能够飞行的羽毛和翅膀，并且产卵。

PHARMACY.en: (countable) A place where prescription drugs are dispensed; a dispensary.
PHARMACY.zh: （可数）配发处方药的地方；药房。

BRAZIL.en: A red-orange dye obtained from __ wood.
BRAZIL.zh: 从巴西木材中提取的红橙色染料。

CREATION.en: Something created such as an invention or artwork.
CREATION.zh: 创造出来的东西，例如发明或艺术品。

STATIC.en: Interference on a broadcast signal caused by atmospheric disturbances; heard as crackles on radio, or seen as random specks on television.
STATIC.zh: 大气扰动对广播信号造成的干扰；在收音机中听到的是爆裂声，或者在电视上看到的是随机斑点。

SCENE.en: The location of an event that attracts attention.
SCENE.zh: 引起注意的事件的地点。

HUNTER.en: One who hunts game for sport or for food; a huntsman or huntswoman.
HUNTER.zh: 为运动或食物而狩猎的人；猎人或女猎人。

LADY.en: An aristocratic title for a woman; the wife of a lord and/or a woman who holds the position in her own right; a title for a peeress, the wife of a peer or knight, and the daughters and daughters-in-law of certain peers.
LADY.zh: 女性的贵族头衔；领主的妻子和/或凭借自己的权利担任职位的妇女；对贵族女性、贵族或骑士的妻子以及某些贵族的女儿和儿媳的头衔。

FAMOUS.en: To make __; to bring renown to.

WRITER.en: A person who writes, or produces literary work.
WRITER.zh: 写作或创作文学作品的人。

CHAIRMAN.en: A person presiding over a meeting.

FANS.en: A hand-held device consisting of concertinaed material, or slats of material, gathered together at one end, that may be opened out into the shape of a sector of a circle and waved back and forth in order to move air towards oneself and cool oneself.
FANS.zh: 一种手持式装置，由六角形材料或材料板条组成，一端聚集在一起，可以打开成扇形，并前后挥动，以便将空气吹向自己并为自己降温。

DRINK.en: To consume (a liquid) through the mouth.

ACADEMY.en: (usually capitalized) The garden where Plato taught.
ACADEMY.zh: （通常大写）柏拉图教学的花园。

DYNAMIC.en: A characteristic or manner of an interaction; a behavior.
DYNAMIC.zh: 交互的特征或方式；一种行为。

EAT.en: Something to be __en; a meal; a food item.
EAT.zh: 可以吃的东西；一顿饭；一种食品。

DELL.en: A valley, especially in the form of a natural hollow, small and deep.
DELL.zh: 山谷，特指自然凹陷的山谷，小而深。

CLEANING.en: To remove dirt from a place or object.
CLEANING.zh: 清除某个地方或物体上的污垢。

CONCERNS.en: That which affects one’s welfare or happiness. A matter of interest to someone. The adposition before the matter of interest is usually over, about or for.
CONCERNS.zh: 影响一个人的福利或幸福的事物。某人感兴趣的事情。感兴趣的事物之前的介词通常是 over、about 或 for。

COLOUR.en: The spectral composition of visible light

VENDOR.en: A person or a company that vends or sells.
VENDOR.zh: 贩卖或销售的个人或公司。

OFFICERS.en: One who has a position of authority in a hierarchical organization, especially in military, police or government organizations.
OFFICERS.zh: 在等级组织中，特别是在军队、警察或政府组织中拥有权威职位的人。

AIM.en: The pointing of a weapon, as a gun, a dart, or an arrow, or object, in the line of direction with the object intended to be struck; the line of fire; the direction of anything, such as a spear, a blow, a discourse, a remark, towards a particular point or object, with a view to strike or affect it.
AIM.zh: 将武器（如枪、飞镖、箭或物体）指向要攻击的物体的方向；火线；任何事物的方向，例如矛、打击、话语、言论，指向特定的点或物体，以打击或影响它。

BIDS.en: To issue a command; to tell.

REGIONS.en: Any considerable and connected part of a space or surface; specifically, a tract of land or sea of considerable but indefinite extent; a country; a district; in a broad sense, a place without special reference to location or extent but viewed as an entity for geographical, social or cultural reasons.
REGIONS.zh: 空间或表面的任何重要且相连的部分；具体来说，是一块相当大但不确定范围的陆地或海洋；一个国家；一个区；从广义上讲，一个地方，没有特别提到位置或范围，但由于地理、社会或文化原因被视为一个实体。

TOLL.en: Loss or damage incurred through a disaster.
TOLL.zh: 灾难造成的损失或损坏。

LES.en: A homosexual woman, one who is mostly or exclusively sexually or romantically attracted to other women.
LES.zh: 同性恋女性，主要或完全被其他女性性或浪漫吸引的女性。

CAPE.en: A piece or point of land, extending beyond the adjacent coast into a sea or lake; a promontory; a headland.
CAPE.zh: 一块或一点陆地，延伸到邻近的海岸之外，进入海洋或湖泊；海角；岬角。

RINGS.en: (physical) A solid object in the shape of a circle.

MEANING.en: (of words or symbols) The entity, perception, feeling or concept thereby represented or evoked.
MEANING.zh: （词语或符号）由此表示或唤起的实体、感知、感觉或概念。

MINE.en: My; belonging to me; that which belongs to me.
MINE.zh: 我的;属于我的；属于我的。

LADIES.en: An aristocratic title for a woman; the wife of a lord and/or a woman who holds the position in her own right; a title for a peeress, the wife of a peer or knight, and the daughters and daughters-in-law of certain peers.
LADIES.zh: 女性的贵族头衔；领主的妻子和/或凭借自己的权利担任职位的妇女；对贵族女性、贵族或骑士的妻子以及某些贵族的女儿和儿媳的头衔。

HENRY.en: In the International System of Units, the derived unit of electrical inductance; the inductance induced in a circuit by a rate of change of current of one ampere per second and a resulting electromotive force of one volt. Symbol: H
HENRY.zh: 在国际单位制中，电感的衍生单位；每秒一安培的电流变化率和一伏特的电动势在电路中感应的电感。符号：H

TICKET.en: A pass entitling the holder to admission to a show, concert, etc.
TICKET.zh: 持有者有权观看演出、音乐会等的通行证。

GUESS.en: To reach a partly (or totally) unqualified conclusion.
GUESS.zh: 得出部分（或完全）无条件的结论。

AGREED.en: To harmonize in opinion, statement, or action; to be in unison or concord; to be or become united or consistent; to concur.
AGREED.zh: 协调意见、声明或行动；一致或一致；变得团结或一致；同意。

WHOM.en: (interrogative) What person or people; which person or people.
WHOM.zh: （疑问）什么人或哪些人；哪个人或哪些人。

SKI.en: One of a pair of long flat runners designed for gliding over snow or water
SKI.zh: 一对长平滑道之一，设计用于在雪或水上滑行

MATH.en: A mowing; what is gathered from mowing.
MATH.zh: 割草；割草时收集到的东西。

IMPORT.en: Something brought in from an exterior source, especially for sale or trade.
IMPORT.zh: 从外部来源带来的东西，特别是为了销售或贸易。

POSTING.en: To hang (a notice) in a conspicuous manner for general review.
POSTING.zh: 以显眼的方式悬挂（通知）以供一般审查。

PRESENCE.en: The fact or condition of being present, or of being within sight or call, or at hand.
PRESENCE.zh: 存在的事实或条件，或在视线范围内或呼叫范围内，或在手边。

INSTANT.en: A very short period of time; a moment.
INSTANT.zh: 很短的一段时间；一会儿。

CHRIST.en: A figure or other artistic depiction of Jesus __.
CHRIST.zh: 耶稣基督的人物或其他艺术描绘。

DAN.en: A title of honour similar to "master" or "father", used of historical and legendary figures of the past.
DAN.zh: 类似于“大师”或“父亲”的荣誉称号，用于过去的历史和传奇人物。

DOGS.en: A mammal, Canis familiaris or Canis lupus familiaris, that has been domesticated for thousands of years, of highly variable appearance due to human breeding.
DOGS.zh: 一种哺乳动物，犬科动物（Canisamilis）或犬狼疮（Canislupusfamilias），已被驯化数千年，由于人类繁殖而具有高度可变的外观。

ASPECTS.en: Any specific feature, part, or element of something.
ASPECTS.zh: 某事物的任何特定特征、部分或元素。

AHEAD.en: In or to the front; in advance; onward.

MOON.en: The Earth's __ Luna; the sole natural satellite of the Earth, represented in astronomy and astrology by ☾.
MOON.zh: 地球的月亮Luna；地球唯一的天然卫星，在天文学和占星学中用 ☾ 表示。

UTILITY.en: The state or condition of being useful; usefulness.
UTILITY.zh: 有用的状态或条件；用处。

FLY.en: Any insect of the order Diptera; characterized by having two wings (except for some wingless species), also called true flies.
FLY.zh: 双翅目任何昆虫；其特征是有两个翅膀（某些无翅品种除外），也称为真蝇。

STRENGTH.en: The quality or degree of being strong.

PROPER.en: Something set apart for a special use.
PROPER.zh: 为特殊用途而专门设置的东西。

DEGREES.en: A stage of proficiency or qualification in a course of study, now especially an award bestowed by a university or, in some countries, a college, as a certification of academic achievement. (In the United States, can include secondary schools.)
DEGREES.zh: 学习课程中的熟练程度或资格阶段，现在特指由大学或在某些国家/地区由学院授予的奖项，作为学术成就的证明。 （在美国，可以包括中学。）

DELTA.en: The fourth letter of the modern Greek alphabet Δ, δ.
DELTA.zh: 现代希腊字母表的第四个字母Δ、δ。

FEAR.en: A strong, uncontrollable, unpleasant emotion or feeling caused by actual or perceived danger or threat.
FEAR.zh: 由实际或感知的危险或威胁引起的强烈、无法控制、不愉快的情绪或感觉。

SEEKING.en: To try to find; to look for; to search for.

INCHES.en: A unit of length equal to one twelfth of a foot, or exactly 2.54 centimetres.
INCHES.zh: 长度单位，等于十二分之一英尺，即 2.54 厘米。

PHOENIX.en: A mythological bird, said to be the only one of its kind, which lives for 500 years and then dies by burning to ashes on a pyre of its own making, ignited by the sun. It then arises anew from the ashes.
PHOENIX.zh: 一种神话鸟，据说是同类中唯一的一种，能活 500 年，然后在太阳点燃的柴堆上烧成灰烬而死。然后它会从灰烬中重新出现。

SHARES.en: A portion of something, especially a portion given or allotted to someone.
SHARES.zh: 某物的一部分，尤其是给予或分配给某人的一部分。

STANDING.en: (heading) To position or be positioned physically.

COLORS.en: The spectral composition of visible light

WARS.en: Organized, large-scale, armed conflict between countries or between national, ethnic, or other sizeable groups, usually involving the engagement of military forces.
WARS.zh: 国家之间或民族、种族或其他较大群体之间有组织的大规模武装冲突，通常涉及军事力量的参与。

CISCO.en: Any North American freshwater fish of certain species of the genus Coregonus that live in cold-water lakes.
CISCO.zh: 生活在冷水湖中的任何北美淡水鱼，属于 Coregonus 属的某些种类。

ORDERING.en: To set in some sort of order.

KEPT.en: To continue in (a course or mode of action); not to intermit or fall from; to uphold or maintain.
KEPT.zh: 继续（行动方针或模式）；不要中断或跌倒；坚持或维持。

ALPHA.en: The name of the first letter of the Greek __bet (Α,  α), followed by beta. In the Latin __bet it is the predecessor to A.
ALPHA.zh: 名称采用希腊字母表的第一个字母（α、α），后面是 beta。在拉丁字母中，它是 A 的前身。

APPEAL.en: An application for the removal of a cause or suit from an inferior to a superior judge or court for re-examination or review.
APPEAL.zh: 向上级法官或法院提出撤销案件或诉讼以进行重新审查或复审的申请。

CRUISE.en: A sea or lake voyage, especially one taken for pleasure.
CRUISE.zh: 海上或湖泊航行，尤其是为了享乐而进行的航行。

BONUS.en: Something extra that is good; an added benefit.
BONUS.zh: 额外的东西是好的；一个额外的好处。

BOOKMARK.en: A strip of material used to mark a place in a book.
BOOKMARK.zh: 用于标记书中某个位置的一条材料。

SPECIALS.en: A reduction in consumer cost (usually for a limited time) for items or services rendered.
SPECIALS.zh: 所提供的物品或服务的消费者成本降低（通常是在有限的时间内）。

ADOBE.en: An unburnt brick dried in the sun.
ADOBE.zh: 未烧完的砖在阳光下晒干。

SMOKING.en: To inhale and exhale the smoke from a burning cigarette, cigar, pipe, etc.
SMOKING.zh: 吸入和呼出燃烧的香烟、雪茄、烟斗等产生的烟雾。

DRIVES.en: Motivation to do or achieve something; ability coupled with ambition.
DRIVES.zh: 做某事或取得某事的动机；能力加上野心。

ARMS.en: The portion of the upper human appendage, from the shoulder to the wrist and sometimes including the hand.
ARMS.zh: 人类上肢的部分，从肩膀到手腕，有时包括手。

TEA.en: A drug smoked or ingested for euphoric effect, cannabis.
TEA.zh: 大麻是一种为了产生欣快效果而吸食或摄入的药物。

IMPROVED.en: To make (something) better; to increase the value or productivity (of something).
IMPROVED.zh: 使（某事）变得更好；增加（某物）的价值或生产力。

TREES.en: Fast growing function based on Kruskal's tree theorem.
TREES.zh: 基于克鲁斯卡尔树定理的快速增长函数。

ACHIEVE.en: To succeed in something, now especially in academic performance.
ACHIEVE.zh: 在某件事上取得成功，现在尤其是在学业成绩方面。

DRESS.en: An item of clothing (usually worn by a woman or young girl) which both covers the upper part of the body and includes skirts below the waist.
DRESS.zh: 一种衣服（通常由妇女或年轻女孩穿着），既覆盖上半身又包括腰部以下的裙子。

DEALER.en: One who deals in goods, especially automobiles; a middleman.
DEALER.zh: 从事货物贸易，尤其是汽车贸易的；一个中间人。

SKY.en: The atmosphere above a given point, especially as visible from the ground during the day.
SKY.zh: 给定点上方的大气，尤其是白天从地面可见的大气。

ROM.en: (of type) upright, as opposed to italic

CARRIED.en: To lift (something) and take it to another place; to transport (something) by lifting.
CARRIED.zh: 举起（某物）并将其带到另一个地方；通过提升来运输（某物）。

EXPOSURE.en: The condition of being exposed, uncovered, or unprotected.
EXPOSURE.zh: 暴露、未覆盖或未受保护的状况。

HIDE.en: To put (something) in a place where it will be harder to discover or out of sight.
HIDE.zh: 将（某物）放置在较难发现或看不见的地方。

GAMBLING.en: To take a risk, with the potential of a positive outcome.
GAMBLING.zh: 承担风险，并有可能获得积极结果。

MILLER.en: A person who owns or operates a mill, especially a flour mill.
MILLER.zh: 拥有或经营工厂（尤其是面粉厂）的人。

OUTDOORS.en: (often preceded by "the") The environment outside of enclosed structures.
OUTDOORS.zh: （通常前面带有“the”）封闭结构之外的环境。

CLOTHES.en: A woven fabric such as used in dressing, decorating, cleaning or other practical use.
CLOTHES.zh: 用于穿着、装饰、清洁或其他实际用途的机织织物。

CAUSED.en: To set off an event or action.

BABES.en: A baby or infant; a very young human or animal.
BABES.zh: 婴儿或婴儿；非常年轻的人类或动物。

FRAMES.en: The structural elements of a building or other constructed object.
FRAMES.zh: 建筑物或其他建筑物体的结构元件。

TOY.en: Something to play with, especially as intended for use by a child.
TOY.zh: 可以玩的东西，尤其是供儿童使用的东西。

LAYER.en: A single thickness of some material covering a surface.
LAYER.zh: 覆盖表面的某种材料的单一厚度。

PRINTED.en: To produce one or more copies of a text or image on a surface, especially by machine; often used with out or off: print out, print off.
PRINTED.zh: 在表面上制作一份或多份文本或图像副本，尤其是通过机器；常与out或off连用：打印输出、打印关闭。

SLOW.zh: 行动迟缓的人；一个懒鬼。

REMOVAL.en: The process of moving, or the fact of being removed.
REMOVAL.zh: 移动的过程，或者被移除的事实。

HIP.en: The outward-projecting parts of the pelvis and top of the femur and the overlying tissue.
HIP.zh: 骨盆和股骨顶部以及上面的组织向外突出的部分。

FAQS.en: A list of questions said to be frequently asked, and their answers.
FAQS.zh: 据说经常被问到的问题及其答案的列表。

ADDING.en: To join or unite (e.g. one thing to another, or as several particulars) so as to increase the number, augment the quantity or enlarge the magnitude, or so as to form into one aggregate.
ADDING.zh: 连接或联合（例如，一件事与另一件事，或作为几个细节），以增加数量，扩大数量或扩大规模，或形成一个聚合体。

MOSTLY.en: Mainly or chiefly; for the most part; usually, generally, on the whole.
MOSTLY.zh: 主要或主要地；大部分情况下；通常，通常，总的来说。

SPOT.en: A round or irregular patch on the surface of a thing having a different color, texture etc. and generally round in shape.
SPOT.zh: 物体表面上的圆形或不规则斑块，具有不同的颜色、纹理等，通常呈圆形。

PRINTS.en: Books and other material created by printing presses, considered collectively or as a medium.
PRINTS.zh: 由印刷机制作的书籍和其他材料，统称为或作为媒介。

SPEND.en: Amount of money spent (during a period); expenditure.
SPEND.zh: 花费的金额（在一段时间内）；支出。

FACTORY.en: A trading establishment, especially set up by merchants working in a foreign country.
FACTORY.zh: 贸易机构，特别是由在外国工作的商人设立的。

INTERIOR.en: The inside of a building, container, cavern, or other enclosed structure.
INTERIOR.zh: 建筑物、容器、洞穴或其他封闭结构的内部。

REVISED.en: To look at again, to reflect on.

GROW.en: To become larger, to increase in magnitude.

OPTICAL.en: Of, or relating to sight; visual.
OPTICAL.zh: Of, or relating to sight;视觉的。

RELATIVE.en: Someone in the same family; someone connected by blood, marriage, or adoption.
RELATIVE.zh: 同一个家庭中的某个人；因血缘、婚姻或收养而有联系的人。

AMAZING.en: To fill with wonder and surprise; to astonish, astound, surprise or perplex.
AMAZING.zh: 充满惊奇和惊喜；使惊讶、惊讶、惊讶或困惑。

CLOCK.en: An instrument used to measure or keep track of time; a non-portable timepiece.
CLOCK.zh: 用于测量或记录时间的仪器；非便携式计时器。

SUITES.en: A retinue or company of attendants, as of a distinguished personage
SUITES.zh: 显赫人物的随从或随行人员

FEELING.en: (heading) To use or experience the sense of touch.

HIDDEN.en: Located or positioned out of sight; not visually apparent.
HIDDEN.zh: 位于或位于视线之外；视觉上不明显。

VICTORIA.en: A kind of low four-wheeled pleasure carriage, with a calash top, designed for two persons and the driver who occupies a high seat in front.
VICTORIA.zh: 一种低矮的四轮游乐马车，带有轿顶，专为两人和坐在前面高位的司机而设计。

SERIAL.en: A work, such as a work of fiction, published in installments, often numbered and without a specified end.
SERIAL.zh: 分期出版的作品，例如小说作品，通常有编号且没有指定的结尾。

RELIEF.en: The removal of stress or discomfort.

RATIO.en: A number representing a comparison between two named things.
RATIO.zh: 表示两个命名事物之间比较的数字。

RAIN.en: Condensed water falling from a cloud.

ONTO.en: (of a function) Assuming each of the values in its codomain; having its range equal to its codomain.
ONTO.zh: （函数的）假设其共域中的每个值；其范围等于其密码域。

COPIES.en: The result of copying; an identical duplicate of an original.
COPIES.zh: 复制的结果；与原件完全相同的副本。

SEEING.en: (stative) To perceive or detect with the eyes, or as if by sight.
SEEING.zh: （静态）用眼睛或仿佛通过视觉来感知或检测。

PROOF.en: An effort, process, or operation designed to establish or discover a fact or truth; an act of testing; a test; a trial.
PROOF.zh: 旨在建立或发现事实或真理的努力、过程或操作；测试行为；测试；一次审判。

DNA.en: The part of a living being that carries genetic information.
DNA.zh: 生物体内携带遗传信息的部分。

DIFF.en: Any program which compares two files or sets of files and outputs a description of the __erences between them.
DIFF.zh: 比较两个文件或文件集并输出它们之间差异的描述的任何程序。

TENNIS.en: A sport played by two players (or four in doubles), who alternately strike the ball over a net using racquets.
TENNIS.zh: 由两名球员（或双打四名球员）进行的一项运动，他们交替使用球拍将球击过网。

BASS.en: A low spectrum of sound tones.

BEDROOM.en: A room in a house where a bed is kept for sleeping.
BEDROOM.zh: 房子里的一个房间，里面有一张床供睡觉。

EMPTY.en: (usually plural) A container, especially a bottle, whose contents have been used up, leaving it __.
EMPTY.zh: （通常是复数）容器，尤其是瓶子，其内容物已用完，空了。

INSTANCE.en: Urgency of manner or words; an urgent request; insistence.
INSTANCE.zh: 方式或言语的紧迫性；紧急请求；坚持。

HOLE.en: A hollow place or cavity; an excavation; a pit; an opening in or through a solid body, a fabric, etc.; a perforation; a rent; a fissure.
HOLE.zh: 中空的地方或空腔；挖掘；一个坑；固体、织物等中或穿过固体、织物等的开口；穿孔；租金；一条裂缝。

PETS.en: An animal kept as a companion.

LICENSED.en: To give a formal (usually written) authorization.
LICENSED.zh: 给予正式（通常是书面）授权。

BUREAU.en: An administrative unit of government; office.

PAIR.en: Two similar or identical things taken together; often followed by of.
PAIR.zh: 两个相似或相同的事物放在一起；后面经常跟着 of。

IDEAL.en: A perfect standard of beauty, intellect etc., or a standard of excellence to aim at.
IDEAL.zh: 美丽、智力等的完美标准，或者追求的卓越标准。

SPECS.en: Two similar or identical things taken together; often followed by of.
SPECS.zh: 两个相似或相同的事物放在一起；后面经常跟着 of。

RECORDED.en: To make a record of information.

DON.en: A university professor, particularly one at Oxford or Cambridge.
DON.zh: 大学教授，尤其是牛津大学或剑桥大学的教授。

PIECES.en: A part of a larger whole, usually in such a form that it is able to be separated from other parts.
PIECES.zh: 较大整体的一部分，通常以能够与其他部分分离的形式存在。

PARKS.en: An area of land set aside for environment preservation or recreation.
PARKS.zh: 为环境保护或娱乐而预留的土地区域。

LAWYERS.en: A professional person qualified (as by a law degree or bar exam) and authorized to practice law, i.e. represent parties in lawsuits or trials and give legal advice.
LAWYERS.zh: 具有资格（如通过法律学位或律师考试）并有权执业的专业人士，即在诉讼或审判中代表当事人并提供法律建议。

CREAM.en: The butterfat/milkfat part of milk which rises to the top; this part when separated from the remainder.
CREAM.zh: 牛奶中升到顶部的乳脂/乳脂部分；这部分与其余部分分开时。

RUNS.en: Act or instance of running, of moving rapidly using the feet.
RUNS.zh: 跑步、用脚快速移动的动作或实例。

TRENDS.en: An inclination in a particular direction.

BOXES.en: Senses relating to a three-dimensional object or space.
BOXES.zh: 与三维物体或空间相关的感觉。

HILLS.en: An elevated location smaller than a mountain.

FOURTH.en: (not used in the plural) The person or thing in the __ position.
FOURTH.zh: （不用于复数）第四个位置的人或物。

EVIL.en: Moral badness; wickedness; malevolence; the forces or behaviors that are the opposite or enemy of good.
EVIL.zh: 道德败坏；邪恶；恶意;与善相反或敌人的力量或行为。

AWARE.en: Vigilant or on one's guard against danger or difficulty.
AWARE.zh: 警惕或警惕危险或困难。

SHAPE.en: The status or condition of something

GREATEST.en: Relatively large in scale, size, extent, number (i.e. having many parts or members) or duration (i.e. relatively long); very big.
GREATEST.zh: 规模、大小、范围、数量（即具有许多部分或成员）或持续时间（即相对较长）相对较大；很大。

FIRMS.en: A business partnership; the name under which it trades.
FIRMS.zh: 商业伙伴关系；其交易名称。

EURO.zh: 居住在欧洲或来自欧洲的人

GENERIC.en: A product sold under a __ name.
GENERIC.zh: 以通用名称销售的产品。

USAGE.en: The manner or the amount of using; use.

CAP.en: A close-fitting hat, either brimless or peaked.
CAP.zh: 一种贴身的帽子，无檐或有檐。

INK.en: A pigment (or dye)-based fluid used for writing, printing etc.
INK.zh: 用于书写、印刷等的基于颜料（或染料）的液体。

CENSUS.en: An official count or enumeration of members of a population (not necessarily human), usually residents or citizens in a particular region, often done at regular intervals.
CENSUS.zh: 对人口成员（不一定是人类）（通常是特定地区的居民或公民）进行的官方统计或计数，通常定期进行。

PEAK.en: A point; the sharp end or top of anything that terminates in a point; as, the __, or front, of a cap.
PEAK.zh: 一点；任何终止于点的尖端或顶部；如帽子的顶部或前部。

EXIST.en: (stative) to be; have __ence; have being or reality

WHEEL.en: A circular device capable of rotating on its axis, facilitating movement or transportation or performing labour in machines.
WHEEL.zh: 能够绕其轴旋转的圆形装置，便于移动或运输或在机器中执行劳动。

TRANSIT.en: The act of passing over, across, or through something.
TRANSIT.zh: 越过、跨过或穿过某物的行为。

SALT.en: A common substance, chemically consisting mainly of sodium chloride (NaCl), used extensively as a condiment and preservative.
SALT.zh: 一种常见物质，化学成分主要为氯化钠 (NaCl)，广泛用作调味品和防腐剂。

POETRY.en: Literature composed in verse or language exhibiting conscious attention to patterns and rhythm.
POETRY.zh: 用诗歌或语言创作的文学，表现出对模式和节奏的有意识的关注。

LIGHTS.en: Visible electromagnetic radiation. The human eye can typically detect radiation (light) in the wavelength range of about 400 to 750 nanometers. Nearby shorter and longer wavelength ranges, although not visible, are commonly called ultraviolet and infrared light.
LIGHTS.zh: 可见电磁辐射。人眼通常可以检测到波长范围约为 400 至 750 纳米的辐射（光）。附近较短和较长的波长范围虽然不可见，但通常称为紫外线和红外线。

TRACKING.zh: 随着时间的推移继续进行。

ANGEL.en: An incorporeal and sometimes divine messenger from a deity, or other divine entity, often depicted in art as a youthful winged figure in flowing robes.
ANGEL.zh: 来自神灵或其他神圣实体的无形的、有时是神圣的使者，在艺术中经常被描绘成穿着飘逸长袍的年轻有翼人物。

BELL.en: A percussive instrument made of metal or other hard material, typically but not always in the shape of an inverted cup with a flared rim, which resonates when struck.
BELL.zh: 由金属或其他硬质材料制成的打击乐器，通常但不总是呈倒置杯子形状，边缘呈喇叭形，敲击时会产生共鸣。

KEEPING.en: To continue in (a course or mode of action); not to intermit or fall from; to uphold or maintain.
KEEPING.zh: 继续（行动方针或模式）；不要中断或跌倒；坚持或维持。

ATTEMPT.en: The action of trying at something.

MATCHES.en: A competitive sporting event such as a boxing meet, a baseball game, or a cricket match.
MATCHES.zh: 竞技性体育赛事，例如拳击比赛、棒球比赛或板球比赛。

NOISE.en: Various sounds, usually unwanted or unpleasant.
NOISE.zh: 各种声音，通常是不想要的或令人不愉快的。

ENGINES.en: A large construction used in warfare, such as a battering ram, catapult etc.
ENGINES.zh: 战争中使用的大型建筑，如攻城锤、弹射器等。

PIN.en: A needle without an eye (usually) made of drawn-out steel wire with one end sharpened and the other flattened or rounded into a head, used for fastening.
PIN.zh: 一种没有眼的针（通常），由拉出的钢丝制成，一端削尖，另一端压平或磨成圆头，用于紧固。

ALCOHOL.en: Any of a class of organic compounds (such as ethanol) containing a hydroxyl functional group (-OH).
ALCOHOL.zh: 任何一类含有羟基官能团 (-OH) 的有机化合物（例如乙醇）。

GREEK.en: An inhabitant, resident, or person of descent from Greece.
GREEK.zh: 来自希腊的居民、居民或后裔。

MANAGING.en: To direct or be in charge of.

SISTER.en: A daughter of the same parents as another person; a female sibling.
SISTER.zh: 与他人同父母的女儿；一个女性兄弟姐妹。

RAW.en: (sugar refining, sugar trade) An unprocessed sugar; a batch of such.
RAW.zh: （糖精炼、糖贸易）未加工的糖；一批这样的。

WALKING.en: To move on the feet by alternately setting each foot (or pair or group of feet, in the case of animals with four or more feet) forward, with at least one foot on the ground at all times. Compare run.
WALKING.zh: 通过交替地将每只脚（或一对或一组脚，如果是有四只或更多脚的动物）向前移动，至少一只脚始终踩在地面上。比较跑。

EXPLAIN.en: To make plain, manifest, or intelligible; to clear of obscurity; to illustrate the meaning of.
EXPLAIN.zh: 使明白、明显或易于理解；消除晦涩难懂；来说明其含义。

SMALLER.en: Not large or big; insignificant; few in number.
SMALLER.zh: 不大不小；微不足道;数量很少。

GNU.en: A large antelope of the genus Connochaetes, native to Africa, having curved horns.
GNU.zh: 羚羊属的一种大羚羊，原产于非洲，有弯曲的角。

EXTENT.en: A range of values or locations.

SHARP.en: The symbol ♯, placed after the name of a note in the key signature or before a note on the staff to indicate that the note is to be played a semitone higher.
SHARP.zh: 符号 ♯ 放置在调号中的音符名称之后或五线谱上的音符之前，表示该音符要演奏高半音。

LESBIANS.en: A homosexual woman, one who is mostly or exclusively sexually or romantically attracted to other women.
LESBIANS.zh: 同性恋女性，主要或完全被其他女性性或浪漫吸引的女性。

LANE.en: (used in street names) A road, street, or similar thoroughfare.
LANE.zh: （用于街道名称）道路、街道或类似的通道。

MANAGERS.en: A person whose job is to manage something, such as a business, a restaurant, or a sports team.
MANAGERS.zh: 负责管理某事的人，例如企业、餐馆或运动队。

AIRCRAFT.en: A vehicle capable of atmospheric flight due to interaction with the air, such as buoyancy or lift
AIRCRAFT.zh: 由于与空气的相互作用（例如浮力或升力）而能够在大气层中飞行的飞行器

MODULES.en: A self-contained component of a system, often interchangeable, which has a well-defined interface to the other components.
MODULES.zh: 系统的独立组件，通常可以互换，具有与其他组件明确定义的接口。

VERSIONS.en: A specific form or variation of something.
VERSIONS.zh: 某物的特定形式或变体。

EMPLOYER.en: A person, firm or other entity which pays for or hires the services of another person.
EMPLOYER.zh: 支付或雇用他人服务的个人、公司或其他实体。

CITIZENS.en: A resident of a city or town, especially one with legally-recognized rights or duties.
CITIZENS.zh: 城市或城镇的居民，尤其是具有法律承认的权利或义务的居民。

COACH.en: A wheeled vehicle, generally drawn by horse power.
COACH.zh: 一种轮式车辆，通常由马力牵引。

ASSIGNED.en: To designate or set apart something for some purpose.
ASSIGNED.zh: 为某种目的指定或分开某物。

AGES.en: The whole duration of a being, whether animal, plant, or other kind, being alive.
AGES.zh: 一个生物（无论是动物、植物还是其他物种）活着的整个持续时间。

PLUG.en: A pronged connecting device which fits into a mating socket, especially an electrical one.
PLUG.zh: 一种插入配合插座（尤其是电气插座）的插脚连接装置。

VIRGIN.en: A person who has never had sexual intercourse, or sometimes, one who has never engaged in any sexual activity at all.
VIRGIN.zh: 从未发生过性行为的人，或者有时根本没有进行过任何性活动的人。

RAISED.en: (physical) To cause to rise; to lift or elevate.
RAISED.zh: （身体上的）引起上升；举起或举起。

HAT.en: A covering for the head, often in the approximate form of a cone or a cylinder closed at its top end, and sometimes having a brim and other decoration.
HAT.zh: 头部的覆盖物，通常呈顶端封闭的圆锥体或圆柱体的近似形状，有时具有边缘和其他装饰。

DEALERS.en: One who deals in goods, especially automobiles; a middleman.
DEALERS.zh: 从事货物贸易，尤其是汽车贸易的；一个中间人。

HELPING.en: To provide assistance to (someone or something).
HELPING.zh: 向（某人或某事）提供帮助。

BIKE.en: A vehicle that has two wheels, one behind the other, a steering handle, and a saddle seat or seats and is usually propelled by the action of a rider’s feet upon pedals.
BIKE.zh: 一种车辆，有两个轮子，一个在另一个轮子后面，一个转向手柄，一个或多个马鞍座，通常通过骑车人的脚踩踏板来推动。

TOTALLY.en: To the fullest extent or degree.
TOTALLY.zh: 达到最大的范围或程度。

PLATE.en: A slightly curved but almost flat dish from which food is served or eaten.
PLATE.zh: 稍微弯曲但几乎平坦的盘子，用于盛放或食用食物。

EXPENSES.en: A spending or consuming, often a disbursement of funds.
EXPENSES.zh: 支出或消费，通常是资金的支出。

BLONDE.en: A pale yellowish (golden brown) color, especially said of hair color.
BLONDE.zh: 淡黄色（金棕色）颜色，尤其是头发颜色。

DER.en: Disdainful indication that something is obvious.
DER.zh: 轻蔑地表明某事是显而易见的。

LOSE.en: To cause (something) to cease to be in one's possession or capability due to unfortunate or unknown circumstances, events or reasons.
LOSE.zh: 由于不幸或未知的情况、事件或原因，导致某人不再拥有或无法拥有（某物）。

SEEK.en: The operation of navigating through a stream.

ALBUMS.en: A book specially designed to keep photographs, stamps, or autographs.
ALBUMS.zh: 专为保存照片、邮票或亲笔签名而设计的书。

CHEATS.en: To violate rules in order to gain advantage from a situation.
CHEATS.zh: 为了从某种情况中获得利益而违反规则。

GUESTS.en: A recipient of hospitality, specifically someone staying by invitation at the house of another.
GUESTS.zh: 受款待者，特指受邀请住在他人家中的人。

HOSTED.en: To perform the role of a host.

DISEASES.en: An abnormal condition of a human, animal or plant that causes discomfort or dysfunction; distinct from injury insofar as the latter is usually instantaneously acquired.
DISEASES.zh: 导致不适或功能障碍的人类、动物或植物的异常状况；与伤害不同，后者通常是瞬时获得的。

KITS.en: A circular wooden vessel, made of hooped staves.
KITS.zh: 一种圆形木器，由箍筋制成。

TRACKS.en: A mark left by something that has passed along.
TRACKS.zh: 已经过去的事物留下的痕迹。

CAM.en: A turning or sliding piece which imparts motion to a rod, lever or block brought into sliding or rolling contact with it.
CAM.zh: 一种转动或滑动件，使与之滑动或滚动接触的杆、杠杆或块体运动。

LOGIC.en: A method of human thought that involves thinking in a linear, step-by-step manner about how a problem can be solved. __ is the basis of many principles including the scientific method.
LOGIC.zh: 一种人类思维方法，涉及以线性、逐步的方式思考如何解决问题。逻辑是包括科学方法在内的许多原则的基础。

TEMPLATE.en: A physical object whose shape is used as a guide to make other objects.
TEMPLATE.zh: 一种物理物体，其形状可用作制作其他物体的指导。

PRINCE.en: A (male) ruler, a sovereign; a king, monarch.

SOIL.en: A mixture of mineral particles and organic material, used to support plant growth.
SOIL.zh: 矿物颗粒和有机材料的混合物，用于支持植物生长。

GRANTS.en: The act of granting; a bestowing or conferring; concession; allowance; permission.
GRANTS.zh: 授予行为；授予或授予；让步;津贴;允许。

LEAVING.en: To have a consequence or remnant.

WILDLIFE.en: Animals, plants, and fungi, not normally domesticated, often to the exclusion of plants, fungi, fish, insects and other invertebrates, and microscopic plants and animals; hence:
WILDLIFE.zh: 通常不驯化的动物、植物和真菌，通常不包括植物、真菌、鱼类、昆虫和其他无脊椎动物，以及微观植物和动物；因此：

MATT.en: (coppersmithing) An alloy of copper, tin, iron, etc.; white metal.
MATT.zh: （铜加工）铜、锡、铁等的合金；白色金属。

COOKING.en: To prepare (food) for eating by heating it, often by combining it with other ingredients.
COOKING.zh: 通过加热（通常与其他成分混合）来准备（食物）供食用。

SPONSORS.en: A person or organisation with some sort of responsibility for another person or organisation, especially where the responsibility has a religious, legal, or financial aspect.
SPONSORS.zh: 对另一个人或组织负有某种责任的个人或组织，尤其是当责任涉及宗教、法律或财务方面时。

FOX.en: A red __, small carnivore (Vulpes vulpes), related to dogs and wolves, with red or silver fur and a bushy tail.
FOX.zh: 红狐，小型食肉动物（Vulpes vulpes），与狗和狼有亲缘关系，有红色或银色的皮毛和浓密的尾巴。

SIZES.zh: （在方言之外已废弃）巡回法庭。

EXIT.en: An act of going out or going away, or leaving; a departure.
EXIT.zh: 外出或走开或离开的行为；一次出发。

ENTERED.en: To go or come into an enclosed or partially enclosed space.
ENTERED.zh: 进入或进入封闭或部分封闭的空间。

ARM.en: The portion of the upper human appendage, from the shoulder to the wrist and sometimes including the hand.
ARM.zh: 人类上肢的部分，从肩膀到手腕，有时包括手。

KEYS.en: An object designed to open and close a lock.
KEYS.zh: 设计用于打开和关闭锁的对象。

WAVE.en: To move back and forth repeatedly and somewhat loosely.
WAVE.zh: 反复地、稍微宽松地来回移动。

HOLY.en: A thing that is extremely __; used almost exclusively in __ of Holies.
HOLY.zh: 极其神圣的东西；几乎专门用于至圣所。

MESH.en: A structure made of connected strands of metal, fiber, or other flexible/ductile material, with evenly spaced openings between them.
MESH.zh: 由连接的金属、纤维或其他柔性/延展材料的股线制成的结构，它们之间具有均匀间隔的开口。

TRAIL.en: The track or indication marking the route followed by something that has passed, such as the footprints of animal on land or the con__ of an airplane in the sky.
TRAIL.zh: 标记经过的物体所遵循的路线的轨迹或指示，例如动物在陆地上的脚印或飞机在天空中的轨迹。

OBSERVED.en: To notice or view, especially carefully or with attention to detail.
OBSERVED.zh: 注意到或观察，特别仔细或注意细节。

DEAN.en: A senior official in a college or university, who may be in charge of a division or faculty (for example, the __ of science) or have some other advisory or disciplinary function (for example, the __ of students).
DEAN.zh: 学院或大学的高级官员，可能负责部门或教员（例如理学院院长）或具有其他咨询或纪律职能（例如学生主任）。

SETUP.en: Equipment designed for a particular purpose; an apparatus.
SETUP.zh: 为特定目的而设计的设备；一个装置。

POLL.en: A survey of people, usually statistically analyzed to gauge wider public opinion.
POLL.zh: 对人们的调查，通常进行统计分析以衡量更广泛的公众意见。

BOOKING.zh: 保留（某物）以供将来使用。

GLOSSARY.en: A list of terms in a particular domain of knowledge with their definitions.
GLOSSARY.zh: 特定知识领域的术语及其定义的列表。

FISCAL.en: A public official in certain countries having control of public revenue.
FISCAL.zh: 某些国家控制公共收入的公职人员。

STYLES.en: Senses relating to a thin, pointed object.
STYLES.zh: 与薄而尖的物体有关的感觉。

UNIX.zh: 任何类 __ 操作系统，包括 __。

FILLED.en: To occupy fully, to take up all of.

BOND.en: Evidence of a long-term debt, by which the __ issuer (the borrower) is obliged to pay interest when due, and repay the principal at maturity, as specified on the face of the __ certificate. The rights of the holder are specified in the __ indenture, which contains the legal terms and conditions under which the __ was issued. __s are available in two forms: registered __s, and bearer __s.
BOND.zh: 债券发行人（借款人）有义务在到期时支付利息并在到期时偿还本金的长期债务的证据，如债券凭证表面所示。债券契约中规定了持有人的权利，其中包含发行债券的法律条款和条件。债券有两种形式：记名债券和不记名债券。

CHANNELS.en: The physical confine of a river or slough, consisting of a bed and banks.
CHANNELS.zh: 河流或泥沼的物理范围，由河床和河岸组成。

APPENDIX.en: Something attached to something else; an attachment or accompaniment.
APPENDIX.zh: 某物依附于另一物；附件或伴奏。

BLUES.en: The colour of the clear sky or the deep sea, between green and violet in the visible spectrum, and one of the primary additive colours for transmitted light; the colour obtained by subtracting red and green from white light using magenta and cyan filters; or any colour resembling this.
BLUES.zh: 晴空或深海的颜色，可见光谱中的绿色和紫色之间，是透射光的主要加色之一；使用品红色和青色滤镜从白光中减去红色和绿色获得的颜色；或任何类似的颜色。

PUB.en: A __lic house where beverages, primarily alcoholic, may be bought and consumed, also providing food and sometimes entertainment such as live music or television.
PUB.zh: 可以购买和消费饮料（主要是酒精）的酒馆，也提供食物，有时还提供现场音乐或电视等娱乐活动。

SCOPE.en: The breadth, depth or reach of a subject; a domain.
SCOPE.zh: 主题的广度、深度或范围；一个域。

CABLES.en: (material) A long object used to make a physical connection.
CABLES.zh: （材料）用于建立物理连接的长物体。

BIOLOGY.en: The study of all life or living matter.
BIOLOGY.zh: 对所有生命或有生命物质的研究。

DENTAL.en: Cleaning and polishing of an animal's teeth.
DENTAL.zh: 清洁和抛光动物的牙齿。

KILLED.en: To put to death; to extinguish the life of.

ANCIENT.en: A person who is very old.

DEBATE.en: An argument, or discussion, usually in an ordered or formal setting, often with more than two people, generally ending with a vote or other decision.
DEBATE.zh: 通常在有序或正式的场合进行的争论或讨论，通常有两个以上的人参与，通常以投票或其他决定结束。

CAUSES.en: (often with of, typically of adverse results) The source of, or reason for, an event or action; that which produces or effects a result.
CAUSES.zh: （通常与 of，通常是不利结果）事件或行动的来源或原因；产生或影响结果的事物。

LEISURE.en: Freedom provided by the cessation of activities.
LEISURE.zh: 停止活动所提供的自由。

LEARNED.en: Having much learning, knowledgeable, erudite; highly educated.
LEARNED.zh: 博学多才，学识渊博，博学多才；受过高等教育。

HISTORIC.en: A history, a non-fiction account of the past.
HISTORIC.zh: 一部历史，一部对过去的非小说类叙述。

ATTACHED.en: To fasten, to join to (literally and figuratively).
ATTACHED.zh: 紧固、连接（字面意义和象征意义）。

OPENED.en: To make something accessible or allow for passage by moving from a shut position.
OPENED.zh: 通过从关闭位置移动来使某物可接近或允许通过。

HUSBAND.en: The master of a house; the head of a family; a householder.
HUSBAND.zh: 一家之主；一家之主；一个户主。

DISABLED.en: To render unable; to take away an ability of, as by crippling.
DISABLED.zh: 使无法；剥夺……的能力，如削弱。

CRAZY.en: An insane or eccentric person; a crackpot.
CRAZY.zh: 疯狂或古怪的人；一个疯子。

CONCERT.en: Agreement in a design or plan; union formed by mutual communication of opinions and views; accordance in a scheme; harmony; simultaneous action.
CONCERT.zh: 设计或计划协议；相互交流意见和看法而形成的联盟；按照计划；和谐;同时动作。

SCORES.en: The total number of goals, points, runs, etc. earned by a participant in a game.
SCORES.zh: 参与者在一场比赛中获得的进球、得分、跑动等的总数。

COMEDY.en: A choric song of celebration or revel, especially in Ancient Greece.
COMEDY.zh: 庆祝或狂欢的合唱歌曲，尤其是在古希腊。

ADOPTED.en: To take by choice into relationship (a child, heir, friend, citizen, etc.)
ADOPTED.zh: 选择建立关系（孩子、继承人、朋友、公民等）

BEARS.en: A large omnivorous mammal, related to the dog and raccoon, having shaggy hair, a very small tail, and flat feet; a member of family Ursidae.
BEARS.zh: 一种大型杂食性哺乳动物，与狗和浣熊有关，具有蓬松的毛发、非常小的尾巴和扁平足；熊科的成员。

CARRIER.en: A person or object that carries someone or something else.
CARRIER.zh: 携带某人或某物的人或物体。

EDITED.en: To change a text, or a document.

VISA.en: A permit to enter and leave a country, normally issued by the authorities of the country to be visited.
VISA.zh: 进入和离开一个国家的许可证，通常由要访问的国家当局签发。

MOUTH.en: The opening of a creature through which food is ingested.
MOUTH.zh: 生物的开口，通过它摄取食物。

LINKED.en: To connect two or more things.

CONCEPTS.en: An abstract and general idea; an abstraction.
CONCEPTS.zh: 抽象和一般的想法；一个抽象。

GUN.en: A device for projecting a hard object very forcefully; a firearm or cannon.
GUN.zh: 一种用于非常有力地投射硬物的装置；枪支或大炮。

PURE.en: One who, or that which, is __.
PURE.zh: 一个人，或者说那个人，是纯洁的。

LESSONS.en: A section of learning or teaching into which a wider learning content is divided.
LESSONS.zh: 学习或教学的一个部分，其中划分了更广泛的学习内容。

FRUIT.en: (often in the plural) In general, a product of plant growth useful to man or animals.
FRUIT.zh: （通常为复数）一般来说，对人类或动物有用的植物生长产物。

BEGINS.en: To start, to initiate or take the first step into something.
BEGINS.zh: 开始、开始或迈出某事的第一步。

LENS.en: An object, usually made of glass, that focuses or defocuses the light that passes through it.
LENS.zh: 通常由玻璃制成的物体，可以对穿过它的光进行聚焦或散焦。

TREATED.en: To negotiate, discuss terms, bargain (for or with).
TREATED.zh: 谈判、讨论条款、讨价还价（为或与）。

DRAW.en: The result of a contest that neither side has won; a tie.
DRAW.zh: 双方均未获胜的比赛结果；领带。

RELATING.en: To tell in a descriptive way.

WARM.en: Having a temperature slightly higher than usual, but still pleasant; mildly hot.
WARM.zh: 气温比平时稍高，但仍宜人；微热。

LEWIS.en: A cramp iron inserted into a cavity in order to lift heavy stones; used as a symbol of strength in Freemasonry.
LEWIS.zh: 插入空腔以举起重石的夹铁；在共济会中用作力量的象征。

OFFLINE.en: To take (a system, etc.) __; to demote from an active or online state.
OFFLINE.zh: 使（系统等）离线；从活动或在线状态降级。

LEAVES.en: The usually green and flat organ that represents the most prominent feature of most vegetative plants.
LEAVES.zh: 通常是绿色且扁平的器官，代表大多数营养植物最显着的特征。

BABE.en: A baby or infant; a very young human or animal.
BABE.zh: 婴儿或婴儿；非常年轻的人类或动物。

CHECKS.en: A situation in which the king is directly threatened by an opposing piece.
CHECKS.zh: 国王受到对方棋子直接威胁的情况。

REACHED.en: To extend, stretch, or thrust out (for example a limb or object held in the hand).
REACHED.zh: 延伸、伸展或伸出（例如手中握着的肢体或物体）。

SAFARI.en: A trip into any undeveloped area to see, photograph or hunt wild animals in their own environment.
SAFARI.zh: 前往任何未开发地区，在野生动物的环境中观看、拍摄或狩猎它们。

SUGAR.en: Sucrose in the form of small crystals, obtained from __ cane or __ beet and used to sweeten food and drink.
SUGAR.zh: 小晶体形式的蔗糖，从甘蔗或甜菜中提取，用于使食物和饮料变甜。

CREW.en: To make the shrill sound characteristic of a rooster; to make a sound in this manner, either in gaiety, joy, pleasure, or defiance.
CREW.zh: 发出公鸡特有的尖锐声音；以这种方式发出声音，无论是欢快、快乐、愉快还是蔑视。

LEGS.en: A limb or appendage that an animal uses for support or locomotion.
LEGS.zh: 动物用来支撑或运动的肢体或附属物。

STICK.en: An elongated piece of wood or similar material, typically put to some use, for example as a wand or baton.
STICK.zh: 细长的木头或类似材料，通常有某种用途，例如用作魔杖或警棍。

RELATION.en: The manner in which two things may be associated.
RELATION.zh: 两个事物可能关联的方式。

ENABLED.en: To make somebody able (to do, or to be, something); to give sufficient ability or power to do or to be; to give strength or ability to.
ENABLED.zh: 使某人能够（做某事或成为某事）；给予足够的能力或权力去做或成为；给予力量或能力。

GENRE.en: A kind; a stylistic category or sort, especially of literature or other artworks.
GENRE.zh: 一种；一种文体类别或类别，尤其是文学或其他艺术品的文体类别或类别。

SLIDE.en: An item of play equipment that children can climb up and then __ down again.
SLIDE.zh: 儿童可以爬上去然后再滑下来的游乐设施。

REAR.en: To bring up to maturity, as offspring; to educate; to instruct; to foster.
REAR.zh: 作为后代，抚养成熟；教育；指示；培养。

EXACT.en: To demand and enforce the payment or performance of, sometimes in a forcible or imperious way.
EXACT.zh: 有时以强制或专横的方式要求并强制付款或履行。

BOUND.en: To tie; to confine by any ligature.
BOUND.zh: 打结；通过任何结扎来限制。

ADAPTER.en: One who is capable of adapting to differing situations.
ADAPTER.zh: 一个能够适应不同情况的人。

NODE.en: A knot, knob, protuberance or swelling.

LOCK.en: Something used for fastening, which can only be opened with a key or combination.
LOCK.zh: 用于紧固的东西，只能用钥匙或组合打开。

HOCKEY.en: Ice __, a game on ice in which two teams of six players skate and try to score by shooting a puck into the opposing team's net, using their sticks.
HOCKEY.zh: 冰球是一种冰上运动，由六名球员组成的两队滑行，并尝试用球杆将冰球射入对方球网以得分。

STORM.en: Any disturbed state of the atmosphere, especially as affecting the earth's surface, and strongly implying destructive or unpleasant weather.
STORM.zh: 大气层的任何扰动状态，尤其是影响地球表面的，并强烈暗示破坏性或令人不愉快的天气。

COLLEGES.en: A corporate group; a group of colleagues.

MILE.en: The international __: a unit of length precisely equal to 1.609344 kilometers established by treaty among Anglophone nations in 1959, divided into 5,280 feet or 1,760 yards.
MILE.zh: 国际英里：英语国家于 1959 年通过条约建立的精确等于 1.609344 公里的长度单位，分为 5,280 英尺或 1,760 码。

SHOWED.en: To display, to have somebody see (something).

EDITORS.en: A person who edits or makes changes to documents.

THREADS.en: A long, thin and flexible form of material, generally with a round cross-section, used in sewing, weaving or in the construction of string.
THREADS.zh: 一种长、薄且柔韧的材料，通常具有圆形横截面，用于缝纫、编织或绳结构。

BOWL.en: A roughly hemispherical container used to hold, mix or present food, such as salad, fruit or soup, or other items.
BOWL.zh: 一种大致半球形的容器，用于盛装、混合或呈现食物，例如沙拉、水果或汤或其他物品。

BROTHERS.en: Son of the same parents as another person.
BROTHERS.zh: 与另一个人同父母的儿子。

PRESENTS.en: The current moment or period of time.

TANK.en: A closed container for liquids or gases.
TANK.zh: 盛装液体或气体的密闭容器。

DOLLS.en: A toy in the form of a human.

NAVY.en: A country's entire sea force, including ships and personnel.
NAVY.zh: 一个国家的整个海上力量，包括船只和人员。

CANCEL.en: A __lation (US); (nonstandard in some kinds of English).
CANCEL.zh: 取消（美国）； （某些英语是非标准的）。

LIMITS.en: A restriction; a bound beyond which one may not go.
LIMITS.zh: 限制；一个人不能超越的界限。

WEAPONS.en: An instrument of attack or defense in combat or hunting, e.g. most guns, missiles, or swords.
WEAPONS.zh: 战斗或狩猎中攻击或防御的工具，例如大多数枪支、导弹或剑。

PAINT.en: A substance that is applied as a liquid or paste, and dries into a solid coating that protects or adds color/colour to an object or surface to which it has been applied.
PAINT.zh: 以液体或糊状形式施用并干燥成固体涂层的物质，可保护所施用的物体或表面或为其添加颜色/颜色。

DELAY.en: A period of time before an event occurs; the act of __ing; procrastination; lingering inactivity.
DELAY.zh: 事件发生前的一段时间；拖延行为；拖延;持续不活动。

PILOT.en: A person who steers a ship, a helmsman.

OUTLET.en: A vent or similar passage to allow the escape of something.
OUTLET.zh: 允许某物逃逸的通风口或类似通道。

NOVEL.en: Newly made, formed or evolved; having no precedent; of recent origin; new.
NOVEL.zh: 新制造的、形成的或演变的；没有先例；最近起源的；新的。

PAN.en: A wide, flat receptacle used around the house, especially for cooking.
PAN.zh: 房屋周围使用的宽而扁平的容器，特别是用于烹饪。

WINNER.en: One who has won or often wins.
WINNER.zh: 曾经获胜或经常获胜的人。

POTTER.en: One who makes pots and other ceramic wares.
POTTER.zh: 制作罐子和其他陶瓷制品的人。

DISH.en: A vessel such as a plate for holding or serving food, often flat with a depressed region in the middle.
DISH.zh: 用于盛放或盛放食物的盘子，例如盘子，通常是扁平的，中间有凹陷区域。

PLAYS.en: Activity for amusement only, especially among the young.
PLAYS.zh: 仅供娱乐的活动，尤其是年轻人。

BULLETIN.en: A short report, especially one released through official channels to be broadcast or publicized.
BULLETIN.zh: 简短的报道，尤其是通过官方渠道发布并广播或宣传的报道。

OXFORD.en: A variety of shoe, typically made of heavy leather.
OXFORD.zh: 各种鞋，通常由厚皮革制成。

TRULY.en: (manner) In accordance with the facts; truthfully, accurately.

UNIVERSE.en: Our __, the sum of everything that exists in the cosmos, including time and space itself.
UNIVERSE.zh: 我们的宇宙，是宇宙中存在的一切事物的总和，包括时间和空间本身。

PATENT.en: A declaration issued by a government agency declaring someone the inventor of a new invention and having the privilege of stopping others from making, using or selling the claimed invention; a letter __.
PATENT.zh: 政府机构发布的声明，宣布某人是新发明的发明人，并有权阻止他人制造、使用或销售所主张的发明；专利证书。

SLOT.en: A broad, flat, wooden bar, a slat, especially as used to secure a door, window, etc.
SLOT.zh: 一种宽阔、平坦的木条、板条，尤其用于固定门、窗等。

WATCHING.en: To look at, see, or view for a period of time.
WATCHING.zh: 观看、观看或观看一段时间。

LODGE.en: A building for recreational use such as a hunting __ or a summer cabin.
LODGE.zh: 供娱乐用途的建筑物，例如狩猎小屋或避暑小屋。

STERLING.en: The currency of the United Kingdom; especially the pound.
STERLING.zh: 英国的货币；尤其是英镑。

SESSIONS.en: An informal gathering of musicians to play music, especially improvised jazz or a similar genre.
SESSIONS.zh: 音乐家的非正式聚会，演奏音乐，特别是即兴爵士乐或类似流派。

KERNEL.en: The core, center, or essence of an object or system.
KERNEL.zh: 物体或系统的核心、中心或本质。

BUYERS.en: A person who makes one or more purchases.
BUYERS.zh: 进行一次或多次购买的人。

JOURNALS.en: A diary or daily record of a person, organization, vessel etc.; daybook.
JOURNALS.zh: 个人、组织、船只等的日记或日常记录；日记本。

GRAY.en: An achromatic colour intermediate between black and white.
GRAY.zh: 介于黑色和白色之间的无彩色。

CHARGED.en: To assign a duty or responsibility to

BROAD.en: A shallow lake, one of a number of bodies of water in eastern Norfolk and Suffolk.
BROAD.zh: 一个浅湖，诺福克东部和萨福克东部的众多水体之一。

CHOSEN.en: To pick; to make the choice of; to select.
CHOSEN.zh: 去挑选；做出选择；来选择。

SWISS.en: To prepare (meat, fabric, etc.) by rolling or pounding in order to soften it.
SWISS.zh: 通过碾压或捣碎来准备（肉、织物等）以使其软化。

LABOUR.en: Effort expended on a particular task; toil, work.
LABOUR.zh: 为某项特定任务付出的努力；辛劳，工作。

TERMINAL.en: A building in an airport where passengers transfer from ground transportation to the facilities that allow them to board airplanes.
TERMINAL.zh: 机场内的一栋建筑，乘客可在此从地面交通转乘至登机设施。

RICE.en: Cereal plants, Oryza sativa of the grass family whose seeds are used as food.
RICE.zh: 谷类植物，禾本科植物，其种子用作食物。

LOOP.en: A length of thread, line or rope that is doubled over to make an opening.
LOOP.zh: 对折以形成开口的一段线、线或绳。

SALARY.en: A fixed amount of money paid to a worker, usually calculated on a monthly or annual basis, not hourly, as wages. Implies a degree of professionalism and/or autonomy.
SALARY.zh: 支付给工人的固定金额，通常按月或按年计算，而不是按小时计算，作为工资。意味着一定程度的专业精神和/或自主权。

FOODS.en: Any solid substance that can be consumed by living organisms, especially by eating, in order to sustain life.
FOODS.zh: 任何可以被生物体消耗的固体物质，特别是通过进食来维持生命。

GOURMET.en: A connoisseur in eating and drinking; someone who takes their food seriously.
GOURMET.zh: 吃喝行家；认真对待食物的人

GUARD.en: A person who, or thing that, protects or watches over something.
GUARD.zh: 保护或监视某物的人或事物。

TWENTY.en: A banknote with a denomination of 20.

NEWLY.en: Very recently; in the immediate past.

RAISE.en: An increase in wages or salary; a rise (UK).
RAISE.zh: 工资或薪水的增加；上升（英国）。

AVATAR.en: The incarnation of a deity, particularly Vishnu.
AVATAR.zh: 神的化身，特别是毗湿奴。

HUNDREDS.en: A hundred-dollar bill, or any other note denominated 100 (e.g. a hundred euros).
HUNDREDS.zh: 百元钞票或任何其他面值 100 的纸币（例如一百欧元）。

HELPED.en: To provide assistance to (someone or something).
HELPED.zh: 向（某人或某事）提供帮助。

PREMIER.en: (Westminster system) The head of government in parliament and leader of the cabinet.
PREMIER.zh: （威斯敏斯特体系）议会中的政府首脑和内阁领袖。

TOMORROW.en: The day after the present day.

MILK.en: A white liquid produced by the mammary glands of female mammals to nourish their young. From certain animals, especially cows, it is also called dairy __ and is a common food for humans as a beverage or used to produce various dairy products such as butter, cheese, and yogurt.
MILK.zh: 雌性哺乳动物乳腺产生的白色液体，用于滋养幼崽。来自某些动物，尤其是奶牛，它也被称为牛奶，是人类的常见食物，作为饮料或用于生产各种乳制品，如黄油、奶酪和酸奶。

DECIDE.en: To resolve (a contest, problem, dispute, etc.); to choose, determine, or settle
DECIDE.zh: 解决（竞赛、问题、争议等）；选择、决定或解决

DRAMA.en: A composition, normally in prose, telling a story and intended to be represented by actors impersonating the characters and speaking the dialogue
DRAMA.zh: 一种作品，通常是散文，讲述一个故事，并由演员模仿角色并说出对话来表现

VISITING.en: To habitually go to (someone in distress, sickness etc.) to comfort them. (Now generally merged into later senses, below.)
VISITING.zh: 习惯性地去（遇到困难、生病等的人）安慰他们。 （现在通常合并到后来的含义中，见下文。）

BANDS.en: A strip of material used for strengthening or coupling.
BANDS.zh: 用于加强或连接的一条材料。

BOOT.en: A heavy shoe that covers part of the leg.

SUITABLE.en: Having sufficient or the required properties for a certain purpose or task; appropriate to a certain occasion.
SUITABLE.zh: 具有用于特定目的或任务的足够或所需的属性；适合某种场合。

LUNCH.en: A light meal usually eaten around midday, notably when not as main meal of the day.
LUNCH.zh: 通常在中午左右吃的便餐，特别是当不作为一天的主餐时。

PUSH.en: A short, directed application of force; an act of __ing.
PUSH.zh: 短时间、定向施力；一种推动的行为。

CHAMBER.en: A room or set of rooms, particularly:
CHAMBER.zh: 一个房间或一组房间，特别是：

FINDINGS.en: A result of research or an investigation.

ISO.en: The state of being __lated, detached, or separated.
ISO.zh: 孤立、分离或分离的状态。

CLICKING.en: To cause to make a click; to operate (a switch, etc) so that it makes a click.
CLICKING.zh: 引起点击；操作（开关等），使其发出咔哒声。

POLLS.en: A survey of people, usually statistically analyzed to gauge wider public opinion.
POLLS.zh: 对人们的调查，通常进行统计分析以衡量更广泛的公众意见。

TOWER.en: A very tall iron-framed structure, usually painted red and white, on which microwave, radio, satellite, or other communication antennas are installed; mast.
TOWER.zh: 非常高的铁架结构，通常漆成红色和白色，上面安装有微波、无线电、卫星或其他通信天线；桅杆。

YOURS.en: That which belongs to you (singular); the possessive second-person singular pronoun used without a following noun.
YOURS.zh: 属于你的（单数）；不带名词的第二人称单数所有格代词。

SUM.en: A quantity obtained by addition or aggregation.
SUM.zh: 通过相加或聚合获得的数量。

MISC.en: Consisting of a variety of ingredients or parts.
MISC.zh: 由多种成分或部分组成。

CHICKEN.en: A domestic fowl, Gallus gallus, especially when young.
CHICKEN.zh: 一种家禽（Gallus gallus），尤其是在幼年时。

SHOWER.en: A brief fall of precipitation (spell of rain, or a similar fall of snow, sleet, or cascade).
SHOWER.zh: 短暂的降水（阵雨，或类似的降雪、雨夹雪或瀑布）。

SENDING.en: To make something (such as an object or message) go from one place to another.
SENDING.zh: 使某物（例如物体或消息）从一个地方移动到另一个地方。

TONIGHT.en: The nighttime of the current day or date; this night.
TONIGHT.zh: 当日或日期的夜间；今天晚上。

DEAR.zh: 一个非常善良、有爱心的人。

SHELL.en: A hard external covering of an animal.

CATHOLIC.en: Of the Western Christian church, as differentiated from e.g. the Orthodox church.
CATHOLIC.zh: 西方基督教会，与例如基督教会不同。东正教教堂。

OAK.en: A deciduous tree with distinctive deeply lobed leaves, acorns, and notably strong wood, typically of England and northeastern North America, included in genus Quercus.
OAK.zh: 一种落叶树，具有独特的深裂叶、橡子和特别坚固的木材，通常产于英格兰和北美洲东北部，属于栎属。

VAT.en: A large tub, such as is used for making wine or for tanning.
VAT.zh: 一个大浴缸，例如用于酿酒或晒黑的。

GOVERNOR.en: The chief executive officer of a first-level division of a country.
GOVERNOR.zh: 一个国家一级部门的首席执行官。

BEER.en: An alcoholic drink fermented from starch material, commonly barley malt, often with hops or some other substance to impart a bitter flavor.
BEER.zh: 由淀粉材料（通常是大麦麦芽）发酵而成的酒精饮料，通常与啤酒花或其他物质一起发酵，以赋予苦味。

SEEMED.en: To appear; to look outwardly; to be perceived as.

SWIMMING.en: The act or art of sustaining and propelling the body in water.
SWIMMING.zh: 在水中维持和推动身体的行为或艺术。

SPYWARE.en: Programs that surreptitiously monitor and report the actions of a computer user.
SPYWARE.zh: 秘密监视和报告计算机用户操作的程序。

SOLAR.en: Of or pertaining to the sun; proceeding from the sun
SOLAR.zh: 属于或关于太阳的；从太阳出发

CATCH.en: The act of seizing or capturing.

JANE.en: A silver Genovese coin, first used in England in the 14th century.
JANE.zh: 热那亚银币，14 世纪首次在英国使用。

RELIABLE.zh: 可靠或可靠的某事或某人

SIR.en: A man of a higher rank or position.

DOUBT.en: Disbelief or uncertainty (about something); a particular instance of such disbelief or uncertainty.
DOUBT.zh: （对某事）不相信或不确定；这种怀疑或不确定性的一个具体例子。

EARN.en: To gain (success, reward, recognition) through applied effort or work.
EARN.zh: 通过努力或工作获得（成功、奖励、认可）。

FINDER.en: One who finds or discovers something.

UNABLE.en: Not able; lacking a certain ability.

TASKS.en: A piece of work done as part of one’s duties.
TASKS.zh: 作为职责的一部分完成的一项工作。

ATTACKS.en: An attempt to cause damage, injury to, or death of opponent or enemy.
ATTACKS.zh: 试图对对手或敌人造成损害、伤害或死亡。

CONST.en: A variable whose value cannot be changed directly.
CONST.zh: 其值不能直接更改的变量。

DOORS.en: A portal of entry into a building, room, or vehicle, consisting of a rigid plane movable on a hinge. __ are frequently made of wood or metal. May have a handle to help open and close, a latch to hold the door closed and a lock that ensures the door cannot be opened without the key.
DOORS.zh: 进入建筑物、房间或车辆的入口，由可通过铰链移动的刚性平面组成。门通常由木材或金属制成。可能有一个帮助打开和关闭的把手、一个用于保持门关闭的闩锁以及一个确保没有钥匙就无法打开门的锁。

SYMPTOMS.en: A perceived change in some function, sensation or appearance of a person that indicates a disease or disorder, such as fever, headache or rash.
SYMPTOMS.zh: 人的某些功能、感觉或外观的感知变化，表明存在疾病或紊乱，例如发烧、头痛或皮疹。

RESORTS.en: A place where people go for recreation, especially one with facilities such as lodgings, entertainment, and a relaxing environment.
RESORTS.zh: 人们休闲娱乐的地方，尤指有住宿、娱乐、环境轻松等设施的地方。

VISITOR.en: Someone who visits someone else; someone staying as a guest.
VISITOR.zh: 拜访别人的人；有人作为客人入住。

TWIN.en: Either of two people (or, less commonly, animals) who shared the same uterus at the same time; one who was born at the same birth as a sibling.
TWIN.zh: 两个人（或者不太常见的是动物）同时共享同一个子宫；与兄弟姐妹同一出生的人。

FORTH.en: Forward in time, place or degree.
FORTH.zh: 在时间、地点或程度上向前推进。

ORDERED.en: To set in some sort of order.

FIGHTING.en: To contend in physical conflict, either singly or in war, battle etc.
FIGHTING.zh: 在身体冲突中进行斗争，无论是单独还是在战争、战斗等中。

SPY.en: A person who secretly watches and examines the actions of other individuals or organizations and gathers information on them (usually to gain an advantage).
SPY.zh: 秘密观察和检查其他个人或组织的行为并收集有关他们的信息（通常是为了获得优势）的人。

ROMANCE.en: A story relating to chivalry; a story involving knights, heroes, adventures, quests, etc.
ROMANCE.zh: 一个关于骑士精神的故事；涉及骑士、英雄、冒险、任务等的故事。

THEMES.en: A subject of a talk or an artistic piece; a topic.
THEMES.zh: 谈话或艺术作品的主题；一个话题。

POWERS.en: Ability to do or undergo something.
POWERS.zh: 做某事或经历某事的能力。

BITS.en: A piece of metal placed in a horse's mouth and connected to the reins to direct the animal.
BITS.zh: 放置在马嘴中并连接到缰绳以引导动物的一块金属。

FOCUSED.en: (followed by on or upon) To concentrate one's attention.
FOCUSED.zh: （后面跟在或之上）集中注意力。

ASKING.en: To request (information, or an answer to a question).
ASKING.zh: 请求（信息或问题的答案）。

BLOCKS.en: A substantial, often approximately cuboid, piece of any substance.
BLOCKS.zh: 任何物质的实体，通常近似长方体。

NORMALLY.en: Under normal conditions or circumstances; usually; most of the time
NORMALLY.zh: 在正常条件或情况下；通常;大部分时间

DIABETES.en: __ insipidus; any condition characterized by excessive or incontinent urine, now specifically as caused by impaired production of, or response to, the antidiuretic hormone vasopressin.
DIABETES.zh: 尿崩症；任何以尿液过多或尿失禁为特征的病症，特别是由于抗利尿激素加压素的产生或反应受损而引起的。

SUIT.en: A set of clothes to be worn together, now especially a man's matching jacket and trousers (also business __ or lounge __), or a similar outfit for a woman.
SUIT.zh: 一套可以一起穿的衣服，现在特别是男士配套的夹克和裤子（也可以是商务套装或休闲套装），或者是女士的类似服装。

SHIFT.en: A modifier key whose main function is __ing between two or more functions of any of certain other keys (usually by pressing __ and the other button simultaneously).
SHIFT.zh: 修饰键，其主要功能是在任何某些其他键的两个或多个功能之间切换（通常通过同时按下 __ 和其他按钮）。

CHIP.en: A small piece broken from a larger piece of solid material.
CHIP.zh: 从大块固体材料上折下的小块。

RES.en: The act of __erving, withholding or keeping back.
RES.zh: 保留、扣留或保留的行为。

SIT.en: Subsidence of the roof of a coal mine.

CUTTING.en: (heading) To incise, to cut into the surface of something.

WOW.en: Anything exceptionally surprising, unbelievable, outstanding, etc.
WOW.zh: 任何异常令人惊讶的、难以置信的、杰出的等等。

WRITERS.en: A person who writes, or produces literary work.
WRITERS.zh: 写作或创作文学作品的人。

LOVED.en: (usually transitive, sometimes intransitive, stative) To have a strong affection for (someone or something).
LOVED.zh: （通常及物，有时不及物，静态）对（某人或某事）有强烈的感情。

MAPPING.en: To create a visual representation of a territory, etc. via cartography.
MAPPING.zh: 通过制图创建领土等的视觉表示。

BIRDS.en: A member of the class of animals Aves in the phylum Chordata, characterized by being warm-blooded, having feathers and wings usually capable of flight, and laying eggs.
BIRDS.zh: 脊索动物门鸟纲的成员，其特征是温血动物，具有通常能够飞行的羽毛和翅膀，并且产卵。

INDEXED.en: To arrange an index for something, especially a long text.
INDEXED.zh: 为某事（尤其是长文本）安排索引。

SUPERIOR.en: A person of higher rank or quality.

PAYING.en: To give money or other compensation to in exchange for goods or services.
PAYING.zh: 给予金钱或其他补偿以换取商品或服务。

CARTOON.en: A humorous drawing, often with a caption, or a strip of such drawings.
CARTOON.zh: 一幅幽默的图画，通常带有标题，或者是这样的图画的一条。

SHOTS.en: The result of launching a projectile or bullet.
SHOTS.zh: 发射射弹或子弹的结果。

CHOICES.en: An option; a decision; an opportunity to choose or select something.
CHOICES.zh: 一个选项；决定；选择或选择某事的机会。

CARBON.en: The chemical element (symbol C) with an atomic number of 6. It can be found in pure form for example as graphite, a black, shiny and very soft material, or diamond, a colourless, transparent, crystalline solid and the hardest known material.
CARBON.zh: 原子序数为 6 的化学元素（符号 C）。它可以以纯净的形式存在，例如石墨（一种黑色、有光泽且非常柔软的材料）或钻石（一种无色、透明的结晶固体和已知最硬的材料）。

REGISTRY.en: A building in which things are registered or where registers are kept.
REGISTRY.zh: 登记物品或保存登记册的建筑物。

MASSIVE.en: A homogeneous mass of rock, not layered and without an obvious crystal structure.
MASSIVE.zh: 均匀的岩石块，没有层状，也没有明显的晶体结构。

EMPLOYED.en: To hire (somebody for work or a job).

BRIGHT.en: An artist's brush used in oil and acrylic painting with a long ferrule and a flat, somewhat tapering bristle head.
BRIGHT.zh: 用于油画和丙烯画的艺术家画笔，具有长套圈和扁平且稍呈锥形的刷毛头。

TREAT.en: An entertainment, outing, food, drink, or other indulgence provided by someone for the enjoyment of others.
TREAT.zh: 某人为了他人的享受而提供的娱乐、郊游、食物、饮料或其他放纵。

HEADER.en: The upper portion of a page (or other) layout.
HEADER.zh: 页面（或其他）布局的上部。

POVERTY.en: The quality or state of being poor; lack of money

FORMED.en: To assume (a certain shape or visible structure).
FORMED.zh: 呈现（某种形状或可见结构）。

PIANO.en: A percussive keyboard musical instrument, usually ranging over seven octaves, with white and black colored keys, played by pressing these keys, causing hammers to strike strings
PIANO.zh: 一种打击键盘乐器，通常音域超过七个八度，有白色和黑色的琴键，通过按下这些琴键来演奏，使锤子敲击琴弦

ECHO.en: A reflected sound that is heard again by its initial observer.
ECHO.zh: 最初的观察者再次听到的反射声音。

QUE.en: A fireplace or pit for grilling food, typically used outdoors and traditionally employing hot charcoal as the heating medium.
QUE.zh: 用于烧烤食物的壁炉或坑，通常在户外使用，传统上使用热木炭作为加热介质。

GRID.en: A rectangular array of squares or rectangles of equal size, such as in a crossword puzzle.
GRID.zh: 由相同大小的正方形或矩形组成的矩形阵列，例如填字游戏中的矩形阵列。

SHEETS.en: A thin bed cloth used as a covering for a mattress or as a layer over the sleeper.
SHEETS.zh: 一种薄床布，用作床垫的覆盖物或覆盖睡眠者的一层。

PLASMA.en: A state of matter consisting of partially ionized gas and electrons
PLASMA.zh: 由部分电离的气体和电子组成的物质状态

ALLOWING.en: To grant, give, admit, accord, afford, or yield; to let one have.
ALLOWING.zh: 授予、给予、承认、同意、负担或让步；让一个人拥有。

BIDDING.en: To issue a command; to tell.

RISKS.en: A possible adverse event or outcome
RISKS.zh: 可能的不良事件或结果

FIG.en: A fruit-bearing tree or shrub of the genus Ficus that is native mainly to the tropics.
FIG.zh: 榕属的一种结果树或灌木，主要原产于热带地区。

COUNTIES.en: The land ruled by a count or a countess.
COUNTIES.zh: 由伯爵或伯爵夫人统治的土地。

PORTS.en: A place on the coast at which ships can shelter, or dock to load and unload cargo or passengers.
PORTS.zh: 海岸上船舶可以停泊或停靠装卸货物或乘客的地方。

DREAMS.en: Imaginary events seen in the mind while sleeping.
DREAMS.zh: 睡觉时脑海中看到的想象事件。

BLOGGER.en: A contributor to a blog (from weblog) or online journal.
BLOGGER.zh: 博客（来自博客）或在线期刊的撰稿人。

TEACH.en: To show (someone) the way; to guide, conduct; to point, indicate.
TEACH.zh: 为（某人）指明道路；指导、进行；指出，表明。

RAPID.en: (often in the plural) a rough section of a river or stream which is difficult to navigate due to the swift and turbulent motion of the water.
RAPID.zh: （通常为复数）河流或溪流的一段崎岖不平的区域，由于水流的快速和湍急的运动而难以航行。

HAIRY.en: Of a person, having a lot of hair on the body.

SEMINAR.en: A class held for advanced studies in which students meet regularly to discuss original research, under the guidance of a professor.
SEMINAR.zh: 为高级研究而举办的课程，学生在教授的指导下定期聚会讨论原创研究。

LATINA.zh: 一位拉丁美洲女性。 （比较拉丁裔。）

WHEELS.en: A circular device capable of rotating on its axis, facilitating movement or transportation or performing labour in machines.
WHEELS.zh: 能够绕其轴旋转的圆形装置，便于移动或运输或在机器中执行劳动。

SPECIFY.en: To state explicitly, or in detail, or as a condition.
SPECIFY.zh: 明确地、详细地、或作为条件地陈述。

FORMATS.en: The layout of a publication or document.

TAB.en: A small flap or strip of material attached to something, for holding, manipulation, identification, opening etc.
TAB.zh: 附着在某物上的小翼片或材料条，用于固定、操纵、识别、打开等。

DEPENDS.en: (followed by on or upon, formerly also by of) To be contingent or conditioned; to have something as a necessary condition; to hinge on.
DEPENDS.zh: （后接 on 或 on，以前也接 of）有条件的或有条件的；拥有某种东西作为必要条件；取决于。

BOOTS.en: A heavy shoe that covers part of the leg.

ROUTER.en: Someone who routes or directs items from one location to another.
ROUTER.zh: 将物品从一个地点运送或引导至另一地点的人。

EDITING.en: To change a text, or a document.

FOLDER.en: An organizer that papers are kept in, usually with an index tab, to be stored as a single unit in a filing cabinet.
FOLDER.zh: 一种存放纸张的组织器，通常带有索引标签，以便作为一个单元存储在文件柜中。

PULSE.en: A normally regular beat felt when arteries are depressed, caused by the pumping action of the heart.
PULSE.zh: 当动脉受压时，由心脏的泵血作用引起，通常会感觉到有规律的搏动。

VOTING.en: To cast a vote; to assert a formalized choice in an election
VOTING.zh: 投票；在选举中主张正式的选择

COURTS.en: An enclosed space; a courtyard; an uncovered area shut in by the walls of a building, or by different buildings; also, a space opening from a street and nearly surrounded by houses; a blind alley.
COURTS.zh: 封闭的空间；一个庭院；被建筑物墙壁或不同建筑物封闭的未覆盖区域；此外，还有一个从街道开口、几乎被房屋包围的空间；死胡同。

STRIP.en: A long, thin piece of land; any long, thin area.
STRIP.zh: 一块又长又薄的土地；任何长而薄的区域。

PEARL.en: A shelly concretion, usually rounded, and having a brilliant luster, with varying tints, found in the mantle, or between the mantle and shell, of certain bivalve mollusks, especially in the __ oysters and river mussels, and sometimes in certain univalves. It is usually due to a secretion of shelly substance around some irritating foreign particle. Its substance is the same as nacre, or mother-of-__. Round lustrous __s are used in jewellery.
PEARL.zh: 一种壳状结核，通常呈圆形，具有明亮的光泽，具有不同的色调，见于某些双壳类软体动物的地幔或地幔与贝壳之间，特别是珍珠贝和河蚌，有时也见于某些单壳类。这通常是由于一些刺激性异物周围分泌出壳状物质。其物质与珍珠母或珍珠母相同。圆形有光泽的珍珠用于珠宝。

ACCIDENT.en: An unexpected event with negative consequences occurring without the intention of the one suffering the consequences.
ACCIDENT.zh: 一种具有负面后果的意外事件，而遭受后果的人无意中发生。

NICK.en: A small cut in a surface.

RESIDENT.en: A person, animal or plant living at a certain location or in a certain area.
RESIDENT.zh: 生活在一定地点或一定区域的人、动物或植物。

PLOT.en: (authorship) The course of a story, comprising a series of incidents which are gradually unfolded, sometimes by unexpected means.
PLOT.zh: （作者身份）故事的进程，由一系列逐渐展开的事件组成，有时以意想不到的方式展开。

POSSIBLY.en: (modifying a clause or predicate) Perhaps; indicates that the proposition may be true (is not certainly false) regardless of any facts or circumstances known to, stated by or implied by the speaker.
POSSIBLY.zh: （修饰从句或谓语）也许；表明该命题可能是正确的（不一定是错误的），无论说话者已知、陈述或暗示的任何事实或情况如何。

AIRLINE.en: A company that flies airplanes to transport people and goods.
AIRLINE.zh: 一家驾驶飞机运输人员和货物的公司。

PUMP.en: A device for moving or compressing a liquid or gas.
PUMP.zh: 用于移动或压缩液体或气体的装置。

EXISTS.en: (stative) to be; have existence; have being or reality

FLASHING.en: To cause to shine briefly or intermittently.

NARROW.en: (chiefly in the plural) A __ passage, especially a contracted part of a stream, lake, or sea; a strait connecting two bodies of water.
NARROW.zh: （主要是复数）狭窄的通道，尤指溪流、湖泊或海洋的收缩部分；连接两个水体的海峡。

THREAT.en: An expression of intent to injure or punish another.
THREAT.zh: 表达伤害或惩罚他人的意图。

SURVEYS.en: The act of surveying; a general view.

SITTING.en: A period during which one is seated for a specific purpose.
SITTING.zh: 一个人为了特定目的而坐着的一段时间。

TRAILER.en: Someone who or something that trails.

GARDENS.en: An outdoor area containing one or more types of plants, usually plants grown for food or ornamental purposes.
GARDENS.zh: 含有一种或多种植物的室外区域，通常是为了食用或观赏目的而种植的植物。

ANTIQUE.en: A grotesque representation of a figure; a gargoyle.
ANTIQUE.zh: 怪诞的人物形象；石像鬼。

LABELS.en: A small ticket or sign giving information about something to which it is attached or intended to be attached.
LABELS.zh: 一种小票或标志，提供有关其所附着或打算附着的物品的信息。

HEADS.en: The part of the body of an animal or human which contains the brain, mouth and main sense organs.
HEADS.zh: 动物或人类身体的一部分，包含大脑、口腔和主要感觉器官。

STORED.en: To keep (something) while not in use, generally in a place meant for that purpose.
STORED.zh: 在不使用时保留（某物），通常放在专门用于此目的的地方。

LOGOS.en: A form of rhetoric in which the writer or speaker uses logic as the main argument.
LOGOS.zh: 一种修辞形式，作者或演讲者使用逻辑作为主要论点。

ANTIQUES.en: A grotesque representation of a figure; a gargoyle.
ANTIQUES.zh: 怪诞的人物形象；石像鬼。

DENSITY.en: A measure of the mass of matter contained by a unit volume.
DENSITY.zh: 单位体积所含物质质量的度量。

BEDS.en: A piece of furniture, usually flat and soft, on which to rest or sleep.
BEDS.zh: 一件家具，通常平坦且柔软，可供休息或睡觉。

PCS.en: Initialism of permanent change of station.

BILLS.en: Any of various bladed or pointed hand weapons, originally designating an Anglo-Saxon sword, and later a weapon of infantry, especially in the 14th and 15th centuries, commonly consisting of a broad, heavy, double-edged, hook-shaped blade, with a short pike at the back and another at the top, attached to the end of a long staff.
BILLS.zh: 各种带刃或尖头的手持武器，最初指盎格鲁-撒克逊剑，后来指步兵武器，特别是在 14 世纪和 15 世纪，通常由宽而重的双刃钩形刀片组成，背面有一根短矛，顶部有一根短矛，连接在长杖的末端。

STABLE.en: A building, wing or dependency set apart and adapted for lodging and feeding (and training) animals with hoofs, especially horses.
STABLE.zh: 为住宿和喂养（和训练）有蹄动物（尤其是马）而分开的建筑物、翼楼或附属物。

OPERA.en: A theatrical work, combining drama, music, song and sometimes dance.
OPERA.zh: 一种戏剧作品，结合了戏剧、音乐、歌曲，有时还有舞蹈。

DOCTORS.en: A physician; a member of the medical profession; one who is trained and licensed to heal the sick or injured. The final examination and qualification may award a doctor degree in which case the post-nominal letters are D.O., DPM, M.D., DMD, DDS, in the US or MBBS in the UK.
DOCTORS.zh: 医生；医学界人士；受过培训并获得许可来治疗病人或伤者的人。最终考试和资格可能授予博士学位，在这种情况下，提名字母在美国为 D.O.、DPM、M.D.、DMD、DDS，在英国为 MBBS。

CINEMA.en: A movie theatre, a movie house

ASSET.en: Something or someone of any value; any portion of one's property or effects so considered.
ASSET.zh: 有任何价值的东西或人；如此考虑的一个人的财产或财物的任何部分。

DRINKING.en: To consume (a liquid) through the mouth.

REACTION.en: An action or statement in response to a stimulus or other event.
REACTION.zh: 对刺激或其他事件作出反应的行动或陈述。

BLANK.en: A small French coin, originally of silver, afterwards of copper, worth 5 deniers; also a silver coin of Henry V current in the parts of France then held by the English, worth about 8 pence .
BLANK.zh: 一枚法国小硬币，最初是银币，后来是铜币，价值 5 旦尼尔；还有一枚亨利五世的银币，当时在法国部分地区由英国人持有，价值约8便士。

DELUXE.en: Very fine in quality or luxurious.

HUMOR.en: The quality of being amusing, comical, funny.

AGED.en: To cause to grow old; to impart the characteristics of age to.

MONITORS.en: Someone who watches over something; a person in charge of something or someone.
MONITORS.zh: 监视某事的人；负责某事或某人的人。

LIVED.en: To be alive; to have life.

PURSUANT.en: In conformance to, or in agreement with.

DOMAINS.en: A geographic area owned or controlled by a single person or organization.
DOMAINS.zh: 由个人或组织拥有或控制的地理区域。

FLYING.en: To hit a fly ball; to hit a fly ball that is caught for an out. Compare ground (verb) and line (verb).
FLYING.zh: 击打飞球；击打被抓出界外的飞球。比较地面（动词）和线（动词）。

SIN.en: A violation of God's will or religious law.
SIN.zh: 违反上帝的意志或宗教法律。

CUTE.en: Possessing physical features, behaviors, personality traits or other properties that are mainly attributed to infants and small or cuddly animals; e.g. fair, dainty, round, and soft physical features, disproportionately large eyes and head, playfulness, fragility, helplessness, curiosity or shyness, innocence, affectionate behavior.
CUTE.zh: 拥有主要归因于婴儿和小动物或可爱动物的身体特征、行为、性格特征或其他特性；例如公平、精致、圆润、柔软的身体特征，不成比例的大眼睛和头部，顽皮、脆弱、无助、好奇或害羞、天真、深情的行为。

PARA.en: A former subunit of currency in several countries in the Ottoman/Turkish and Yugoslav regions.
PARA.zh: 奥斯曼/土耳其和南斯拉夫地区几个国家的前货币子单位。

SIEMENS.en: In the International System of Units, the derived unit of electrical conductance; the electric conductance in a body that has a resistance of one ohm. Symbol: S
SIEMENS.zh: 在国际单位制中，电导的衍生单位；电阻为一欧姆的物体的电导率。符号：S

POUNDS.en: A unit of mass equal to 16 avoirdupois ounces (= 453.592 37 g). Today this value is the most common meaning of "pound" as a unit of weight.
POUNDS.zh: 质量单位，等于 16 常衡盎司 (= 453.592 37 g)。今天，这个值是“磅”作为重量单位的最常见含义。

BUFFALO.en: Any of the Old World mammals of the family Bovidae, such as the Cape __, Syncerus caffer, or the water __ Bubalus bubalis.
BUFFALO.zh: 任何旧大陆牛科哺乳动物，例如非洲水牛、Syncerus caffer 或水牛 Bubalus bubalis。

SEED.en: A fertilized and ripened ovule, containing an embryonic plant.
SEED.zh: 受精且成熟的胚珠，含有胚胎植物。

CAMPING.en: To live in a tent or similar temporary accommodation.
CAMPING.zh: 住在帐篷或类似的临时住处。

MEETS.en: A sports competition, especially for track and field (a track meet) or swimming (a swim meet).
MEETS.zh: 体育比赛，特别是田径（田径比赛）或游泳（游泳比赛）。

WELFARE.en: Health, safety, happiness and prosperity; well-being in any respect.
WELFARE.zh: 健康、安全、幸福、繁荣；任何方面的幸福。

MARKED.en: Having a visible or identifying mark.

DRIVEN.en: To provide an impetus for motion or other physical change, to move an object by means of the provision of force thereto.
DRIVEN.zh: 为运动或其他物理变化提供动力，通过向物体提供力来移动物体。

MEASURED.en: To ascertain the quantity of a unit of material via calculated comparison with respect to a standard.
MEASURED.zh: 通过与标准的计算比较来确定单位材料的数量。

BOTTLE.en: A container, typically made of glass or plastic and having a tapered neck, used primarily for holding liquids.
BOTTLE.zh: 一种容器，通常由玻璃或塑料制成，具有锥形颈部，主要用于盛装液体。

MASSAGE.en: The action of rubbing, kneading or hitting someone's body, to help the person relax, prepare for muscular action (as in contact sports) or to relieve aches.
MASSAGE.zh: 摩擦、揉捏或击打某人身体的动作，以帮助该人放松、为肌肉活动（如接触运动）做好准备或缓解疼痛。

RUBBER.en: Pliable material derived from the sap of the __ tree; a hydrocarbon polymer of isoprene.
RUBBER.zh: 来自橡胶树汁液的柔韧材料；异戊二烯的烃聚合物。

MEAT.en: The flesh (muscle tissue) of an animal used as food.
MEAT.zh: 用作食物的动物的肉（肌肉组织）。

ING.en: A meadow, especially a low meadow near a river; water meadow.
ING.zh: 草地，尤指河边的低矮草地；水草甸。

PYTHON.en: A type of large constricting snake.

VILLA.en: (plural "__s") A house, often larger and more expensive than average, in the countryside or on the coast, often used as a retreat.
VILLA.zh: （复数“别墅”）位于乡村或海岸的房屋，通常比一般房屋更大且更昂贵，通常用作休养所。

BONE.en: A composite material consisting largely of calcium phosphate and collagen and making up the skeleton of most vertebrates.
BONE.zh: 一种主要由磷酸钙和胶原蛋白组成的复合材料，构成大多数脊椎动物的骨骼。

COLUMNS.en: A solid upright structure designed usually to support a larger structure above it, such as a roof or horizontal beam, but sometimes for decoration.
COLUMNS.zh: 坚固的直立结构，通常设计用于支撑其上方的较大结构，例如屋顶或水平梁，但有时用于装饰。

BUGS.en: An insect of the order Hemiptera (the “true __”).
BUGS.zh: 半翅目昆虫（“真正的昆虫”）。

COOKIES.en: A small, flat, baked good which is either crisp or soft but firm.
COOKIES.zh: 一种小而扁平的烘焙食品，要么脆，要么软但坚硬。

TUTORIAL.en: A self-paced learning exercise; a lesson prepared so that a student can learn at their own speed, at their convenience.
TUTORIAL.zh: 自定进度的学习练习；准备的课程，以便学生可以在方便时按照自己的速度学习。

MED.en: (chiefly in the plural) __ications, especially prescribed psychoactive __ications.
MED.zh: （主要是复数）药物，尤其是处方的精神活性药物。

ENTITY.en: That which has a distinct existence as an individual unit. Often used for organisations which have no physical form.
ENTITY.zh: 作为一个单独的单位具有独特的存在。通常用于没有物理形式的组织。

CRUISES.en: A sea or lake voyage, especially one taken for pleasure.
CRUISES.zh: 海上或湖泊航行，尤其是为了享乐而进行的航行。

GATE.en: A doorlike structure outside a house.

ROMAN.en: One of the main three types used for the Latin alphabet (the others being italics and blackletter), in which the ascenders are mostly straight.
ROMAN.zh: 拉丁字母的三种主要类型之一（其他是斜体和黑体），其中上升部分大多是直的。

DUTIES.en: That which one is morally or legally obligated to do.
DUTIES.zh: 一个人在道德上或法律上有义务去做的事情。

VALUABLE.en: A personal possession such as jewellery, of relatively great monetary value; — usually used in plural form.
VALUABLE.zh: 具有相对较高货币价值的个人财产，例如珠宝； - 通常以复数形式使用。

ETHICS.en: The study of principles relating to right and wrong conduct.
ETHICS.zh: 研究与正确和错误行为有关的原则。

HEATING.en: To cause an increase in temperature of (an object or space); to cause to become hot (often with "up").
HEATING.zh: 导致（物体或空间）温度升高；导致变热（通常与“up”一起使用）。

LEG.en: A limb or appendage that an animal uses for support or locomotion.
LEG.zh: 动物用来支撑或运动的肢体或附属物。

NECK.en: The part of the body connecting the head and the trunk found in humans and some animals.
NECK.zh: 人类和某些动物连接头部和躯干的身体部分。

WING.en: An appendage of an animal's (bird, bat, insect) body that enables it to fly; a similar fin at the side of a ray or similar fish
WING.zh: 动物（鸟、蝙蝠、昆虫）身体的附属物，使其能够飞行；鳐鱼或类似鱼侧面的类似鳍

STEREO.en: A system of recording or reproducing sound that uses two channels, each playing a portion of the original sound in such a way as to create the illusion of locating the sound at a particular position, each offset from the other, thereby more accurately imitating the location of the original sound when the recorded or reproduced sound is heard.
STEREO.zh: 一种使用两个声道录制或再现声音的系统，每个声道播放原始声音的一部分，从而产生将声音定位在特定位置的错觉，每个声道都相互偏移，从而在听到录制或再现的声音时更准确地模仿原始声音的位置。

TASTE.en: One of the sensations produced by the tongue in response to certain chemicals; the quality of giving this sensation.
TASTE.zh: 舌头响应某些化学物质而产生的感觉之一；给予这种感觉的质量。

DEALING.en: To distribute among a number of recipients, to give out as one’s portion or share.
DEALING.zh: 分发给许多接受者，作为一个人的部分或份额分发。

RAIL.en: A horizontal bar extending between supports and used for support or as a barrier; a __ing.
RAIL.zh: 在支撑物之间延伸并用于支撑或作为屏障的水平杆；栏杆。

AIRLINES.en: A company that flies airplanes to transport people and goods.
AIRLINES.zh: 一家驾驶飞机运输人员和货物的公司。

LIBERAL.en: One with __ views, supporting individual liberty (see Wikipedia's article on __ism).
LIBERAL.zh: 具有自由主义观点，支持个人自由（参见维基百科关于自由主义的文章）。

JAY.en: Any one of the numerous species of birds belonging to several genera within the family Corvidae, including Garrulus, Cyanocitta, Aphelocoma, Perisoreus, Cyanocorax, Gymnorhinus, Cyanolyca, Ptilostomus, and Calocitta, allied to the crows, but smaller, more graceful in form, often handsomely coloured, usually having a crest, and often noisy.
JAY.zh: 属于鸦科几个属的众多鸟类中的任何一种，包括 Garrulus、Cyanocitta、Aphelocoma、Perisoreus、Cyanocorax、Gymnorhinus、Cyanolyca、Ptilostomus 和 Calocitta，与乌鸦有亲缘关系，但体型较小，形状更加优美，通常颜色漂亮，通常有羽冠，并且经常吵闹。

TRIPS.en: A journey; an excursion or jaunt
TRIPS.zh: 一次旅行；短途旅行或短途旅行

GAP.en: An opening in anything made by breaking or parting.
GAP.zh: 任何因断裂或分离而形成的开口。

SIDES.en: A bounding straight edge of a two-dimensional shape.

TUBE.en: Anything that is hollow and cylindrical in shape.
TUBE.zh: 任何中空且圆柱形的物体。

TURNS.en: (heading) to make a non-linear physical movement.

CACHE.en: A store of things that may be required in the future, which can be retrieved rapidly, protected or hidden in some way.
CACHE.zh: 存储将来可能需要的东西，可以通过某种方式快速检索、保护或隐藏。

BELT.en: A band worn around the waist to hold clothing to one's body (usually pants), hold weapons (such as a gun or sword), or serve as a decorative piece of clothing.
BELT.zh: 系在腰间的带子，用于将衣服固定在身上（通常是裤子）、固定武器（如枪或剑）或用作衣服的装饰。

JACKET.en: A piece of clothing worn on the upper body outside a shirt or blouse, often waist length to thigh length.
JACKET.zh: 穿在衬衫或衬衫外面的上半身的一件衣服，通常是腰部长度到大腿长度。

ORACLE.en: A shrine dedicated to some prophetic deity.
ORACLE.zh: 供奉某些预言神灵的神殿。

AVIATION.en: The art or science of making and flying aircraft.
AVIATION.zh: 制造和飞行飞机的艺术或科学。

HOBBIES.en: An activity that one enjoys doing in one's spare time.
HOBBIES.zh: 一个人在业余时间喜欢做的一项活动。

PROUD.en: Feeling honoured (by something); feeling happy or satisfied about an event or fact; gratified.
PROUD.zh: （因某事）感到荣幸；对某件事或事实感到高兴或满意；很满意。

EXCESS.en: The state of surpassing or going beyond limits; the being of a measure beyond sufficiency, necessity, or duty; that which exceeds what is usual or proper
EXCESS.zh: 超越或超越极限的状态；超出充分性、必要性或义务的措施；超出通常或适当范围的

GIANT.en: A mythical human of very great size.
GIANT.zh: 一个身材非常巨大的神话人物。

ACHIEVED.en: To succeed in something, now especially in academic performance.
ACHIEVED.zh: 在某件事上取得成功，现在尤其是在学业成绩方面。

INJURIES.en: Damage to the body of a human or animal.
INJURIES.zh: 对人类或动物的身体造成损害。

ALARM.en: A summons to arms, as on the approach of an enemy.
ALARM.zh: 战斗召唤，如敌人逼近时的召唤。

VOLTAGE.en: The difference in electrostatic potential between two points in space, especially between live and neutral conductors or the earth.
VOLTAGE.zh: 空间中两点之间的静电势差，尤其是带电导体和中性导体或大地之间的静电势差。

USUAL.en: The typical state of something, or something that is typical.
USUAL.zh: 某事物的典型状态，或典型的事物。

LOADING.en: To put a load on or in (a means of conveyance or a place of storage).
LOADING.zh: 将负载放置在（运输工具或储存地点）上或内部。

STAMPS.en: An act of stamping the foot, paw or hoof.
STAMPS.zh: 跺脚、爪子或蹄子的行为。

APPEARED.en: To come or be in sight; to be in view; to become visible.
APPEARED.zh: 来到或出现在眼前；在视野中；变得可见。

FRANKLIN.en: A freeholder, especially as belonging to a class of landowners in the 14th and 15th century ranking below the gentry.
FRANKLIN.zh: 自由保​​有者，尤指 14 世纪和 15 世纪阶级低于士绅的地主阶级。

ANGLE.en: A figure formed by two rays which start from a common point (a plane __) or by three planes that intersect (a solid __).
ANGLE.zh: 由从公共点（平面角）开始的两条射线或相交的三个平面（立体角）形成的图形。

ROB.en: To steal from, especially using force or violence.
ROB.zh: 偷窃，尤指使用武力或暴力。

VINYL.en: The univalent radical CH2=CH−, derived from ethylene.

ONGOING.en: To be __ (occurring, happening); to last, proceed or continue.
ONGOING.zh: 持续进行（正在发生，正在发生）；持续、进行或继续。

IMAGING.en: To represent by an image or symbol; to portray.
IMAGING.zh: 用图像或符号来表示；来描绘。

BETTING.en: To stake or pledge upon the outcome of an event; to wager.
BETTING.zh: 对事件的结果进行抵押或质押；来打赌。

LIBERTY.en: The condition of being free from control or restrictions.
LIBERTY.zh: 不受控制或限制的状态。

ERA.en: A time period of indeterminate length, gen__lly more than one year.
ERA.zh: 长度不确定的时间段，通常超过一年。

DERIVED.en: To obtain or receive (something) from something else.
DERIVED.zh: 从其他事物获得或接收（某物）。

HONOR.en: Recognition of importance or value; respect; veneration (of someone, usually for being morally upright or successful)
HONOR.zh: 承认重要性或价值；尊重;尊敬（对某人的尊敬，通常是因为道德正直或成功）

ORIENTED.en: To build or place (something) so as to face eastward.
ORIENTED.zh: 建造或放置（某物）面向东方。

EAGLE.en: Any of several large carnivorous and carrion-eating birds in the family Accipitridae, having a powerful hooked bill and keen vision.
EAGLE.zh: 鹰科中几种大型食肉和食腐鸟类的一种，具有强大的钩状喙和敏锐的视力。

DESKTOPS.en: The top surface of a desk.

PANTS.en: (Manchester) An outer garment that covers the body from the waist downwards, covering each leg separately, usually as far as the ankles; trousers.
PANTS.zh: （曼彻斯特）从腰部以下覆盖身体的外衣，分别覆盖每条腿，通常一直到脚踝；裤子。
