PRAYER.en: A practice of communicating with one's God.

LUCK.en: Something that happens to someone by chance, a chance occurrence, especially a favourable one.
LUCK.zh: 某人偶然发生的事情，偶然发生的事情，特别是有利的事情。

POSTAGE.en: The charge for posting an item.

DIAL.en: A graduated, circular scale over which a needle moves to show a measurement (such as speed).
DIAL.zh: 带有刻度的圆形刻度，指针在其上移动以显示测量结果（例如速度）。

CHEESE.en: A dairy product made from curdled or cultured milk.
CHEESE.zh: 由凝乳或发酵乳制成的乳制品。

JET.en: A collimated stream, spurt or flow of liquid or gas from a pressurized container, an engine, etc.
JET.zh: 来自加压容器、发动机等的液体或气体的准直流、喷射或流。

CROWN.en: A royal, imperial or princely headdress; a diadem.
CROWN.zh: 皇家、帝国或王子的头饰；王冠。

PAR.en: A passage in text that is about a different subject from the preceding text, marked by commencing on a new line, the first line sometimes being indented.
PAR.zh: 文本中与前文主题不同的段落，以换行开始为标志，第一行有时会缩进。

MAKER.en: Someone who makes; a person or thing that makes or produces something.
MAKER.zh: 制造的人；制造或生产某物的人或物。

CRACK.en: A thin and usually jagged space opened in a previously solid material.
CRACK.zh: 先前为固体的材料中出现了一个薄薄且通常呈锯齿状的空间。

PICKS.en: A tool used for digging; a pickaxe.
PICKS.zh: 用于挖掘的工具；一把镐。

SEMESTER.en: Half of a school year or academic year such as fall or spring __.
SEMESTER.zh: 一个学年或学年的一半，例如秋季或春季学期。

FETISH.en: Something which is believed to possess, contain, or cause spiritual or magical powers; an amulet or a talisman.
FETISH.zh: 被认为拥有、包含或产生精神或魔法力量的东西；护身符或护身符。

APPLIES.en: To lay or place; to put (one thing to another)
APPLIES.zh: 铺设或放置；把（一件事放到另一件事上）

CASINOS.en: A public building or room for entertainment, especially gambling.
CASINOS.zh: 供娱乐，尤其是赌博的公共建筑或房间。

SMOKE.en: The visible vapor/vapour, gases, and fine particles given off by burning or smoldering material.
SMOKE.zh: 材料燃烧或阴燃时释放出的可见蒸气/蒸气、气体和细颗粒。

APACHE.en: Any of several Athabascan-speaking peoples of the American southwest excluding Navajo, i.e. Chiricahua, Jicarilla, Lipan, Mescalero, Plains __, or Western __.
APACHE.zh: 美国西南部讲阿萨巴斯卡语的任何民族，不包括纳瓦霍人，即奇里卡瓦人、吉卡里拉人、利潘人、梅斯卡莱罗人、平原阿帕奇人或西阿帕奇人。

FILTERS.en: A device which separates a suspended, dissolved, or particulate matter from a fluid, solution, or other substance; any device that separates one substance from another.
FILTERS.zh: 将悬浮物、溶解物或颗粒物与流体、溶液或其他物质分离的装置；将一种物质与另一种物质分离的任何装置。

CAKE.en: A rich, sweet dessert food, typically made of flour, sugar and eggs and baked in an oven, and often covered in icing.
CAKE.zh: 一种浓郁的甜味甜点食品，通常由面粉、糖和鸡蛋制成，在烤箱中烘烤，通常覆盖有糖霜。

APART.en: (Used after a noun or in the predicate) Exceptional, distinct.
APART.zh: （用在名词后面或谓语中）例外的，独特的。

BLIND.en: A covering for a window to keep out light. The covering may be made of cloth or of narrow slats that can block light or allow it to pass.
BLIND.zh: 窗户上遮光的遮盖物。覆盖物可以由布或窄板条制成，可以阻挡光线或允许光线通过。

LOUNGE.en: A waiting room in an office, airport etc.
LOUNGE.zh: 办公室、机场等的候诊室。

COINS.en: (money) A piece of currency, usually metallic and in the shape of a disc, but sometimes polygonal, or with a hole in the middle.
COINS.zh: （钱）一种货币，通常是金属的，呈圆盘状，但有时是多边形的，或者中间有一个孔。

STRONGLY.en: In a strong or powerful manner.

CAFE.en: A convenience store, originally one that sold coffee and similar basic items.
CAFE.zh: 一家便利店，最初是一家出售咖啡和类似基本物品的商店。

KEN.en: To give birth, conceive, beget, be born; to develop (as a fetus); to nourish, sustain (as life).
KEN.zh: 生育、怀孕、生育、出生；发育（作为胎儿）；滋养、维持（如生命）。

PROTEINS.en: Any of numerous large, complex naturally-produced molecules composed of one or more long chains of amino acids, in which the amino acid groups are held together by peptide bonds.
PROTEINS.zh: 由一个或多个氨基酸长链组成的众多大型、复杂的天然分子中的一种，其中氨基酸基团通过肽键连接在一起。

TILL.en: Until; to, up to; as late as (a given time).
TILL.zh: 直到;至，至；最迟（给定时间）。

PEN.en: An enclosure (enclosed area) used to contain domesticated animals, especially sheep or cattle.
PEN.zh: 用于圈养家养动物（尤其是羊或牛）的围栏（封闭区域）。

SHOE.en: A protective covering for the foot, with a bottom part composed of thick leather or plastic sole and often a thicker heel, and a softer upper part made of leather or synthetic material. __s generally do not extend above the ankle, as opposed to boots, which do.
SHOE.zh: 足部的保护层，底部由厚皮革或塑料鞋底组成，通常有较厚的鞋跟，上部较软，由皮革或合成材料制成。鞋子通常不会延伸到脚踝以上，而靴子则可以。

ELECTED.en: To choose or make a decision (to do something)
ELECTED.zh: 选择或做出决定（做某事）

CARRYING.en: To lift (something) and take it to another place; to transport (something) by lifting.
CARRYING.zh: 举起（某物）并将其带到另一个地方；通过提升来运输（某物）。

VICTORY.en: An instance of having won a competition or battle or succeeded in an effort.
VICTORY.zh: 赢得比赛或战斗或努力取得成功的实例。

SAND.en: Rock that is ground more finely than gravel, but is not as fine as silt (more formally, see grain sizes chart), forming beaches and deserts and also used in construction.
SAND.zh: 比砾石磨得更细，但不像淤泥那么细的岩石（更正式地，参见粒度表），形成海滩和沙漠，也用于建筑。

MADISON.en: A two-man track cycling event in which partners take turns to race round the track a number of times, and then must exchange places with a partner by means of a hand sling.
MADISON.zh: 两人场地自行车比赛，搭档轮流绕赛道比赛多次，然后必须通过手吊带与搭档交换位置。

JOY.en: A feeling of extreme happiness or cheerfulness, especially related to the acquisition or expectation of something good.
JOY.zh: 一种极度幸福或快乐的感觉，尤其与获得或期待美好事物有关。

EDITIONS.en: A written work edited and published, as by a certain editor or in a certain manner.
EDITIONS.zh: 由某个编辑或以某种方式编辑和出版的书面作品。

ETHNIC.en: An __ person, especially a foreigner or member of an immigrant community.
ETHNIC.zh: 少数民族，尤其是外国人或移民社区的成员。

ACTOR.en: A person who performs, plays a part in a theatrical play or film.
ACTOR.zh: 在戏剧或电影中表演、扮演角色的人。

FINDS.en: Anything that is found (usually valuable), as objects on an archeological site or a person with talent.
FINDS.zh: 任何发现的东西（通常是有价值的），如考古遗址上的物品或有才华的人。

SEAL.en: A pinniped (Pinnipedia), particularly an earless __ (true __) or eared __.
SEAL.zh: 鳍足类动物（Pinnipedia），特别是无耳海豹（真海豹）或有耳海豹。

FIFTH.en: The person or thing in the __ position.

PRIZE.en: That which is taken from another; something captured; a thing seized by force, stratagem, or superior power.
PRIZE.zh: 取自他人的；捕获的东西；用武力、计谋或上级力量夺取的东西。

ANYTIME.en: Suitable for any time; not associated with any particular time.
ANYTIME.zh: 适合任何时间；与任何特定时间无关。

LIES.en: The terrain and conditions surrounding the ball before it is struck.
LIES.zh: 击球前球周围的地形和条件。

PIPE.en: Meanings relating to a wind instrument.

SOLDIERS.en: A member of an army, of any rank.

LAYOUT.en: A structured arrangement of items within certain limits.
LAYOUT.zh: 在一定范围内对项目进行结构化排列。

ILL.zh: （通常为复数形式）麻烦；苦恼；不幸;逆境。

CLASSICS.en: A perfect and/or early example of a particular style.
CLASSICS.zh: 特定风格的完美和/或早期示例。

HORSES.en: Any of several animals related to Equus ferus caballus.
HORSES.zh: 与马属（Equus ferus caballus）有关的几种动物中的任何一种。

LOL.en: (British commonwealth) Loyal Orange Lodge, a prefix given to all branches of the Loyal Orange Order. For example, __ 1 is Portadown branch.
LOL.zh: （英联邦）忠诚橙色会社，忠诚橙色勋章所有分支的前缀。例如，__ 1是Portadown分支。

DECK.en: Any raised flat surface that can be walked on: a balcony; a porch; a raised patio; a flat rooftop.
DECK.zh: 任何可以行走的凸起平坦表面：阳台；门廊；一个凸起的露台；平坦的屋顶。

DONATE.en: To make a donation; to give away something of value to support or contribute towards a cause or for the benefit of another.
DONATE.zh: 捐款；捐赠一些有价值的东西来支持或为一项事业做出贡献或为了他人的利益。

TAUGHT.en: To show (someone) the way; to guide, conduct; to point, indicate.
TAUGHT.zh: 为（某人）指明道路；指导、进行；指出，表明。

WORKER.en: A person who performs labor for a living, especially manual labor.
WORKER.zh: 以劳动为生的人，尤其是体力劳动。

WINGS.en: An appendage of an animal's (bird, bat, insect) body that enables it to fly; a similar fin at the side of a ray or similar fish
WINGS.zh: 动物（鸟、蝙蝠、昆虫）身体的附属物，使其能够飞行；鳐鱼或类似鱼侧面的类似鳍

BREAKS.en: An instance of breaking something into two or more pieces.
BREAKS.zh: 将某物分成两块或更多块的实例。

WATERS.en: A substance (of molecular formula H₂O) found at room temperature and pressure as a clear liquid; it is present naturally as rain, and found in rivers, lakes and seas; its solid form is ice and its gaseous form is steam.
WATERS.zh: 在室温和压力下为透明液体的物质（分子式为 H2O）；它以雨的形式自然存在，存在于河流、湖泊和海洋中；它的固态形式是冰，气态形式是蒸汽。

THIN.en: A loss or tearing of paper from the back of a stamp, although not sufficient to create a complete hole.
THIN.zh: 邮票背面的纸张丢失或撕裂，但不足以形成完整的孔。

RIDGE.en: The back of any animal; especially the upper or projecting part of the back of a quadruped.
RIDGE.zh: 任何动物的背部；尤其是四足动物背部的上部或突出部分。

MODEM.en: A device that encodes digital computer signals into analog/analogue telephone signals and vice versa and allows computers to communicate over a phone line.
MODEM.zh: 一种将数字计算机信号编码为模拟/模拟电话信号（反之亦然）的设备，并允许计算机通过电话线进行通信。

SICK.en: __ people in general as a group.

TIFFANY.en: A kind of gauze, or very thin silk.
TIFFANY.zh: 一种纱布，或者说很薄的丝绸。

BET.en: A wager, an agreement __ween two parties that a stake (usually money) will be paid by the loser to the winner (the winner being the one who correctly forecast the outcome of an event).
BET.zh: 一种赌注，两方之间达成的协议，即输家将向赢家支付赌注（通常是金钱）（赢家是正确预测事件结果的人）。

STREETS.en: A paved part of road, usually in a village or a town.
STREETS.zh: 道路的一部分，通常位于村庄或城镇。

VECTOR.en: A directed quantity, one with both magnitude and direction; the signed difference between two points.
VECTOR.zh: 有向量，既有大小又有方向；两点之间的有符号差。

SHAVED.en: To make bald or shorter by using a tool such as a razor or pair of electric clippers to cut the hair close to the skin.
SHAVED.zh: 使用剃刀或电动推剪等工具将靠近皮肤的头发剪掉，从而使头发变秃或变短。

TURNING.en: (heading) to make a non-linear physical movement.

BUFFER.en: Of the color of buff leather, a brownish yellow.
BUFFER.zh: 浅黄色皮革的颜色，棕黄色。

DEF.en: __iciency in amount or quality; a falling short; lack.
DEF.zh: 数量或质量不足；达不到要求；缺少。

LETS.en: The allowing of possession of a property etc. in exchange for rent.
LETS.zh: 允许拥有财产等以换取租金。

SYNTAX.en: A set of rules that govern how words are combined to form phrases and sentences.
SYNTAX.zh: 一组规则，用于控制单词如何组合以形成短语和句子。

PRISON.en: A place or institution of confinement, especially of long-term confinement for those convicted of serious crimes or otherwise considered undesirable by the government.
PRISON.zh: 监禁的场所或机构，尤其是对那些犯有严重罪行或政府认为不受欢迎的人的长期监禁。

SKILL.en: Capacity to do something well; technique, ability. __s are usually acquired or learned, as opposed to abilities, which are often thought of as innate.
SKILL.zh: 做好某事的能力；技术，能力。技能通常是获得或学习的，而不是能力，而能力通常被认为是与生俱来的。

CHAIRS.en: An item of furniture used to sit on or in, comprising a seat, legs, back, and sometimes arm rests, for use by one person. Compare stool, couch, sofa, settee, loveseat and bench.
CHAIRS.zh: 一种用于坐在上面或里面的家具，包括座椅、腿、靠背，有时还有扶手，供一个人使用。比较凳子、沙发、沙发、长沙发、双人沙发和长凳。

EVERYDAY.en: (rare) the ordinary or routine day or occasion
EVERYDAY.zh: （罕见）普通或例行的日子或场合

MOVES.en: The act of moving; a movement.

INQUIRY.en: The act of inquiring; a seeking of information by asking questions; interrogation; a question or questioning.
INQUIRY.zh: 询问的行为；通过提问寻求信息；审讯；一个问题或疑问。

ETHERNET.en: A computer network that complies with this set of standards.
ETHERNET.zh: 符合这套标准的计算机网络。

TREND.en: An inclination in a particular direction.

CATS.en: An animal of the family Felidae:

OLDEST.en: Of an object, concept, relationship, etc., having existed for a relatively long period of time.
OLDEST.zh: 存在了相当长一段时间的对象、概念、关系等。

VICTIMS.en: One that is harmed—killed, injured, subjected to oppression, deceived, or otherwise adversely affected—by someone or something, especially another person or event, force, or condition; in particular:
VICTIMS.zh: 受到某人或某事，尤其是另一个人或事件、力量或状况的伤害（被杀、受伤、受到压迫、欺骗或其他不利影响）；尤其：

BURNING.en: To cause to be consumed by fire.

COUPONS.en: A section of a ticket, showing the holder to be entitled to some specified accommodation or service, as to a passage over a designated line of travel, a particular seat in a theater, a discount, etc.
COUPONS.zh: 机票的一部分，显示持有人有权享受某些指定的住宿或服务，如指定旅行线路的通行、剧院的特定座位、折扣等。

SOMEWHAT.en: More or less; a certain quantity or degree; a part, more or less; something.
SOMEWHAT.zh: 或多或少;一定数量或程度；或多或少的一部分；某物。

RECEIVER.en: A person who or thing that receives or is intended to receive something. More formal, usually referring to one who receives such things as an award or medal.
RECEIVER.zh: 接收或打算接收某物的人或物。更正式，通常指获得奖励或奖章等东西的人。

BOATS.en: A craft used for transportation of goods, fishing, racing, recreational cruising, or military use on or in the water, propelled by oars or outboard motor or inboard motor or by wind.
BOATS.zh: 用于水上或水中货物运输、钓鱼、竞赛、休闲巡航或军事用途的船只，由桨或舷外发动机或舷内发动机或风驱动。

TELLS.en: A reflexive, often habitual behavior, especially one occurring in a context that often features attempts at deception by persons under psychological stress (such as a poker game or police interrogation), that reveals information that the person exhibiting the behavior is attempting to withhold.
TELLS.zh: 一种反射性的、通常是习惯性的行为，尤其是在人们经常在心理压力下试图欺骗的情况下发生的行为（例如扑克游戏或警察审讯），它揭示了表现出行为的人试图隐瞒的信息。

FIBER.en: A single elongated piece of a given material, roughly round in cross-section, often twisted with other __s to form thread.
FIBER.zh: 给定材料的单个细长片，横截面大致为圆形，通常与其他纤维绞合以形成线。

GRAPH.en: (applied mathematics) A data chart (__ical representation of data) intended to illustrate the relationship between a set (or sets) of numbers (quantities, measurements or indicative numbers) and a reference set, whose elements are indexed to those of the former set(s) and may or may not be numbers.
GRAPH.zh: （应用数学）数据图表（数据的图形表示），旨在说明一组（或多组）数字（数量、测量值或指示性数字）与参考集之间的关系，其元素被索引到前一组的元素，并且可以是也可以不是数字。

COVERING.en: To place something over or upon, as to conceal or protect.
COVERING.zh: 将某物放置在上面或上面，以隐藏或保护。

PLATINUM.en: The chemical element with atomic number 78 and symbol Pt; a dense, malleable, ductile, highly unreactive, silverish-white transition metal of great value.
PLATINUM.zh: 原子序数78、符号Pt的化学元素；一种致密、有延展性、延展性、高度不反应、具有巨大价值的银白色过渡金属。

BEDROOMS.en: A room in a house where a bed is kept for sleeping.
BEDROOMS.zh: 房子里的一个房间，里面有一张床供睡觉。

TALKS.en: To communicate, usually by means of speech.
TALKS.zh: 沟通，通常是通过言语的方式。

FILING.en: To commit (official papers) to some office.
FILING.zh: 将（官方文件）提交给某个办公室。

MODELING.en: To display for others to see, especially in regard to wearing clothing while performing the role of a fashion model
MODELING.zh: 展示给别人看，特别是在扮演时装模特时穿着的衣服

AWARDED.en: To give by sentence or judicial determination; to assign or apportion, after careful regard to the nature of the case; to adjudge
AWARDED.zh: 通过判决或司法裁决作出；仔细考虑案件的性质后进行分配或分摊；判断

TRIALS.en: An opportunity to test something out; a test.
TRIALS.zh: 测试某些东西的机会；一个测试。

MASTERS.en: Someone who has control over something or someone.

BONDS.en: Evidence of a long-term debt, by which the bond issuer (the borrower) is obliged to pay interest when due, and repay the principal at maturity, as specified on the face of the bond certificate. The rights of the holder are specified in the bond indenture, which contains the legal terms and conditions under which the bond was issued. __ are available in two forms: registered __, and bearer __.
BONDS.zh: 债券发行人（借款人）有义务在到期时支付利息并在到期时偿还本金的长期债务的证据，如债券凭证表面所示。债券契约中规定了持有人的权利，其中包含发行债券的法律条款和条件。债券有两种形式：记名债券和不记名债券。

FOLK.en: A grouping of smaller peoples or tribes as a nation.
FOLK.zh: 一群较小的民族或部落作为一个国家。

COMMONS.en: Mutual good, shared by more than one.

FRAUD.en: The crime of stealing or otherwise illegally obtaining money by use of deception tactics.
FRAUD.zh: 采用欺骗手段盗窃或者以其他方式非法获取财物的犯罪。

SPECTRUM.en: A range; a continuous, infinite, one-dimensional set, possibly bounded by extremes.
SPECTRUM.zh: 一个范围；连续、无限、一维的集合，可能受极值限制。

ARRIVAL.en: The act of arriving or something that has arrived.
ARRIVAL.zh: 到达的行为或已经到达的东西。

POTTERY.en: Fired ceramic wares that contain clay when formed.
POTTERY.zh: 烧制的陶瓷制品在成型时含有粘土。

ROGER.en: (radio telecommunications) Received (used in radio communications to acknowledge that a message has been received and understood)
ROGER.zh: （无线电通讯）已接收（在无线电通信中用于确认已收到并理解消息）

AWESOME.en: Short for __ness: the quality, state, or essence of being __.
AWESOME.zh: __ness 的缩写：__ness 的品质、状态或本质。

COUNTS.en: The act of counting or tallying a quantity.
COUNTS.zh: 计算或统计数量的行为。

PRICED.en: To determine the monetary value of (an item); to put a price on.
PRICED.zh: 确定（物品）的货币价值；定价。

HIST.en: An instance of an exclamation attracting attention or injunction to be silent.
HIST.zh: 引起注意的感叹或要求保持沉默的例子。

CRASH.en: A sudden, intense, loud sound, as made for example by cymbals.
CRASH.zh: 突然、强烈、响亮的声音，例如铙钹发出的声音。

DESIRED.en: To want; to wish for earnestly.

ASSUMES.en: To authenticate by means of belief; to surmise; to suppose to be true, especially without proof
ASSUMES.zh: 通过信仰来验证；推测；假设是真的，尤其是在没有证据的情况下

HEIGHTS.en: The distance from the base of something to the top.
HEIGHTS.zh: 从某物的底部到顶部的距离。

SHADOW.en: A dark image projected onto a surface where light (or other radiation) is blocked by the shade of an object.
SHADOW.zh: 投影到光（或其他辐射）被物体的阴影阻挡的表面上的暗图像。

RIDING.en: To transport oneself by sitting on and directing a horse, later also a bicycle etc.
RIDING.zh: 通过坐在马上并指挥来运输自己，后来也骑自行车等。

CLINIC.en: A medical facility, such as a hospital, especially one for the treatment and diagnosis of outpatients.
CLINIC.zh: 医疗机构，例如医院，特指用于治疗和诊断门诊病人的机构。

HEALING.en: The process where the cells in the body regenerate and repair themselves.
HEALING.zh: 体内细胞再生和自我修复的过程。

PRINCESS.en: A female member of a royal family other than a queen, especially a daughter or granddaughter.
PRINCESS.zh: 王后以外的王室女性成员，尤其是女儿或孙女。

MALL.en: A pedestrianised street, especially a shopping precinct.

ENTERING.en: To go or come into an enclosed or partially enclosed space.
ENTERING.zh: 进入或进入封闭或部分封闭的空间。

PACKET.en: A small pack or package; a little bundle or parcel
PACKET.zh: 小包装或包裹；一小捆或包裹

SPRAY.en: A fine, gentle, dispersed mist of liquid.
SPRAY.zh: 细腻、温和、分散的液体雾。

STUDIOS.en: An artist’s or photographer’s workshop or the room in which an artist works.
STUDIOS.zh: 艺术家或摄影师的工作室或艺术家工作的房间。

DAD.zh: 一个父亲，一个男性父母。

BUTTONS.en: One who adjusts, especially for the insurance industry's employment title "loss adjuster" (or "claims adjuster" in the United States).
BUTTONS.zh: 一位进行调整的人，尤其是保险业的就业头衔“损失理算员”（或在美国为“索赔理算员”）。

WINNERS.en: One who has won or often wins.
WINNERS.zh: 曾经获胜或经常获胜的人。

ROADS.en: A way used for travelling between places, originally one wide enough to allow foot passengers and horses to travel, now (US) usually one surfaced with asphalt or concrete and designed to accommodate many vehicles travelling in both directions. In the UK both senses are heard: a country road is the same as a country lane.
ROADS.zh: 一种用于两地之间旅行的道路，最初宽度足以允许步行乘客和马匹行驶，现在（美国）通常铺有沥青或混凝土，设计用于容纳许多双向行驶的车辆。在英国，这两种含义都可以听到：乡村道路与乡村小路相同。

PAT.en: The sound of a light slap or tap with a soft flat object, especially of a footstep
PAT.zh: 用柔软的扁平物体轻轻拍打或敲击的声音，尤其是脚步声

ROLLING.en: To cause to revolve by turning over and over; to move by turning on an axis; to impel forward by causing to turn over and over on a supporting surface.
ROLLING.zh: 通过翻来覆去地引起旋转；通过绕轴转动来移动；通过在支撑面上翻来覆去推动前进。

YARD.en: A small, usually uncultivated area adjoining or (now especially) within the precincts of a house or other building.
YARD.zh: 毗邻房屋或其他建筑物或（现在特别是）房屋或其他建筑物范围内的通常未开垦的小区域。

MEMORIES.en: The ability of the brain to record information or impressions with the facility of recalling them later at will.
MEMORIES.zh: 大脑记录信息或印象并能在以后随意回忆的能力。

NELSON.en: A score of 111, sometimes considered to be unlucky.

ARRIVED.en: To reach; to get to a certain place.

CREATES.en: To bring into existence; (sometimes in particular:)

FACES.en: The front part of the head of a human or other animal, featuring the eyes, nose and mouth, and the surrounding area.
FACES.zh: 人类或其他动物头部的前部，包括眼睛、鼻子和嘴巴以及周围区域。

MAYOR.en: The chief executive of the municipal government of a city, borough, &c., formerly usually appointed as a caretaker by European royal courts but now usually appointed or elected locally.
MAYOR.zh: 城市、行政区等市政府的首席执行官，以前通常由欧洲皇家法院任命为看守人，但现在通常由当地任命或选举。

MURDER.en: The crime of deliberately killing another person without justification.
MURDER.zh: 无正当理由故意杀人罪。

SENATOR.en: A member, normally elected, in the house or chamber of a legislature called a senate. The legislatures of the United States and Canada have __s.
SENATOR.zh: 立法机关众议院或参议院中通常选举产生的成员，称为参议院。美国和加拿大的立法机关均设有参议员。

YIELD.en: To pay, give in payment; repay, recompense; reward; requite.
YIELD.zh: 付款，付款；偿还，报答；报酬;报答。

CARTOONS.en: A humorous drawing, often with a caption, or a strip of such drawings.
CARTOONS.zh: 一幅幽默的图画，通常带有标题，或者是这样的图画的一条。

LODGING.en: To be firmly fixed in a specified position.
LODGING.zh: 牢固地固定在指定位置。

HENCE.en: From here, from this place, away
HENCE.zh: 从这里，从这个地方，远离

WIKI.en: A collaborative website which can be directly edited merely by using a web browser, often by anyone with access to it.
WIKI.zh: 一种协作网站，只需使用网络浏览器即可直接编辑，通常由有权访问该网站的任何人进行编辑。

ENTIRELY.en: To the full or entire extent.

REPLACED.en: To restore to a former place, position, condition, etc.; to put back
REPLACED.zh: 恢复到以前的地点、位置、状况等；放回去

RADAR.en: A method of detecting distant objects and determining their position, velocity, or other characteristics by analysis of sent radio waves (usually microwaves) reflected from their surfaces
RADAR.zh: 一种通过分析从其表面反射的发送无线电波（通常是微波）来检测远处物体并确定其位置、速度或其他特征的方法

LOSSES.en: The result of no longer possessing an object, a function, or a characteristic due to external causes or misplacement.
LOSSES.zh: 由于外部原因或错误放置而不再拥有某个物体、功能或特性的结果。

REDUCING.en: To bring down the size, quantity, quality, value or intensity of something; to diminish, to lower.
REDUCING.zh: 降低某物的大小、数量、质量、价值或强度；减少，降低。

LAKES.en: A small stream of running water; a channel for water; a drain.
LAKES.zh: 一小股流水；水道；排水沟。

DIARY.en: A daily log of experiences, especially those of the writer.
DIARY.zh: 每日的经历日志，尤其是作者的经历。

KINGS.en: A male monarch; a man who heads a monarchy. If it's an absolute monarchy, then he is the supreme ruler of his nation.
KINGS.zh: 男性君主；领导君主政体的人。如果是绝对君主制，那么他就是国家的最高统治者。

ADDS.en: An act or instance of adding.

EAR.en: The organ of h__ing, consisting of the pinna, auditory canal, __drum, malleus, incus, stapes and cochlea.
EAR.zh: 听觉器官，由耳廓、耳道、鼓膜、锤骨、砧骨、镫骨和耳蜗组成。

FLAGS.en: A piece of cloth, often decorated with an emblem, used as a visual signal or symbol.
FLAGS.zh: 一块布，通常装饰有徽章，用作视觉信号或符号。

BAKER.en: A person who bakes and sells bread, cakes and similar items.
BAKER.zh: 烘焙和销售面包、蛋糕和类似物品的人。

LAUNCHED.en: To throw (a projectile such as a lance, dart or ball); to hurl; to propel with force.
LAUNCHED.zh: 投掷（射弹，如长矛、飞镖或球）；投掷；用力推动。

WALLS.en: A rampart of earth, stones etc. built up for defensive purposes.
WALLS.zh: 为防御目的而用土、石等筑成的城墙。

EBONY.en: A hard, dense, deep black wood from various subtropical and tropical trees, especially of the genus Diospyros.
EBONY.zh: 一种坚硬、致密、深黑色的木材，来自各种亚热带和热带树木，尤其是柿属树木。

WARD.en: A __en; a guard; a guardian or watchman.
WARD.zh: 典狱长；一名警卫；监护人或看守人。

VISITED.en: To habitually go to (someone in distress, sickness etc.) to comfort them. (Now generally merged into later senses, below.)
VISITED.zh: 习惯性地去（遇到困难、生病等的人）安慰他们。 （现在通常合并到后来的含义中，见下文。）

ROOF.en: The external covering at the top of a building.
ROOF.zh: 建筑物顶部的外部覆盖物。

WALKER.en: The agent noun of to walk: a person who walks or a thing which walks, especially a pedestrian or a participant in a walking race.
WALKER.zh: 行走的代理名词：行走的人或行走的物体，尤指行人或竞走比赛的参与者。

SUGGESTS.en: To imply but stop short of saying explicitly.

KISS.en: To touch with the lips or press the lips against, usually to show love or affection or passion, or as part of a greeting.
KISS.zh: 用嘴唇接触或用嘴唇按压，通常是为了表达爱、感情或激情，或作为问候的一部分。

BEAST.en: Any animal other than a human; usually only applied to land vertebrates, especially large or dangerous four-footed ones.
BEAST.zh: 除人类以外的任何动物；通常只适用于陆地脊椎动物，尤其是大型或危险的四足脊椎动物。

OPERATED.en: To perform a work or labour; to exert power or strength, physical or mechanical; to act.
OPERATED.zh: 进行工作或劳动；发挥物理或机械的力量或力量；采取行动。

TARGETS.en: A butt or mark to shoot at, as for practice, or to test the accuracy of a firearm, or the force of a projectile.
TARGETS.zh: 用来射击的枪托或标记，用于练习，或测试枪支的准确性或射弹的力量。

PIZZA.en: A baked Italian dish of a thinly rolled bread dough crust typically topped before baking with tomato sauce, cheese and other ingredients such as meat, vegetables or fruit
PIZZA.zh: 一种烘烤的意大利菜肴，由薄薄的面包面团皮制成，通常在烘烤前撒上番茄酱、奶酪和其他配料，如肉类、蔬菜或水果

INVITED.en: To ask for the presence or participation of someone or something.
INVITED.zh: 请求某人或某物在场或参与。

YARDS.en: A small, usually uncultivated area adjoining or (now especially) within the precincts of a house or other building.
YARDS.zh: 毗邻房屋或其他建筑物或（现在特别是）房屋或其他建筑物范围内的通常未开垦的小区域。

MOD.en: An unconventionally __ern style of fashionable dress originating in England in the 1960s, characterized by ankle-length black trenchcoats and sunglasses.
MOD.zh: 一种非传统的现代时装风格，起源于 20 世纪 60 年代的英国，其特点是长及脚踝的黑色风衣和太阳镜。

FARMERS.en: A person who works the land and/or who keeps livestock, especially on a farm.
FARMERS.zh: 耕种土地和/或饲养牲畜的人，尤其是在农场里的人。

QUERIES.en: A question, an inquiry (US), an enquiry (UK).
QUERIES.zh: 一个问题，一个询问（美国），一个询问（英国）。

RUSH.en: Any of several stiff plants of the genus Juncus, or the family Juncaceae, having hollow or pithy stems and small flowers, and often growing in marshes or near water.
RUSH.zh: 灯心草属或灯心草科的几种硬质植物的任何一种，具有中空或多髓的茎和小花，通常生长在沼泽地或水边。

VENDORS.en: A person or a company that vends or sells.
VENDORS.zh: 贩卖或销售的个人或公司。

WHEREAS.en: A clause, as in legal documents, stating __.
WHEREAS.zh: 法律文件中的一个子句，说明 while。

YOGA.en: Any of several Hindu or Buddhist disciplines aimed at training the consciousness for a state of perfect spiritual insight and tranquillity; especially a system of exercises practiced to promote control of the body and mind.
YOGA.zh: 旨在训练意识以达到完美的精神洞察力和宁静状态的印度教或佛教戒律中的任何一种；尤其是一套旨在促进身体和精神控制的练习系统。

SERVES.en: An act of putting the ball or shuttlecock in play in various games.
SERVES.zh: 在各种游戏中将球或毽子投入比赛的动作。

WOODS.en: The substance making up the central part of the trunk and branches of a tree. Used as a material for construction, to manufacture various items, etc. or as fuel.
WOODS.zh: 构成树干和树枝中心部分的物质。用作建筑材料、制造各种物品等或用作燃料。

LAMP.en: A device that generates heat, light or other radiation. Especially an electric light bulb.
LAMP.zh: 产生热、光或其他辐射的装置。尤其是电灯泡。

COUPLES.en: Two partners in a romantic or sexual relationship.
COUPLES.zh: 处于浪漫或性关系中的两个伙伴。

PALACE.en: Official residence of a head of state or other dignitary, especially in a monarchical or imperial governmental system.
PALACE.zh: 国家元首或其他贵宾的官邸，尤其是在君主制或帝国政府体系中。

VERIFY.en: To substantiate or prove the truth of something
VERIFY.zh: 证实或证明某事的真实性

GLOBE.zh: 任何球形（或接近球形）的物体。

TRUSTED.en: To place confidence in; to rely on, to confide, or have faith, in.
TRUSTED.zh: 建立信心；信赖、信赖或相信。

RACK.en: A series of one or more shelves, stacked one above the other
RACK.zh: 一系列一个或多个架子，一个一个地堆叠在一起

REP.en: To __resent; to act as a __resentative for.

SUPPOSED.en: To take for granted; to conclude, with less than absolute supporting data; to believe.
SUPPOSED.zh: 认为理所当然；得出结论，缺乏绝对的支持数据；相信。

NOBODY.en: Someone who is not important or well-known.

GHOST.en: The spirit; the soul of man.

APPLYING.en: To lay or place; to put (one thing to another)
APPLYING.zh: 铺设或放置；把（一件事放到另一件事上）

BOSS.en: A person who oversees and directs the work of others; a supervisor.
BOSS.zh: 监督和指导他人工作的人；一名主管。

PRIDE.en: The quality or state of being proud; an unreasonable overestimation of one's own superiority in terms of talents, looks, wealth, importance etc., which manifests itself in lofty airs, distance, reserve and often contempt of others.
PRIDE.zh: 自豪的品质或状态；对自己在才能、外貌、财富、重要性等方面的优越性的不合理的高估，表现为高傲、疏远、矜持以及常常蔑视他人。

KNOWING.en: To perceive the truth or factuality of; to be certain of or that.
KNOWING.zh: 感知以下事实的真相或事实；确定或那个。

CLOUDY.en: Covered with or characterised by clouds; overcast.
CLOUDY.zh: 被云覆盖或以云为特征的；灰蒙蒙。

CHILE.en: The pungent, spicy fresh or dried fruit of any of several cultivated varieties of capsicum peppers, used in cooking.
CHILE.zh: 几种辣椒栽培品种的辛辣新鲜或干果，用于烹饪。

ANNA.en: A unit of currency in former British India equal to 12 pies or 1/16 rupee.
ANNA.zh: 前英属印度的货币单位，等于 12 派或 1/16 卢比。

SOLO.en: A piece of music for one performer.
SOLO.zh: 为一位表演者创作的一首音乐。

SENTENCE.en: The decision or judgement of a jury or court; a verdict.
SENTENCE.zh: 陪审团或法院的决定或判决；一个判决。

THROAT.en: The front part of the neck.

MARIA.en: A large, dark plain, which may have the appearance of a sea.
MARIA.zh: 一大片黑暗的平原，看起来像大海。

WEALTH.zh: 财富；有价值的物质财产。

TALL.en: (possibly nonstandard) Someone or something that is __.
TALL.zh: （可能是非标准的）高的人或物。

VACUUM.en: A region of space that contains no matter.
VACUUM.zh: 不包含任何物质的空间区域。

DANCING.en: To move with rhythmic steps or movements, especially in time to music.
DANCING.zh: 以有节奏的步伐或动作移动，尤其是随着音乐的节奏移动。

BRASS.en: A metallic alloy of copper and zinc used in many industrial and plumbing applications.
BRASS.zh: 一种铜和锌的金属合金，用于许多工业和管道应用。

WRITES.en: The act or style of writing.

OUTCOMES.en: That which is produced or occurs as a result of an event or process.
OUTCOMES.zh: 由于事件或过程而产生或发生的事物。

SURVIVAL.en: The fact or act of surviving; continued existence or life.
SURVIVAL.zh: 幸存的事实或行为；继续存在或生命。

QUEST.en: A journey or effort in pursuit of a goal (often lengthy, ambitious, or fervent); a mission.
QUEST.zh: 追求目标的旅程或努力（通常是漫长的、雄心勃勃的或热情的）；一个使命。

PUBLISH.en: To issue (something, such as printed work) for distribution and/or sale.
PUBLISH.zh: 发行（某物，例如印刷作品）以供分发和/或销售。

TOE.en: Each of the five digits on the end of the foot.
TOE.zh: 脚末端的五个数字中的每一个。

TRANS.en: To cross from one side to another of (gender, sex or something in that vein).
TRANS.zh: 从（性别、性别或类似的东西）的一侧跨越到另一侧。

JONATHAN.en: An instrument used by smokers to light pipes
JONATHAN.zh: 吸烟者用来点燃烟斗的仪器

WHENEVER.en: (interrogative) When ever: emphatic form of when.

NOVA.en: Any sudden brightening of a previously inconspicuous star.
NOVA.zh: 以前不显眼的恒星突然变亮。

BOOTY.en: A form of prize which, when a ship was captured at sea, could be distributed at once.
BOOTY.zh: 一种战利品，当一艘船在海上被俘获时，可以立即分发。

ACROBAT.en: An athlete who performs acts requiring skill, agility and coordination.
ACROBAT.zh: 执行需要技巧、敏捷性和协调性的动作的运动员。

PLATES.en: A slightly curved but almost flat dish from which food is served or eaten.
PLATES.zh: 稍微弯曲但几乎平坦的盘子，用于盛放或食用食物。

ACRES.en: An English unit of land area (symbol: a. or ac.) originally denoting a day's plowing for a yoke of oxen, now standardized as 4,840 square yards or 4,046.86 square meters.
ACRES.zh: 一种英国土地面积单位（符号：a. 或 ac.），最初表示一轭牛一天的犁耕量，现在标准化为 4,840 平方码或 4,046.86 平方米。

VENUE.en: A theater, auditorium, arena, or other area designated for sporting or entertainment events.
VENUE.zh: 剧院、礼堂、竞技场或其他指定用于体育或娱乐活动的区域。

THERMAL.en: A column of rising air in the lower atmosphere created by uneven heating of Earth's surface.
THERMAL.zh: 由于地球表面加热不均匀而在低层大气中形成的上升空气柱。

ESSAYS.en: (authorship) A written composition of moderate length, exploring a particular issue or subject.
ESSAYS.zh: （作者身份）长度适中的书面作品，探讨特定问题或主题。

VITAL.en: Relating to, or characteristic of life.
VITAL.zh: 与生活有关或具有生活特征。

TELLING.en: (archaic outside of idioms) To count, reckon, or enumerate.
TELLING.zh: （习语之外的古语）计数、推算或列举。

FAIRLY.en: (manner) In a fair manner; fair; not biased or skewed or favouring a certain party
FAIRLY.zh: （方式）以公平的方式；公平的;不存在偏见、扭曲或偏袒某一方

COASTAL.en: Relating to the coast; on or near the coast, as a __ town, a __ breeze
COASTAL.zh: 与海岸有关；在海岸上或海岸附近，作为一个沿海城镇，吹着沿海的微风

CHARITY.en: An organization, the objective of which is to carry out a charitable purpose.
CHARITY.zh: 一个组织，其目标是实现慈善目的。

EXCEL.en: To surpass someone or something; to be better or do better than someone or something.
EXCEL.zh: 超越某人或某事；比某人或某事更好或做得更好。

MODES.en: One of several ancient Greek scales.

WAKE.en: The act of waking, or state of being a__.
WAKE.zh: 醒来的行为，或清醒的状态。

STUPID.zh: 一个愚蠢的人；一个傻瓜。

TRAVELER.en: A member of a particular nomadic ethnic minority in Ireland, the Pavee.
TRAVELER.zh: 爱尔兰特定游牧少数民族帕维人的成员。

REALIZE.en: To make real; to convert from the imaginary or fictitious into reality; to bring into real existence
REALIZE.zh: 使之成为现实；从想象或虚构转变为现实；变为现实存在

ENEMY.en: Someone who is hostile to, feels hatred towards, opposes the interests of, or intends injury to someone else.
ENEMY.zh: 对他人怀有敌意、仇恨、反对他人利益或意图伤害他人的人。

RISING.en: To move, or appear to move, physically upwards relative to the ground.
RISING.zh: 相对于地面物理向上移动或看似移动。

ALUMINUM.en: A metallic chemical element (symbol Al) with an atomic number of 13.
ALUMINUM.zh: 原子序数为13的金属化学元素（符号Al）。

WELLS.en: A hole sunk into the ground as a source of water, oil, natural gas or other fluids.
WELLS.zh: 沉入地下的洞，作为水、石油、天然气或其他液体的来源。

OPENS.en: To make something accessible or allow for passage by moving from a shut position.
OPENS.zh: 通过从关闭位置移动来使某物可接近或允许通过。

SECRETS.en: A piece of knowledge that is hidden and intended to be kept hidden.
SECRETS.zh: 一种被隐藏并且旨在被隐藏的知识。

LUCKY.en: (of people) Favoured by luck; fortunate; having good success or good fortune
LUCKY.zh: （人）受到幸运的眷顾；幸运;拥有良好的成功或好运

LATTER.en: Relating to or being the second of two items.
LATTER.zh: 与两项有关或属于两项中的第二项。

THICK.en: The __est, or most active or intense, part of something.
THICK.zh: 某事物最厚、或最活跃或最强烈的部分。

TRAILERS.en: Someone who or something that trails.

SYNDROME.en: A recognizable pattern of signs, symptoms and/or behaviours, especially of a disease or medical or psychological condition.
SYNDROME.zh: 一种可识别的体征、症状和/或行为模式，尤其是疾病或医疗或心理状况的体征、症状和/或行为模式。

DRUM.en: A percussive musical instrument spanned with a thin covering on at least one end for striking, forming an acoustic chamber, affecting what materials are used to make it; a membranophone.
DRUM.zh: 一种打击乐器，至少一端有一层薄覆盖物用于敲击，形成一个声室，影响其制造材料；薄膜电话。

ENABLES.en: To make somebody able (to do, or to be, something); to give sufficient ability or power to do or to be; to give strength or ability to.
ENABLES.zh: 使某人能够（做某事或成为某事）；给予足够的能力或权力去做或成为；给予力量或能力。

BUILDER.en: A person who builds or constructs things.

VISTA.en: A distant view or prospect, especially one seen through some opening, avenue or passage.
VISTA.zh: 远处的景象或前景，尤其是通过某个开口、大道或通道看到的景象或前景。

CHIPS.en: A small piece broken from a larger piece of solid material.
CHIPS.zh: 从大块固体材料上折下的小块。

TERRY.en: A type of coarse cotton fabric covered in many small raised loops that is used to make towels, bathrobes and some types of nappy/diaper.
TERRY.zh: 一种覆盖有许多小凸起环的粗棉织物，用于制作毛巾、浴袍和某些类型的尿布/尿布。

FLOOD.en: A (usually disastrous) overflow of water from a lake or other body of water due to excessive rainfall or other input of water.
FLOOD.zh: 由于过量降雨或其他水输入，导致湖泊或其他水体的水溢出（通常是灾难性的）。

EASE.en: Ability, the means to do something, particularly:
EASE.zh: 能力，做某事的手段，特别是：

ARENA.en: An enclosed area, often outdoor, for the presentation of sporting events (sports __) or other spectacular events; earthen area, often oval, specifically for rodeos (North America) or circular area for bullfights (especially Hispanic America).
ARENA.zh: 用于举办体育赛事（运动场）或其他壮观活动的封闭区域，通常为室外；土质区域，通常为椭圆形，专门用于牛仔竞技（北美）或圆形区域用于斗牛（尤其是西班牙裔美洲）。

PUPILS.en: A learner under the supervision of a teacher or professor.
PUPILS.zh: 在教师或教授的监督下学习的学生。

TABS.en: A small flap or strip of material attached to something, for holding, manipulation, identification, opening etc.
TABS.zh: 附着在某物上的小翼片或材料条，用于固定、操纵、识别、打开等。

OUTCOME.en: That which is produced or occurs as a result of an event or process.
OUTCOME.zh: 由于事件或过程而产生或发生的事物。

EXPANDED.en: To change (something) from a smaller form and/or size to a larger one; to spread out or lay open.
EXPANDED.zh: 将（某物）从较小的形式和/或尺寸更改为较大的形式和/或尺寸；展开或摊开。

CASUAL.en: A worker who is only working for a company occasionally, not as its permanent employee.
CASUAL.zh: 只偶尔为公司工作而不是永久雇员的工人。

GROWN.en: To become larger, to increase in magnitude.

LOVELY.en: An attractive, __ person, especially a (professional) beauty.
LOVELY.zh: 一个有魅力、可爱的人，尤其是（职业）美女。

EXTRAS.en: Something additional, such as an item above and beyond the ordinary school curriculum, or added to the usual charge on a bill.
EXTRAS.zh: 额外的东西，例如超出普通学校课程的项目，或添加到账单上的通常费用中。

CENTRES.en: The point in the interior of a circle that is equidistant from all points on the circumference.
CENTRES.zh: 圆内部与圆周上所有点距离相等的点。

CLAUSE.en: (grammar) A verb, its necessary grammatical arguments, and any adjuncts affecting them.
CLAUSE.zh: （语法）动词、其必要的语法参数以及影响它们的任何修饰语。

SMILE.en: A facial expression comprised by flexing the muscles of both ends of one's mouth, often showing the front teeth, without vocalisation, and in humans is a common involuntary or voluntary expression of happiness, pleasure, amusement or anxiety.
SMILE.zh: 通过弯曲嘴部两端的肌肉而形成的面部表情，通常露出门牙，但不发声，在人类中是幸福、快乐、娱乐或焦虑的常见非自愿或自愿表达。

LANDS.en: The part of Earth which is not covered by oceans or other bodies of water.
LANDS.zh: 地球上未被海洋或其他水体覆盖的部分。

TROOPS.en: (collective) A collection of people; a number; a multitude (in general).
TROOPS.zh: （集体）人的集合；一个数字；众多（一般而言）。

INDOOR.en: Situated in, or designed to be used in, or carried on within, the interior of a building.
INDOOR.zh: 位于建筑物内部，或设计用于建筑物内部，或在建筑物内部进行。

ARMED.en: To take by the arm; to take up in one's arms.

CHARGER.en: A device that charges or recharges

BELIEVED.en: To accept as true, particularly without absolute certainty (i.e., as opposed to knowing)
BELIEVED.zh: 接受为真实，特别是在没有绝对确定性的情况下（即，与知道相对）

PINE.en: Any coniferous tree of the genus Pinus.

COOLING.en: To lose heat, to get colder.

TEND.en: (Old English law) To make a __er of; to offer or __er.

GULF.en: A hollow place in the earth; an abyss; a deep chasm or basin.
GULF.zh: 地球上的一个空心地方；深渊；深渊或盆地。

RICK.en: Straw, hay etc. stored in a stack for winter fodder, commonly protected with thatch.
RICK.zh: 稻草、干草等堆放起来作为冬季饲料，通常用茅草保护。

TRUCKS.en: A small wheel or roller, specifically the wheel of a gun carriage.
TRUCKS.zh: 小轮子或滚轮，特指炮架的轮子。

DIVORCE.en: The legal dissolution of a marriage.

PARTLY.en: In part, or to some degree, but not completely.
PARTLY.zh: 部分地，或在某种程度上，但不完全。

CANDY.en: Edible, sweet-tasting confectionery containing sugar, or sometimes artificial sweeteners, and often flavored with fruit, chocolate, nuts, herbs and spices, or artificial flavors.
CANDY.zh: 含有糖或有时含有人造甜味剂的可食用甜味糖果，通常用水果、巧克力、坚果、香草和香料或人造香料调味。

PILLS.en: A small, usually round or cylindrical object designed for easy swallowing, usually containing some sort of medication.
PILLS.zh: 一种小的、通常为圆形或圆柱形的物体，设计为易于吞咽，通常含有某种药物。

TIGER.en: Panthera tigris, a large predatory mammal of the cat family, indigenous to Asia.
TIGER.zh: 虎（Panthera tigris），猫科大型食肉哺乳动物，原产于亚洲。

FOLKS.en: A grouping of smaller peoples or tribes as a nation.
FOLKS.zh: 一群较小的民族或部落作为一个国家。

SENSOR.en: A device or organ that detects certain external stimuli and responds in a distinctive manner.
SENSOR.zh: 检测某些外部刺激并以独特方式做出反应的装置或器官。

EXPOSED.en: To reveal, uncover, make visible, bring to light, introduce to.
EXPOSED.zh: 揭示、揭露、使可见、暴露、介绍。

ANGELS.en: An incorporeal and sometimes divine messenger from a deity, or other divine entity, often depicted in art as a youthful winged figure in flowing robes.
ANGELS.zh: 来自神灵或其他神圣实体的无形的、有时是神圣的使者，在艺术中经常被描绘成穿着飘逸长袍的年轻有翼人物。

DEPUTY.en: One appointed as the substitute of another, and empowered to act for them, in their name or their behalf; a substitute in office
DEPUTY.zh: 一个人被任命为另一个人的替代者，并被授权以他们的名义或代表他们行事；办公室替补

LOADED.en: To put a load on or in (a means of conveyance or a place of storage).
LOADED.zh: 将负载放置在（运输工具或储存地点）上或内部。

SCENES.en: The location of an event that attracts attention.
SCENES.zh: 引起注意的事件的地点。

BOOST.en: A push from behind, as to one who is endeavoring to climb.
BOOST.zh: 从后面推一推，就像对一个正在努力攀登的人一样。

SPANKING.en: To beat, smack or slap a person's buttocks, with the bare hand or other object, as punishment, gesture, or form of sexual interaction.
SPANKING.zh: 徒手或其他物体殴打、拍打或拍打某人的臀部，作为惩罚、手势或性互动形式。

MILL.en: A grinding apparatus for substances such as grains, seeds, etc.
MILL.zh: 用于谷物、种子等物质的研磨设备。

ICONS.en: An image, symbol, picture, or other representation usually as an object of religious devotion.
ICONS.zh: 通常作为宗教信仰对象的图像、符号、图片或其他表示形式。

MORAL.en: (of a narrative) The ethical significance or practical lesson.
MORAL.zh: （叙述的）伦理意义或实践教训。

DEN.en: A small cavern or hollow place in the side of a hill, or among rocks; especially, a cave used by a wild animal for shelter or concealment.
DEN.zh: 山坡上或岩石间的小洞穴或凹处；特别是野生动物用来庇护或隐藏的洞穴。

KEEPS.en: The main tower of a castle or fortress, located within the castle walls.
KEEPS.zh: 城堡或要塞的主塔，位于城堡墙内。

POUND.en: A unit of mass equal to 16 avoirdupois ounces (= 453.592 37 g). Today this value is the most common meaning of "__" as a unit of weight.
POUND.zh: 质量单位，等于 16 常衡盎司 (= 453.592 37 g)。今天，这个值是“磅”作为重量单位的最常见含义。

LOCATE.en: To place; to set in a particular spot or position.
LOCATE.zh: 放置；设置在特定的地点或位置。

BURN.en: A physical injury caused by heat, cold, electricity, radiation or caustic chemicals.
BURN.zh: 由热、冷、电、辐射或腐蚀性化学物质引起的身体伤害。

ROSES.en: A shrub of the genus Rosa, with red, pink, white or yellow flowers.
ROSES.zh: 蔷薇属灌木，开红色、粉红色、白色或黄色的花。

BREAD.en: A foodstuff made by baking dough made from cereals.
BREAD.zh: 将谷物制成的面团烘烤而成的食品。

TOBACCO.en: Any plant of the genus Nicotiana.

MOTORS.en: A machine or device that converts other energy forms into mechanical energy, or imparts motion.
MOTORS.zh: 将其他能量形式转换为机械能或传递运动的机器或装置。

TOUGH.en: A person who obtains things by force; a thug or bully.
TOUGH.zh: 以武力获取东西的人；暴徒或恶霸。

DYNAMICS.en: The branch of mechanics that is concerned with the effects of forces on the motion of objects.
DYNAMICS.zh: 力学的一个分支，研究力对物体运动的影响。

LIE.en: The terrain and conditions surrounding the ball before it is struck.
LIE.zh: 击球前球周围的地形和条件。

CHEST.en: A box, now usually a large strong box with a secure convex lid.
CHEST.zh: 一个盒子，现在通常是一个带有安全凸形盖子的大而坚固的盒子。

REVENUES.en: The income returned by an investment.

WORSHIP.en: The condition of being worthy; honour, distinction.
WORSHIP.zh: 有价值的条件；荣誉，区别。

HERSELF.en: (reflexive pronoun) Her; the female object of a verb or preposition that also appears as the subject.
HERSELF.zh: （反身代词）她；也作为主语出现的动词或介词的女性宾语。

CHURCHES.en: A Christian house of worship; a building where Christian religious services take place.
CHURCHES.zh: 基督教礼拜堂；举行基督教宗教仪式的建筑。

DAMAGES.en: To impair the soundness, goodness, or value of; to harm or cause destruction.
DAMAGES.zh: 损害以下各项的健全性、良好性或价值；伤害或造成破坏。

SOLVE.en: (chiefly law enforcement) A solution; an explanation.
SOLVE.zh: （主要是执法部门）解决方案；一个解释。

MINORITY.en: The state of being a minor; youth, the period of a person's life prior to reaching adulthood.
MINORITY.zh: 未成年人的状态；青年时期，是一个人成年之前的生命时期。

DIVERSE.en: Consisting of many different elements; various.
DIVERSE.zh: 由许多不同的元素组成；各种各样的。

SOLE.en: A wooden band or yoke put around the neck of an ox or cow in the stall.
SOLE.zh: 牛栏里套在牛脖子上的木带或轭。

RECORDER.en: An apparatus for recording; a device which records.
RECORDER.zh: 一种记录装置；记录的设备。

FACING.en: (of a person or animal) To position oneself or itself so as to have one's face closest to (something).
FACING.zh: （人或动物）调整自己或自己的位置，使脸最靠近（某物）。

NANCY.en: An effeminate man, especially a homosexual.
NANCY.zh: 女性化的男人，尤其是同性恋。

PASSION.en: Any great, strong, powerful emotion, especially romantic love or extreme hate.
PASSION.zh: 任何伟大、强烈、有力的情感，尤其是浪漫的爱情或极端的仇恨。

SIGHT.en: (in the singular) The ability to see.

LAID.en: (of paper) Marked with parallel lines, as if ribbed, from wires in the mould.
LAID.zh: （纸质）用模具中的电线标记出平行线，就好像有肋骨一样。

CLAY.en: A mineral substance made up of small crystals of silica and alumina, that is ductile when moist; the material of pre-fired ceramics.
CLAY.zh: 一种由二氧化硅和氧化铝小晶体组成的矿物质，潮湿时具有延展性；预烧陶瓷的材料。

DEFENCE.en: The action of defending, of protecting from attack, danger or injury.
DEFENCE.zh: 防御、保护免受攻击、危险或伤害的行为。

PATCHES.en: A piece of cloth, or other suitable material, sewed or otherwise fixed upon a garment to repair or strengthen it, especially upon an old garment to cover a hole.
PATCHES.zh: 一块布或其他合适的材料，缝制或以其他方式固定在衣服上以修复或加固它，特别是在旧衣服上以覆盖破洞。

WEAK.en: Lacking in force (usually strength) or ability.
WEAK.zh: 缺乏力量（通常是力量）或能力。

TOWNS.en: A settlement; an area with residential districts, shops and amenities, and its own local government; especially one larger than a village and smaller than a city.
TOWNS.zh: 和解；拥有住宅区、商店和便利设施以及当地政府的区域；尤其是比村庄大而比城市小的一个。

DIVIDED.en: To split or separate (something) into two or more parts.
DIVIDED.zh: 将（某物）分裂或分离成两个或多个部分。

EMAILS.en: A system for transferring messages from one computer to another, usually through a network.
EMAILS.zh: 通常通过网络将消息从一台计算机传输到另一台计算机的系统。

INSIDER.en: A person who has special knowledge about the inner workings of a group, organization, or institution.
INSIDER.zh: 对团体、组织或机构的内部运作有特殊了解的人。

SEMINARS.en: A class held for advanced studies in which students meet regularly to discuss original research, under the guidance of a professor.
SEMINARS.zh: 为高级研究而举办的课程，学生在教授的指导下定期聚会讨论原创研究。

MAKERS.en: Someone who makes; a person or thing that makes or produces something.
MAKERS.zh: 制造的人；制造或生产某物的人或物。

HEARTS.en: A muscular organ that pumps blood through the body, traditionally thought to be the seat of emotion.
HEARTS.zh: 一种将血液泵入全身的肌肉器官，传统上被认为是情绪的所在地。

EVE.en: The day or night before, usually used for holidays, such as Christmas __.
EVE.zh: 前一天或前一天晚上，通常用于假期，例如平安夜。

LEGACY.en: Money or property bequeathed to someone in a will.
LEGACY.zh: 在遗嘱中遗赠给某人的金钱或财产。

MARC.en: The refuse matter that remains after fruit, particularly grapes, has been pressed.
MARC.zh: 水果（尤其是葡萄）被压榨后留下的垃圾。

PLEASED.en: To make happy or satisfy; to give pleasure to.
PLEASED.zh: 使快乐或满足；给予快乐。

VITAMIN.en: Any of a specific group of organic compounds essential in small quantities for healthy human growth, metabolism, development, and body function; found in minute amounts in plant and animal foods or sometimes produced synthetically; deficiencies of specific __s produce specific disorders.
VITAMIN.zh: 任何对人类健康生长、新陈代谢、发育和身体功能至关重要的少量特定有机化合物；存在于植物和动物食品中或有时合成生产的微量；特定维生素的缺乏会产生特定的疾病。

WIDELY.en: In a wide manner; across a wide area.
WIDELY.zh: 广泛地；跨越广阔的区域。

PHRASE.en: A short written or spoken expression.
PHRASE.zh: 简短的书面或口头表达。

RAISING.en: (physical) To cause to rise; to lift or elevate.
RAISING.zh: （身体上的）引起上升；举起或举起。

PARADISE.en: The place where sanctified souls are believed to live after death.
PARADISE.zh: 人们相信神圣的灵魂死后居住的地方。

HYBRID.en: Offspring resulting from cross-breeding different entities, e.g. two different species or two purebred parent strains.
HYBRID.zh: 不同实体杂交产生的后代，例如两个不同的物种或两个纯种亲本品系。

READS.en: A reading or an act of reading, especially an actor's part of a play.
READS.zh: 阅读或阅读的行为，尤指戏剧中演员的部分。

ROLES.en: A character or part played by a performer or actor.
ROLES.zh: 表演者或演员扮演的角色或角色。

LEAF.en: The usually green and flat organ that represents the most prominent feature of most vegetative plants.
LEAF.zh: 通常是绿色且扁平的器官，代表大多数营养植物最显着的特征。

PAD.en: A flattened mass of anything soft, to sit or lie on.
PAD.zh: 任何柔软的东西的扁平物体，可以坐或躺。

GLORY.en: Great or overwhelming beauty or splendour.
GLORY.zh: 伟大或压倒性的美丽或辉煌。

BILLING.en: To dig, chop, etc., with a bill.
BILLING.zh: 用钞票进行挖掘、砍伐等。

DIESEL.en: A fuel derived from petroleum (or other oils) but heavier than gasoline/petrol. Used to power __ engines which burn this fuel using the heat produced when air is compressed.
DIESEL.zh: 源自石油（或其他油）但比汽油/汽油重的燃料。用于为柴油发动机提供动力，柴油发动机利用空气压缩时产生的热量燃烧这种燃料。

ROD.en: A straight, round stick, shaft, bar, cane, or staff.
ROD.zh: 直的、圆的棍子、轴、杆、手杖或杖。

FAULT.en: A defect; something that detracts from perfection.

SILK.en: A fine fiber excreted by the __worm or other arthropod (such as a spider).
SILK.zh: 蚕或其他节肢动物（如蜘蛛）分泌的细纤维。

BABIES.en: A very young human, particularly from birth to a couple of years old or until walking is fully mastered.
BABIES.zh: 一个非常年轻的人，特别是从出生到几岁或直到完全掌握行走为止。

COMPILED.en: To put together; to assemble; to make by gathering things from various sources.
COMPILED.zh: 放在一起；组装；通过从不同来源收集东西来制作。

ROMANTIC.en: Of or dealing with languages or cultures derived from Roman influence and Latin: Italian, French, Portuguese, Spanish, Romanian, Catalan, Occitan, Corsican, etc.
ROMANTIC.zh: 涉及或涉及受罗马和拉丁语影响的语言或文化：意大利语、法语、葡萄牙语、西班牙语、罗马尼亚语、加泰罗尼亚语、奥克西唐语、科西嘉语等。

REVEALED.en: To uncover; to show and display that which was hidden.
REVEALED.zh: 揭开；显示和显示隐藏的内容。

JIMMY.en: (especially New England and Philadelphia) Chocolate sprinkles used as a topping for ice cream, cookies, or cupcakes.
JIMMY.zh: （尤其是新英格兰和费城）用作冰淇淋、饼干或纸杯蛋糕配料的巧克力粒。

GRAHAM.en: Flour made by grinding wheat berries including the bran.
GRAHAM.zh: 通过研磨包括麸皮在内的小麦浆果制成的面粉。

SAD.en: To make melancholy; to __den or grieve (someone).
SAD.zh: 使人忧郁；使（某人）悲伤或悲伤。

WOLF.en: The gray __, specifically all subspecies of the gray __ (Canis lupus) that are not dingoes or dogs.
WOLF.zh: 灰狼，特别是除野狗或狗以外的灰狼（Canis lupus）的所有亚种。

RUGBY.en: (usually uncountable) A form of football in which players can hold or kick an ovoid ball. The ball cannot be handled forwards and points are scored by touching the ball to the ground in the area past their opponent’s territory or kicking the ball between goalposts and over a crossbar.
RUGBY.zh: （通常不可数）一种足球形式，球员可以握住或踢卵形球。不能向前控球，通过将球触地越过对手领土的区域或将球踢到球门柱之间并越过横梁来得分。

CAL.en: Diameter of the bore of a firearm, typi__ly measured between opposite lands.
CAL.zh: 枪支枪膛的直径，通常在相对的陆地之间测量。

INFANT.en: A very young human being, from birth to somewhere between six months and two years of age, needing almost constant care and/or attention.
INFANT.zh: 一个非常年轻的人，从出生到六个月到两岁之间，需要几乎持续的护理和/或关注。

FLUID.en: Any substance which can flow with relative ease, tends to assume the shape of its container, and obeys Bernoulli's principle; a liquid, gas or plasma.
FLUID.zh: 任何可以相对轻松流动的物质，都倾向于呈现其容器的形状，并遵循伯努利原理；液体、气体或等离子体。

GROUNDS.en: The surface of the Earth, as opposed to the sky or water or underground.
GROUNDS.zh: 地球表面，而不是天空、水或地下。

KICK.en: A hit or strike with the leg, foot or knee.
KICK.zh: 用腿、脚或膝盖击打或打击。

MEAL.en: Food that is prepared and eaten, usually at a specific time, and usually in a comparatively large quantity (as opposed to a snack).
MEAL.zh: 通常在特定时间准备和食用的食物，并且通常数量相对较多（而不是零食）。

HURT.en: An emotional or psychological humiliation or bad experience.
HURT.zh: 情感或心理上的羞辱或糟糕的经历。

UNLIKE.en: Something that is not like something else; something different.
UNLIKE.zh: 与其他事物不同的事物；不同的东西。

BASKETS.en: A lightweight container, generally round, open at the top, and tapering toward the bottom.
BASKETS.zh: 一种轻质容器，通常为圆形，顶部开口，朝底部逐渐变细。

POT.en: A flat-bottomed vessel (usually metal) used for cooking food.
POT.zh: 用于烹饪食物的平底容器（通常是金属）。

WRIGHT.en: A builder or maker of something.
WRIGHT.zh: 某物的建造者或制造者。

BARRY.en: A field divided transversely into several equal parts, and consisting of two different tinctures interchangeably disposed.
BARRY.zh: 横向分成几个相等部分的区域，由可互换放置的两种不同的酊剂组成。

WARREN.en: The system of burrows where rabbits live.

SLIP.en: A thin, __pery mix of clay and water.
SLIP.zh: 粘土和水的稀薄、光滑的混合物。

STUDIED.zh: 练习过；有自我意识；小心。

REVIEWER.en: A person who writes reviews for a newspaper or other publication; a critic.
REVIEWER.zh: 为报纸或其他出版物撰写评论的人；批评家。

INVOLVES.en: To roll or fold up; to wind round; to entwine.
INVOLVES.zh: 卷起或折叠起来；绕圈；缠绕。

PROFITS.en: Total income or cash flow minus expenditures. The money or other benefit a non-governmental organization or individual receives in exchange for products and services sold at an advertised price.
PROFITS.zh: 总收入或现金流量减去支出。非政府组织或个人以广告价格出售产品和服务而获得的金钱或其他利益。

GRASS.en: Any plant of the family Poaceae, characterized by leaves that arise from nodes in the stem and leaf bases that wrap around the stem, especially those grown as ground cover rather than for grain.
GRASS.zh: 任何禾本科植物，其特征是叶子从茎节上长出，叶基部包裹着茎，特别是那些作为地被植物而不是谷物种植的植物。

COMPLY.en: To yield assent; to accord; to acquiesce, agree, consent; to adapt oneself, to conform.
COMPLY.zh: 表示同意；一致；默许、同意、同意；使自己适应，顺从。

CHERRY.en: A small fruit, usually red, black or yellow, with a smooth hard seed and a short hard stem.
CHERRY.zh: 一种小果实，通常为红色、黑色或黄色，有光滑坚硬的种子和短而坚硬的茎。

WEBCAM.en: A video camera whose output may be viewed in real time over a computer network, especially over the World Wide Web.
WEBCAM.zh: 一种摄像机，其输出可以通过计算机网络（尤其是万维网）实时查看。

FUNERAL.en: A ceremony to honour and remember a deceased person. Often distinguished from a memorial service by the presence of the body of the deceased.
FUNERAL.zh: 纪念和纪念死者的仪式。通常与追悼会的区别在于死者尸体的存在。

EARRINGS.en: A piece of jewelry worn on the ear.

ENJOYED.en: To receive pleasure or satisfaction from something
ENJOYED.zh: 从某事中获得快乐或满足

CHAPTERS.en: (authorship) One of the main sections into which the text of a book is divided.
CHAPTERS.zh: （作者身份）一本书的文本分为的主要部分之一。

CHARLIE.en: An enemy; the Vietcong; short for Victor __.
CHARLIE.zh: 一个敌人；越共；维克多·查理的缩写。

TVS.en: The assessed value of an asset from which the tax owing is computed.
TVS.zh: 计算欠税的资产的评估价值。

SIZED.en: To adjust the size of; to make a certain size.
SIZED.zh: 调整大小；来制作一定的尺寸。

SOCKET.en: An opening into which a plug or other connecting part is designed to fit (e.g. a light bulb __).
SOCKET.zh: 设计用于插入插头或其他连接部件（例如灯泡插座）的开口。

EGG.en: An approximately spherical or ellipsoidal body produced by birds, reptiles, insects and other animals, housing the embryo during its development.
EGG.zh: 由鸟类、爬行动物、昆虫和其他动物产生的近似球形或椭圆体，在发育过程中容纳胚胎。

SIGNALS.en: A sequence of states representing an encoded message in a communication channel.
SIGNALS.zh: 表示通信通道中编码消息的状态序列。

CAPS.en: A close-fitting hat, either brimless or peaked.
CAPS.zh: 一种贴身的帽子，无檐或有檐。

PILL.en: A small, usually round or cylindrical object designed for easy swallowing, usually containing some sort of medication.
PILL.zh: 一种小的、通常为圆形或圆柱形的物体，设计为易于吞咽，通常含有某种药物。

SWING.en: The manner in which something is swung.

SYMBOLS.en: A character or glyph representing an idea, concept or object.
SYMBOLS.zh: 代表想法、概念或对象的字符或字形。

LAT.en: A staff, particularly one of an Indian kind.
LAT.zh: 工作人员，尤其是印度人。

META.en: Self-referential; structured analogously, but at a higher level.
META.zh: 自我参照；结构类似，但层次更高。

HUMANS.en: A human being, whether man, woman or child.
HUMANS.zh: 一个人，无论是男人、女人还是孩子。

ANALOG.en: Something that bears an __y to something else
ANALOG.zh: 与其他事物有类比的事物

FACIAL.en: A personal care beauty treatment which involves cleansing and moisturizing of the human face.
FACIAL.zh: 一种涉及清洁和保湿人脸的个人护理美容护理。

CHOOSING.en: To pick; to make the choice of; to select.
CHOOSING.zh: 去挑选；做出选择；来选择。

DATED.en: To note the time or place of writing or executing; to express in an instrument the time of its execution.
DATED.zh: 注明书写或执行的时间或地点；在文书中表达其执行的时间。

WISDOM.en: An element of personal character that enables one to distinguish the wise from the unwise.
WISDOM.zh: 个人性格的一种元素，使人能够区分智者和不智者。

SHOOT.en: The emerging stem and embryonic leaves of a new plant.
SHOOT.zh: 新植物正在长出的茎和胚叶。

BOUNDARY.en: The dividing line or location between two areas.
BOUNDARY.zh: 两个区域之间的分界线或位置。

MINT.en: A building or institution where money (originally, only coins) is produced under government licence.
MINT.zh: 根据政府许可生产货币（最初仅是硬币）的建筑物或机构。

OFFSET.en: Anything that acts as counterbalance; a compensating equivalent.
OFFSET.zh: 任何起到平衡作用的东西；补偿等价物。

PAYDAY.en: The day of the week or month, or the specific day, on which an employee's wages or salary is paid.
PAYDAY.zh: 支付雇员工资或薪水的星期或月份的某一天或特定的一天。

ELITE.en: A special group or social class of people which have a superior intellectual, social or economic status as, the __ of society.
ELITE.zh: 具有优越智力、社会或经济地位的特殊群体或社会阶层，即社会精英。

BELIEVES.en: To accept as true, particularly without absolute certainty (i.e., as opposed to knowing)
BELIEVES.zh: 接受为真实，特别是在没有绝对确定性的情况下（即，与知道相对）

POEMS.en: A literary piece written in verse.
POEMS.zh: 用诗歌写成的文学作品。

ROBOT.en: A machine built to carry out some complex task or group of tasks by physically moving, especially one which can be programmed.
ROBOT.zh: 一种通过物理移动来执行某些复杂任务或一组任务的机器，尤其是可以编程的机器。

COLLINS.en: Any of various alcoholic drinks made with lemon juice, sugar, and carbonated water.
COLLINS.zh: 由柠檬汁、糖和碳酸水制成的各种酒精饮料。

EQUIPPED.en: To supply with something necessary in order to carry out a specific action or task; to provide with (e.g. weapons, provisions, munitions, rigging)
EQUIPPED.zh: 提供执行特定行动或任务所必需的东西；提供（例如武器、给养、弹药、索具）

WINDS.en: Real or perceived movement of atmospheric air usually caused by convection or differences in air pressure.
WINDS.zh: 通常由对流或气压差异引起的实际或感知的大气运动。

POWDER.en: The fine particles which are the result of reducing dry substance by pounding, grinding, or triturating, or the result of decay; dust.
POWDER.zh: 通过捣碎、研磨或研磨减少干燥物质的结果，或腐烂的结果；灰尘。

ASSESS.en: To determine, estimate or judge the value of; to evaluate
ASSESS.zh: 确定、估计或判断……的价值；评估

WASH.en: The process or an instance of __ing or being __ed by water or other liquid.
WASH.zh: 用水或其他液体清洗或被清洗的过程或实例。

STONES.en: A hard earthen substance that can form large rocks.
STONES.zh: 一种坚硬的土质物质，可以形成大岩石。

ENTRANCE.en: The action of entering, or going in.

GNOME.en: A brief reflection or maxim; a pithy saying.
GNOME.zh: 简短的反思或格言；一句精辟的话。

ROOTS.en: The part of a plant, generally underground, that anchors and supports the plant body, absorbs and stores water and nutrients, and in some plants is able to perform vegetative reproduction.
ROOTS.zh: 植物的一部分，通常位于地下，固定和支撑植物体，吸收和储存水和养分，并且在某些植物中能够进行营养繁殖。

LOSING.en: To cause (something) to cease to be in one's possession or capability due to unfortunate or unknown circumstances, events or reasons.
LOSING.zh: 由于不幸或未知的情况、事件或原因，导致某人不再拥有或无法拥有（某物）。

ATTEMPTS.en: The action of trying at something.

GADGETS.en: A thing whose name cannot be remembered; thingamajig, doohickey.
GADGETS.zh: 名字记不住的东西； thingamajig，doohickey。

NOBLE.en: An aristocrat; one of aristocratic blood.

IMPACTS.en: The striking of one body against another; collision.
IMPACTS.zh: 一个身体撞击另一个身体；碰撞。

REV.en: To increase the speed of a motor, or to operate at a higher speed.
REV.zh: 提高电机的速度，或以更高的速度运行。

GOSPEL.en: The first section of the Christian New Testament scripture, comprising the books of Matthew, Mark, Luke and John, concerned with the life, crucifixion, death, resurrection, and teachings of Jesus.
GOSPEL.zh: 基督教新约圣经的第一部分，包括马太福音、马可福音、路加福音和约翰福音，涉及耶稣的生平、受难、死亡、复活和教义。

SHORE.en: Land adjoining a non-flowing body of water, such as an ocean, lake or pond.
SHORE.zh: 毗邻不流动水体（例如海洋、湖泊或池塘）的土地。

INDUCED.en: To lead by persuasion or influence; incite or prevail upon.
INDUCED.zh: 通过说服或影响来领导；煽动或说服。

AIMS.en: The pointing of a weapon, as a gun, a dart, or an arrow, or object, in the line of direction with the object intended to be struck; the line of fire; the direction of anything, such as a spear, a blow, a discourse, a remark, towards a particular point or object, with a view to strike or affect it.
AIMS.zh: 将武器（如枪、飞镖、箭或物体）指向要攻击的物体的方向；火线；任何事物的方向，例如矛、打击、话语、言论，指向特定的点或物体，以打击或影响它。

LINKING.en: To connect two or more things.

APPEALS.en: An application for the removal of a cause or suit from an inferior to a superior judge or court for re-examination or review.
APPEALS.zh: 向上级法官或法院提出撤销案件或诉讼以进行重新审查或复审的申请。

EARNED.en: To gain (success, reward, recognition) through applied effort or work.
EARNED.zh: 通过努力或工作获得（成功、奖励、认可）。

ILLNESS.en: An instance of a disease or poor health.
ILLNESS.zh: 疾病或健康状况不佳的实例。

CORP.en: A non-commissioned officer army rank with NATO code OR-4. The rank below a sergeant but above a lance __oral and private.
CORP.zh: 军士军衔，北约代码 OR-4。军衔低于中士，但高于一等兵和列兵。

TEENAGE.zh: 用于栅栏和树篱的灌木丛。

SOAP.en: A substance able to mix with both oil and water, used for cleaning, often in the form of a solid bar or in liquid form, derived from fats or made synthetically.
SOAP.zh: 一种能够与油和水混合的物质，用于清洁，通常为固体棒或液体形式，源自脂肪或合成制造。

TRIPLE.en: Three times or thrice the number, amount, size, etc
TRIPLE.zh: 三倍或三倍的数量、金额、大小等

COOPER.en: A craftsman who makes and repairs barrels and similar wooden vessels such as casks, buckets and tubs.
COOPER.zh: 制造和修理木桶和类似木器（如木桶、水桶和盆）的工匠。

JAM.en: A sweet mixture of fruit boiled with sugar and allowed to congeal. Often spread on bread or toast or used in __ tarts.
JAM.zh: 水果的甜味混合物，与糖一起煮沸并凝结。通常涂在面包或吐司上或用于果酱馅饼。

SECURED.en: To make safe; to relieve from apprehensions of, or exposure to, danger; to guard; to protect.
SECURED.zh: 确保安全；解除对危险的忧虑或暴露；守护；保护。

UNUSUAL.zh: 不寻常的事情；一个异常现象。

ANSWERED.en: To make a reply or response to.

SLOTS.en: A broad, flat, wooden bar, a slat, especially as used to secure a door, window, etc.
SLOTS.zh: 一种宽阔、平坦的木条、板条，尤其用于固定门、窗等。

TOOLBAR.en: A row of buttons, usually marked with icons, used to activate the functions of an application or operating system
TOOLBAR.zh: 一排按钮，通常标有图标，用于激活应用程序或操作系统的功能

ROCKS.en: An enormous mythical bird in Eastern legend.
ROCKS.zh: 东方传说中的一种巨大神鸟。

TITANS.en: Something or someone of very large stature, greatness, or godliness.
TITANS.zh: 身材高大、伟大或虔诚的某物或某人。

WEARING.en: To carry or have equipped on or about one's body, as an item of clothing, equipment, decoration, etc.
WEARING.zh: 携带或装备在身体上或周围，作为衣服、设备、装饰品等。

AXIS.en: An imaginary line around which an object spins (an __ of rotation) or is symmetrically arranged (an __ of symmetry).
AXIS.zh: 物体绕其旋转（旋转轴）或对称排列（对称轴）的假想线。

SOUGHT.en: To try to find; to look for; to search for.

GENES.en: A theoretical unit of heredity of living organisms; a gene may take several values and in principle predetermines a precise trait of an organism's form (phenotype), such as hair color.
GENES.zh: 生物体遗传的理论单位；一个基因可能有几个值，并且原则上预先确定了生物体形态（表型）的精确特征，例如头发颜色。

MOUNTED.en: To get upon; to ascend; to climb.

FIREWALL.en: A fireproof barrier used to prevent the spread of fire between or through buildings, structures, electrical substation transformers, or within an aircraft or vehicle.
FIREWALL.zh: 用于防止火灾在建筑物、构筑物、变电站变压器之间或飞机或车辆内蔓延的防火屏障。

MEDIAN.en: A central vein or nerve, especially the __ vein or __ nerve running through the forearm and arm.
MEDIAN.zh: 中央静脉或神经，尤其是穿过前臂和手臂的正中静脉或正中神经。

GUNS.en: A device for projecting a hard object very forcefully; a firearm or cannon.
GUNS.zh: 一种用于非常有力地投射硬物的装置；枪支或大炮。

SCANNER.en: A device which scans documents in order to convert them to a digital medium.
SCANNER.zh: 扫描文档以将其转换为数字介质的设备。

HEREIN.en: Within this content, context, or thing.
HEREIN.zh: 在此内容、上下文或事物中。

ANIMATED.en: To impart motion or the appearance of motion to.
ANIMATED.zh: 赋予运动或运动的外观。

JUDICIAL.en: That branch of government which is responsible for maintaining the courts of law and for the administration of justice.
JUDICIAL.zh: 负责维持法院和司法行政的政府部门。

HERO.en: Somebody who possesses great bravery and carries out extraordinary or noble deeds.
HERO.zh: 具有极大勇气并做出非凡或高尚事迹的人。

BACHELOR.en: A person, especially a man, who is socially regarded as able to marry, but has not yet.
BACHELOR.zh: 一个人，尤其是一个男人，被社会认为可以结婚，但还没有结婚。

ATTITUDE.en: The position of the body or way of carrying oneself.
ATTITUDE.zh: 身体的位置或举止方式。

BASICS.en: A necessary commodity, a staple requirement.

LENSES.en: An object, usually made of glass, that focuses or defocuses the light that passes through it.
LENSES.zh: 通常由玻璃制成的物体，可以对穿过它的光进行聚焦或散焦。

BINARY.en: A thing which can have only (one or the other of) two values.
BINARY.zh: 只能具有（其中一个或另一个）两个值的事物。

GENETICS.en: The branch of biology that deals with the transmission and variation of inherited characteristics, in particular chromosomes and DNA.
GENETICS.zh: 生物学的一个分支，研究遗传特征（特别是染色体和 DNA）的传递和变异。

PUNK.en: A person used for sex, particularly:
PUNK.zh: 用于性行为的人，特别是：

DROPPED.en: To fall in droplets (of a liquid).

DUKE.en: The male ruler of a duchy (female equivalent: duchess).
DUKE.zh: 公国的男性统治者（女性相当于：公爵夫人）。

WAGE.en: (often in plural) An amount of money paid to a worker for a specified quantity of work, usually calculated on an hourly basis and expressed in an amount of money per hour.
WAGE.zh: （通常为复数）支付给工人完成指定工作量的金额，通常按小时计算并以每小时的金额表示。

ARC.en: That part of a circle which a heavenly body appears to pass through as it moves above and below the horizon.
ARC.zh: 天体在地平线上方和下方移动时似乎穿过的圆的一部分。

HOSTS.en: One which receives or entertains a guest, socially, commercially, or officially.
HOSTS.zh: 用于社交、商业或正式接待或招待客人的一种活动。

MOMENTS.en: A brief, unspecified amount of time.
MOMENTS.zh: 一段短暂的、未指定的时间。

ATLAS.en: A bound collection of maps often including tables, illustrations or other text.
ATLAS.zh: 装订好的地图集，通常包括表格、插图或其他文本。

STRINGS.en: A building, wing or dependency set apart and adapted for lodging and feeding (and training) animals with hoofs, especially horses.
STRINGS.zh: 为住宿和喂养（和训练）有蹄动物（尤其是马）而分开的建筑物、翼楼或附属物。

DAWN.en: The morning twilight period immediately before sunrise.

FEELS.en: Of or relating to the emotions.

TORTURE.en: Intentional causing of somebody's experiencing agony
TORTURE.zh: 故意造成某人经历痛苦

CARL.en: A rude, rustic man; a churl.
CARL.zh: 一个粗鲁、土气的人；一个粗鲁的人。

DELETED.en: To remove, get rid of or erase, especially written or printed material, or data on a computer or other device.
DELETED.zh: 删除、消除或擦除，尤其是计算机或其他设备上的书面或印刷材料或数据。

COAT.en: An outer garment covering the upper torso and arms.Wp
COAT.zh: 覆盖上躯干和手臂的外衣。Wp

APP.en: An __lication (program), especially a small one designed for a mobile device.
APP.zh: 一种应用程序（程序），尤其是为移动设备设计的小型应用程序。

EMBEDDED.en: To lay as in a bed; to lay in surrounding matter; to bed.
EMBEDDED.zh: 像躺在床上一样躺着；放置在周围的物质中；上床睡觉。

WIZARD.en: Someone, usually male, who uses (or has skill with) magic, mystic items, and magical and mystical practices.
WIZARD.zh: 使用（或擅长）魔法、神秘物品以及魔法和神秘实践的人，通常是男性。

CORPS.en: A battlefield formation composed of two or more divisions.
CORPS.zh: 由两个或两个以上师组成的战场编队。

ACTORS.en: A person who performs, plays a part in a theatrical play or film.
ACTORS.zh: 在戏剧或电影中表演、扮演角色的人。

LIVER.en: A large organ in the body that stores and metabolizes nutrients, destroys toxins and produces bile. It is responsible for thousands of biochemical reactions.
LIVER.zh: 体内的一个大器官，负责储存和代谢营养物质、消除毒素并产生胆汁。它负责数以千计的生化反应。

LIABLE.en: Bound or obliged in law or equity; responsible; answerable.
LIABLE.zh: Bound or obliged in law or equity;负责任的;有责任的。

BROCHURE.en: A booklet of printed informational matter, like a pamphlet, often for promotional purposes.
BROCHURE.zh: 印刷信息材料的小册子，如小册子，通常用于促销目的。

RECALL.en: The action or fact of calling someone or something back.
RECALL.zh: 给某人或某事回电的行为或事实。

ANTENNA.en: A feeler organ on the head of an insect, crab, or other animal.
ANTENNA.zh: 昆虫、螃蟹或其他动物头上的触角器官。

PICKED.en: To grasp and pull with the fingers or fingernails.
PICKED.zh: 用手指或指甲抓住并拉动。

ASSUMED.en: To authenticate by means of belief; to surmise; to suppose to be true, especially without proof
ASSUMED.zh: 通过信仰来验证；推测；假设是真的，尤其是在没有证据的情况下

BELIEF.en: Mental acceptance of a claim as true.
BELIEF.zh: 在心理上接受某个主张是真实的。

KILLING.en: To put to death; to extinguish the life of.

BIKINI.en: A brief two-piece bathing suit worn by women, especially one that exposes the midriff and navel.
BIKINI.zh: 一种女性穿着的短两件式泳衣，特别是露出腹部和肚脐的泳衣。

SHOULDER.en: The part of an animal's body between the base of the neck and forearm socket.
SHOULDER.zh: 动物身体的位于颈根部和前臂窝之间的部分。

DECOR.en: The style of __ation of a room or building.
DECOR.zh: 房间或建筑物的装饰风格。

TEXTS.en: A writing consisting of multiple glyphs, characters, symbols or sentences.
TEXTS.zh: 由多个字形、字符、符号或句子组成的文字。

BROKERS.en: A mediator between a buyer and seller.
BROKERS.zh: 买方和卖方之间的调解人。

ION.en: An atom or group of atoms bearing an electrical charge, such as the sodium and chlorine atoms in a salt solut__.
ION.zh: 带电荷的原子或原子团，例如盐溶液中的钠原子和氯原子。

DIAMETER.en: Any straight line between two points on the circumference of a circle that passes through the centre/center of the circle.
DIAMETER.zh: 圆周上两点之间穿过圆心的任何直线。

DOLL.en: A toy in the form of a human.

PODCAST.en: An audio programme produced on a regular basis, delivered over the Internet in a compressed digital format and designed for playback on computers or portable digital audio players, such as the iPod.
PODCAST.zh: 定期制作的音频节目，以压缩数字格式通过互联网传送，设计用于在计算机或便携式数字音频播放器（例如 iPod）上播放。

SEASONS.en: Each of the four divisions of a year: spring, summer, autumn (fall) and winter

BIDDER.en: Someone who bids, e.g. at an auction
BIDDER.zh: 出价的人，例如在拍卖会上

SINGER.en: A person who sings, often professionally.
SINGER.zh: 唱歌的人，通常是专业歌手。

HERALD.en: A messenger, especially one bringing important news.
HERALD.zh: 信使，尤其是带来重要消息的信使。

AGING.en: To cause to grow old; to impart the characteristics of age to.

FED.en: A __eral government officer or official, especially FBI, CIA, NSA, ATF, and DEA agents.
FED.zh: 联邦政府官员或官员，尤其是 FBI、CIA、NSA、ATF 和 DEA 特工。

INVITE.en: To ask for the presence or participation of someone or something.
INVITE.zh: 请求某人或某物在场或参与。

LATINAS.zh: 一位拉丁美洲女性。 （比较拉丁裔。）

SUPPOSE.en: To take for granted; to conclude, with less than absolute supporting data; to believe.
SUPPOSE.zh: 认为理所当然；得出结论，缺乏绝对的支持数据；相信。

REED.en: Any of various types of tall stiff perennial grass-like plants growing together in groups near water.
REED.zh: 各种高大坚硬的多年生草状植物，在水边成群生长。

TERROR.zh: 强烈的恐惧、恐惧或害怕。

YOUNGER.en: In the early part of growth or life; born not long ago.
YOUNGER.zh: 在成长或生命的早期阶段；出生不久。

MICE.en: Any small rodent of the genus Mus.
MICE.zh: 鼠属的任何小型啮齿动物。

RAPIDLY.en: With speed; in a rapid manner.

CLERK.en: One who occupationally works with records, accounts, letters, etc.; an office worker.
CLERK.zh: 从事记录、账目、信件等工作的人员；一名办公室职员。

MILLS.en: A grinding apparatus for substances such as grains, seeds, etc.
MILLS.zh: 用于谷物、种子等物质的研磨设备。

HOLLAND.en: A type of linen cloth, originally from __.
HOLLAND.zh: 一种亚麻布，原产于荷兰。

RECEIVES.en: An operation in which data is received.

FONTS.en: A receptacle in a church for holy water, especially one used in baptism.
FONTS.zh: 教堂中盛装圣水的容器，尤其是用于洗礼的容器。

ENT.en: A fictional, large, humanoid, mobile talking tree in works by J. R. R. Tolkien.
ENT.zh: J. R. R. 托尔金 (J. R. R. Tolkien) 作品中虚构的、巨大的、人形的、会说话的树。

WRAP.en: To enclose (an object) completely in any flexible, thin material such as fabric or paper.
WRAP.zh: 将（物体）完全封闭在任何柔性的薄材料中，例如织物或纸张。

MOOD.en: A mental or emotional state, composure.

FAVOR.en: A kind or helpful deed; an instance of voluntarily assisting (someone).
FAVOR.zh: 善行或有益的行为；自愿帮助（某人）的一个例子。

VETERANS.en: A person with long experience of a particular activity.
VETERANS.zh: 对某项特定活动具有长期经验的人。

QUIZ.en: An odd, puzzling or absurd person or thing.
QUIZ.zh: 奇怪的、令人费解的或荒谬的人或事。

SIGMA.en: The eighteenth letter of the Classical and Modern Greek alphabets, the twentieth letter of Old and Ancient.
SIGMA.zh: 古典和现代希腊字母表的第十八个字母，古代和古代的第二十个字母。

VICTIM.en: One that is harmed—killed, injured, subjected to oppression, deceived, or otherwise adversely affected—by someone or something, especially another person or event, force, or condition; in particular:
VICTIM.zh: 受到某人或某事，尤其是另一个人或事件、力量或状况的伤害（被杀、受伤、受到压迫、欺骗或其他不利影响）；尤其：

DEMANDS.en: The desire to purchase goods and services.
DEMANDS.zh: 购买商品和服务的愿望。

SLEEPING.en: To rest in a state of reduced consciousness.
SLEEPING.zh: 在意识减弱的状态下休息。

CAREFUL.en: Taking care; attentive to potential danger, error or harm; cautious.
CAREFUL.zh: 照顾；注意潜在的危险、错误或伤害；谨慎。

EXT.en: __erior (describing the location of a shot in a film script, etc.)
EXT.zh: 外观（描述电影剧本中的镜头位置等）

BEAM.en: Any large piece of timber or iron long in proportion to its thickness, and prepared for use.
BEAM.zh: 任何与其厚度成比例且准备使用的大块木材或铁。

TRACKED.zh: 随着时间的推移继续进行。

MOREOVER.en: In addition to what has been said; furthermore; additionally.
MOREOVER.zh: 除了已经说过的；此外;此外。

MINIMAL.en: The smallest possible amount, quantity, or degree.
MINIMAL.zh: 尽可能小的数量、数量或程度。

LOTTERY.en: A scheme for the distribution of prizes by lot or chance, especially a gaming scheme in which one or more tickets bearing particular numbers draw prizes, the other tickets are blanks.
LOTTERY.zh: 一种通过抽签或机会分配奖品的方案，特别是一种游戏方案，其中一张或多张带有特定号码的彩票抽奖，其他彩票是空白的。

TOPS.en: The highest or uppermost part of something.
TOPS.zh: 某物的最高或最上面的部分。

FRAMED.en: To fit, as for a specific end or purpose; make suitable or comfortable; adapt; adjust.
FRAMED.zh: 适合，如特定的目的或目的；使合适或舒适；适应;调整。

ASIDE.en: An incidental remark made quietly so as to be heard by the person to whom it is said and not by any others in the vicinity.
ASIDE.zh: 轻声说的偶然言论，以便被说这句话的人听到，而不是被附近的任何其他人听到。

LICENCE.en: A legal document giving official permission to do something; a permit.
LICENCE.zh: 正式许可做某事的法律文件；许可证。

ESSAY.en: (authorship) A written composition of moderate length, exploring a particular issue or subject.
ESSAY.zh: （作者身份）长度适中的书面作品，探讨特定问题或主题。

CAMPS.en: An outdoor place acting as temporary accommodation in tents or other temporary structures.
CAMPS.zh: 在帐篷或其他临时建筑中充当临时住所的户外场所。

HANDHELD.en: A personal digital assistant or video game console that is small enough to be held in the hands.
HANDHELD.zh: 体积小到可以握在手中的个人数字助理或视频游戏机。

DISPOSAL.en: An arrangement, categorization or classification of things.
DISPOSAL.zh: 事物的排列、分类或分类。

PACKS.en: A bundle made up and prepared to be carried; especially, a bundle to be carried on the back, but also a load for an animal, a bale.
PACKS.zh: 准备好携带的包裹；特别是，可以背在背上的包裹，也可以是动物的负载，即捆包。

SWITCHES.en: A bundle of thin sticks, typically made of wood, sometimes bond in such a way that binding can be moved so that it varies the tightness of the binding.
SWITCHES.zh: 一捆通常由木头制成的细木棍，有时以这样的方式粘合，即可以移动装订，从而改变装订的松紧度。

CONSULT.zh: 咨询或审议的行为；咨询

GREATLY.en: To a great extent or degree.
GREATLY.zh: 在很大程度上或程度上。

MASK.en: A cover, or partial cover, for the face, used for disguise or protection.
MASK.zh: 脸部的遮盖物或部分遮盖物，用于伪装或保护。

CYCLING.en: To ride a bicycle or other cycle.
CYCLING.zh: 骑自行车或其他自行车。

COMMONLY.zh: 作为一项规则；频繁地;通常

COAL.en: A black rock formed from prehistoric plant remains, composed largely of carbon and burned as a fuel.
COAL.zh: 由史前植物遗骸形成的黑色岩石，主要由碳组成，可作为燃料燃烧。

CRY.en: A shedding of tears; the act of __ing.
CRY.zh: 流下的泪水；哭泣的行为。

QUANTUM.en: The total amount of something; quantity.

INTENT.en: A purpose; something that is intended.

ZOO.en: A park where live animals are exhibited.

LARGELY.en: In a widespread or large manner.
LARGELY.zh: 以广泛或大规模的方式。

SPOKE.en: A support structure that connects the axle or the hub of a wheel to the rim.
SPOKE.zh: 将轮轴或轮毂连接到轮辋的支撑结构。

AKA.zh: __ 的替代字母大小写形式

ARROW.en: A projectile consisting of a shaft, a point and a tail with stabilizing fins that is shot from a bow.
ARROW.zh: 从弓射出的射弹，由轴、尖端和带有稳定翼的尾部组成。

SAMPLING.en: To take or to test a sample or samples of.
SAMPLING.zh: 获取或测试一个或多个样品。

ROUGH.en: The unmowed part of a golf course.
ROUGH.zh: 高尔夫球场未修剪的部分。

TEE.en: The name of the Latin-script letter T.
TEE.zh: 拉丁字母 T 的名称。

LION.en: A big cat, Panthera leo, native to Africa, India and formerly much of Europe.
LION.zh: 一种大型猫科动物，Panthera leo，原产于非洲、印度和以前的欧洲大部分地区。

INSPIRED.en: To infuse into the mind; to communicate to the spirit; to convey, as by a divine or supernatural influence; to disclose preternaturally; to produce in, as by inspiration.
INSPIRED.zh: 注入心灵；与精神沟通；传达，如通过神圣或超自然的影响；异常地披露；产生，如灵感。

HOLES.en: A hollow place or cavity; an excavation; a pit; an opening in or through a solid body, a fabric, etc.; a perforation; a rent; a fissure.
HOLES.zh: 中空的地方或空腔；挖掘；一个坑；固体、织物等中或穿过固体、织物等的开口；穿孔；租金；一条裂缝。

WEDDINGS.en: Marriage ceremony; ritual officially celebrating the beginning of a marriage.
WEDDINGS.zh: 结婚典礼；正式庆祝婚姻开始的仪式。

BLADE.en: The sharp cutting edge of a knife, chisel, or other tool, a razor __/sword.
BLADE.zh: 刀、凿子或其他工具、剃须刀片/剑的锋利切削刃。

SUDDENLY.en: Happening quickly and with little or no warning; in a sudden manner.
SUDDENLY.zh: 发生得很快，几乎没有任何警告；突然地。

OXYGEN.en: The chemical element (symbol O) with an atomic number of 8 and relative atomic mass of 15.9994. It is a colorless and odorless gas.
OXYGEN.zh: 化学元素（符号O），原子序数为8，相对原子质量为15.9994。它是一种无色无味的气体。

COOKIE.en: A small, flat, baked good which is either crisp or soft but firm.
COOKIE.zh: 一种小而扁平的烘焙食品，要么脆，要么软但硬。

MEALS.en: Food that is prepared and eaten, usually at a specific time, and usually in a comparatively large quantity (as opposed to a snack).
MEALS.zh: 通常在特定时间准备和食用的食物，并且通常数量相对较多（而不是零食）。

CANYON.en: A valley, especially a long, narrow, steep valley, cut in rock by a river.
CANYON.zh: 山谷，特指一条又长又窄又陡的山谷，被河流切入岩石中。

METERS.en: (always meter) A device that measures things.

POINTER.en: Anything that points or is used for pointing.
POINTER.zh: 任何指向或用于指向的东西。

PERMITS.en: An artifact or document rendering something allowed or legal.
PERMITS.zh: 呈现允许或合法的事物的工件或文档。

SLEEVE.en: The part of a garment that covers the arm.
SLEEVE.zh: 衣服上覆盖手臂的部分。

CLEANER.en: A person whose occupation is to clean floors, windows and other things.
CLEANER.zh: 职业是清洁地板、窗户和其他东西的人。

CRICKET.en: An insect in the order Orthoptera, especially family Gryllidae, that makes a chirping sound by rubbing its wing casings against combs on its hind legs.
CRICKET.zh: 直翅目昆虫，尤其是蝼蛄科昆虫，通过用翅膀外壳摩擦后腿上的鸡冠来发出鸣叫声。

BEEF.en: The meat from a cow, bull or other bovine.
BEEF.zh: 来自牛、公牛或其他牛的肉。

FEEDING.en: (ditransitive) To give (someone or something) food to eat.
FEEDING.zh: （双及物）给（某人或某物）食物吃。

STROKE.en: An act of stroking (moving one's hand over a surface).
STROKE.zh: 抚摸的行为（在表面上移动手）。

RANKINGS.en: One’s relative placement in a list.
RANKINGS.zh: 一个人在列表中的相对位置。

CAD.en: A low-bred, presuming person; a mean, vulgar fellow.
CAD.zh: 没有教养、自以为是的人；一个卑鄙、粗俗的家伙。

HATS.en: A covering for the head, often in the approximate form of a cone or a cylinder closed at its top end, and sometimes having a brim and other decoration.
HATS.zh: 头部的覆盖物，通常呈顶端封闭的圆锥体或圆柱体的近似形状，有时具有边缘和其他装饰。

ROBIN.en: Any of various passerine birds (about 100 species) of the families Muscicapidae, Turdidae and Petroicidae (formerly Eopsaltriidae), typically with a red breast.
ROBIN.zh: 鹪鹩科、鸫科和鸫科（以前称为 Eopsaltriidae）的各种雀形目鸟类（约 100 种），通常有红色胸部。

STRAP.en: A long, narrow, pliable strip of leather, cloth, or the like.
STRAP.zh: 一条又长又窄、柔韧的皮革、布料或类似物。

CROWD.en: A group of people congregated or collected into a close body without order.
CROWD.zh: 一群人无秩序地聚集或聚集成一个紧密的身体。

SURF.en: Waves that break on an ocean shoreline.

REMAINED.en: To stay behind while others withdraw; to be left after others have been removed or destroyed; to be left after a number or quantity has been subtracted or cut off; to be left as not included or comprised.
REMAINED.zh: 当其他人撤退时，留在后面；在其他人被移除或毁坏后被留下；减去或截去某个数字或数量后剩下的；保留为不包含或包含。

ENTITIES.en: That which has a distinct existence as an individual unit. Often used for organisations which have no physical form.
ENTITIES.zh: 作为一个单独的单位具有独特的存在。通常用于没有物理形式的组织。

CUSTOMS.en: (in the plural) The duties or taxes imposed on imported or exported goods.
CUSTOMS.zh: （复数）对进出口货物征收的关税或税款。

RAINBOW.en: A multicoloured arch in the sky, produced by prismatic refraction of light within droplets of rain in the air.
RAINBOW.zh: 天空中的五彩拱门是由空气中的雨滴中的光的棱镜折射产生的。

HOOK.en: A rod bent into a curved shape, typically with one end free and the other end secured to a rope or other attachment.
HOOK.zh: 弯曲成弯曲形状的杆，通常一端自由，另一端固定在绳子或其他附件上。

ROULETTE.en: A game of chance, in which a small ball is made to move round rapidly on a circle divided off into numbered red and black spaces, the one on which it stops indicating the result of a variety of wagers permitted by the game.
ROULETTE.zh: 一种机会游戏，其中一个小球在一个分为红色和黑色编号的圆圈上快速移动，它停止的位置指示游戏允许的各种投注的结果。

GLOVES.en: An item of clothing other than a mitten, covering all or part of the hand and fingers, but usually allowing independent movement of the fingers.
GLOVES.zh: 除手套外的一种衣服，覆盖全部或部分手和手指，但通常允许手指独立运动。

CORD.en: A harmonic set of three or more notes that is heard as if sounding simultaneously.
CORD.zh: 由三个或更多音符组成的和声组，听起来就像同时发声一样。

CLOUD.zh: 一块岩石；巨石;一座小山。

VALVE.en: A device that controls the flow of a gas or fluid through a pipe.
VALVE.zh: 控制气体或液体通过管道流动的装置。

EXPLAINS.en: To make plain, manifest, or intelligible; to clear of obscurity; to illustrate the meaning of.
EXPLAINS.zh: 使明白、明显或易于理解；消除晦涩难懂；来说明其含义。

FEELINGS.zh: 感觉，尤其是通过皮肤的感觉。

KNIFE.en: A utensil or a tool designed for cutting, consisting of a flat piece of hard material, usually steel or other metal (the blade), usually sharpened on one edge, attached to a handle. The blade may be pointed for piercing.
KNIFE.zh: 一种设计用于切割的器具或工具，由一块平坦的硬质材料组成，通常是钢或其他金属（刀片），通常在一个边缘上锋利，附在手柄上。刀片可以尖头用于刺穿。

SHELF.en: A flat, rigid structure, fixed at right angles to a wall or forming a part of a cabinet, desk etc., and used to support, store or display objects.
SHELF.zh: 一种平坦的刚性结构，以直角固定在墙壁上或形成橱柜、桌子等的一部分，用于支撑、存储或展示物体。

TIMING.en: To measure or record the time, duration, or rate of.
TIMING.zh: 测量或记录时间、持续时间或速率。

LIKED.en: To enjoy, be pleased by; favor; be in favor of.
LIKED.zh: 享受，感到高兴；青睐；赞成。

ADOPT.en: To take by choice into relationship (a child, heir, friend, citizen, etc.)
ADOPT.zh: 选择建立关系（孩子、继承人、朋友、公民等）

FREEWARE.en: Complete and functional software that does not require payment or other compensation (such as nags or advertising) for its use. __ may be a proprietary license with no access to the source code.
FREEWARE.zh: 完整且功能齐全的软件，使用时不需要付费或其他补偿（例如广告或广告）。免费软件可能是专有许可证，无法访问源代码。
